<h1>Psalm 1</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> who hath not walked in the counsel of the ungodly, nor stood in the way of sinners, nor sat in the chair of pestilence:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> But his will is in the <a href="../cathen/14779c.htm">law</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and on his law he shall meditate day and night.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> And he shall be like a tree which is planted near the running waters, which shall bring forth its fruit, in due season. And his leaf shall not fall off: and all whatsoever he shall do shall prosper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Not so the wicked, not so: but like the dust, which the wind driveth from the face of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Therefore the wicked shall not rise again in judgment: nor sinners in the council of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> knoweth the way of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>: and the way of the wicked shall perish.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="psa001001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Beatus vir qui non abiit in consilio impiorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in via peccatorum non stetit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in cathedra pestilenti&aelig; non sedit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa001002vul">2</span>&nbsp;sed in lege Domini voluntas ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in lege ejus meditabitur die ac nocte.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa001003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Et erit tamquam lignum quod plantatum est secus decursus aquarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quod fructum suum dabit in tempore suo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et folium ejus non defluet;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnia qu&aelig;cumque faciet prosperabuntur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa001004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Non sic impii, non sic;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sed tamquam pulvis quem projicit ventus a facie terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa001005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Ideo non resurgent impii in judicio,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque peccatores in concilio justorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa001006vul">6</span>&nbsp;quoniam novit Dominus viam justorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et iter impiorum peribit.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
