<h1>Psalm 2</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Why have the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> raged, and the people devised vain things?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The kings of the earth stood up, and the princes met together, against the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and against his <a href="../cathen/10212c.htm">Christ</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let us break their bonds asunder: and let us cast away their yoke from us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He that dwelleth in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> shall laugh at them: and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall deride them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Then shall he speak to them in his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a>, and trouble them in his rage.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> But I am appointed king by him over Sion, his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> mountain, preaching his commandment.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath said to me: Thou art my son, this day have I begotten thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Ask of me, and I will give thee the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> for thy inheritance, and the utmost parts of the earth for thy possession.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Thou shalt rule them with a rod of iron, and shalt break them in pieces like a potter's vessel.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> And now, O ye kings, understand: receive instruction, you that judge the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Serve ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with fear: and rejoice unto him with trembling.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Embrace discipline, lest at any time the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a>, and you perish from the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> When his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> shall be kindled in a short time, <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> are all they that trust in him.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="psa002001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Quare fremuerunt gentes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et populi meditati sunt inania?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Astiterunt reges terr&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et principes convenerunt in unum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adversus Dominum, et adversus christum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Dirumpamus vincula eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et projiciamus a nobis jugum ipsorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Qui habitat in c&aelig;lis irridebit eos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus subsannabit eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Tunc loquetur ad eos in ira sua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in furore suo conturbabit eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ego autem constitutus sum rex ab eo</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super Sion, montem sanctum ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pr&aelig;dicans pr&aelig;ceptum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Dominus dixit ad me: Filius meus es tu;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego hodie genui te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Postula a me, et dabo tibi gentes h&aelig;reditatem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et possessionem tuam terminos terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Reges eos in virga ferrea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tamquam vas figuli confringes eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Et nunc, reges, intelligite;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> erudimini, qui judicatis terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Servite Domino in timore,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsultate ei cum tremore.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Apprehendite disciplinam, nequando irascatur Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et pereatis de via justa.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa002013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Cum exarserit in brevi ira ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> beati omnes qui confidunt in eo.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
