<h1>Psalm 3</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The psalm of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> when he fled from the face of his son <a href="../cathen/01058c.htm">Absalom</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Why, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, are they multiplied that afflict me? many are they who rise up against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Many say to my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: There is no salvation for him in his <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> But thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, art my protector, my <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>, and the lifter up of my head.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I have cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with my voice: and he hath heard me from his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> hill.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> I have slept and have taken my rest: and I have risen up, because the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath protected me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I will not fear thousands of the people surrounding me: arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; save me, O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For thou hast struck all them who are my adversaries without cause: thou hast broken the teeth of sinners.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Salvation is of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and thy <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a> is upon thy people.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa003001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, cum fugeret a facie Absalom filii sui.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa003002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, quid multiplicati sunt qui tribulant me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Multi insurgunt adversum me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003003vul">3</span>&nbsp;multi dicunt anim&aelig; me&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non est salus ipsi in Deo ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Tu autem Domine, susceptor meus es,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> gloria mea, et exaltans caput meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Voce mea ad Dominum clamavi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaudivit me de monte sancto suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ego dormivi, et soporatus sum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsurrexi, quia Dominus suscepit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Non timebo millia populi circumdantis me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Exsurge, Domine; salvum me fac, Deus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Quoniam tu percussisti omnes adversantes mihi sine causa;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dentes peccatorum contrivisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa003009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Domini est salus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super populum tuum benedictio tua.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
