<h1>Psalm 5</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for her that obtaineth the inheritance. A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>For her that obtaineth the inheritance...</strong> That is, for the <a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">church of Christ</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Give ear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to my words, understand my cry.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Hearken to the voice of my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, O my King and my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For to thee will I <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">pray</a>: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in the morning thou shalt hear my voice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> In the morning I will stand before thee, and I will see: because thou art not a <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> that willest <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Neither shall the wicked dwell near thee: nor shall the unjust abide before thy eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Thou <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hatest</a> all the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: thou wilt destroy all that speak a lie. The bloody and the deceitful <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will abhor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> But as for me in the multitude of thy mercy, I will come into thy house; I will worship towards thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>, in thy fear.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Conduct me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: because of my enemies, direct my way in thy sight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For there is no <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> in their mouth: their heart is vain.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Their throat is an open sepulchre: they dealt deceitfully with their tongues: judge them, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. Let them fall from their devices: according to the multitude of their <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickednesses</a> cast them out: for they have provoked thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> But let all them be glad that hope in thee: they shall rejoice for ever, and thou shalt dwell in them. And all they that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> shall <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> in thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For thou wilt <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>. O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou hast crowned us, as with a shield of thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> will.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa005001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro ea qu&aelig; h&aelig;reditatem consequitur. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa005002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Verba mea auribus percipe, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intellige clamorem meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Intende voci orationis me&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> rex meus et Deus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quoniam ad te orabo, Domine:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mane exaudies vocem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Mane astabo tibi, et videbo</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam non Deus volens iniquitatem tu es.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Neque habitabit juxta te malignus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque permanebunt injusti ante oculos tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Odisti omnes qui operantur iniquitatem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> perdes omnes qui loquuntur mendacium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Virum sanguinum et dolosum abominabitur Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Ego autem in multitudine misericordi&aelig; tu&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> introibo in domum tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adorabo ad templum sanctum tuum in timore tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Domine, deduc me in justitia tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter inimicos meos dirige in conspectu tuo viam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam non est in ore eorum veritas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cor eorum vanum est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Sepulchrum patens est guttur eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> linguis suis dolose agebant:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> judica illos, Deus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Decidant a cogitationibus suis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum multitudinem impietatum eorum expelle eos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam irritaverunt te, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et l&aelig;tentur omnes qui sperant in te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in &aelig;ternum exsultabunt, et habitabis in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et gloriabuntur in te omnes qui diligunt nomen tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa005013vul">13</span>&nbsp;quoniam tu benedices justo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, ut scuto bon&aelig; voluntatis tu&aelig; coronasti nos.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
