<h1>Psalm 6</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, in verses, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, for the octave. <span class="stiki"><strong>For the octave...</strong> That is, to be sung on an instrument of eight strings. <a href="../cathen/02084a.htm">St. Augustine</a> understands it mystically, of the <a href="../cathen/12792a.htm">last resurrection</a>, and the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">world to come</a>; which is, as it were, the octave, or eighth day, after the seven days of this mortal life: and for this octave, sinners must dispose themselves, like <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, by bewailing their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>, whilst they are here upon earth.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, rebuke me not in thy indignation, nor chastise me in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I am weak: heal me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for my bones are troubled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is troubled exceedingly: but thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, how long?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Turn to me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and deliver my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: O save me for thy mercy's sake.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For there is no one in death, that is mindful of thee: and who shall confess to thee in hell?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I have laboured in my groanings, every night I will wash my bed: I will water my couch with my tears.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> My eye is troubled through indignation: I have grown old amongst all my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Depart from me, all ye workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath heard the voice of my weeping.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath heard my supplication: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath received my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Let all my enemies be ashamed, and be very much troubled: let them be turned back, and be ashamed very speedily.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa006001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, in carminibus. Psalmus David. Pro octava.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa006002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, ne in furore tuo arguas me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque in ira tua corripias me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Domine, quoniam infirmus sum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sana me, Domine, quoniam conturbata sunt ossa mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Et anima mea turbata est valde;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sed tu, Domine, usquequo?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Convertere, Domine, et eripe animam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvum me fac propter misericordiam tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Quoniam non est in morte qui memor sit tui;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in inferno autem quis confitebitur tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Laboravi in gemitu meo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> lavabo per singulas noctes lectum meum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> lacrimis meis stratum meum rigabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Turbatus est a furore oculus meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inveteravi inter omnes inimicos meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Discedite a me omnes qui operamini iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam exaudivit Dominus vocem fletus mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Exaudivit Dominus deprecationem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus orationem meam suscepit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa006011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Erubescant, et conturbentur vehementer, omnes inimici mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> convertantur, et erubescant valde velociter.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
