<h1>Psalm 7</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The psalm of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, which he sung to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for the words of Chusi, the son of Jemini.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in thee have I put my trust; same me from all them that persecute me, and deliver me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Lest at any time he seize upon my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> like a lion, while there is no one to <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> me, nor to save.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, if I have done this thing, if there be <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> in my hands:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> If I have rendered to them that repaid me <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a>, let me deservedly fall empty before my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Let the enemy pursue my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and take it, and tread down my life, on the earth, and bring down my <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the dust.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Rise up, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a>: and be thou exalted in the borders of my enemies. And arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in the precept which thou hast commanded:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And a congregation of people shall surround thee. And for their sakes return thou on high.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> judgeth the people. Judge me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, according to my <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and according to my innocence in me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a> of sinners shall be brought to nought; and thou shalt direct the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>: the searcher of hearts and reins is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Just is my help from the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; who saveth the upright of heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is a <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> judge, strong and patient: is he <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> every day?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Except you will be converted, he will brandish his sword; he hath bent his bow, and made it ready.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And in it he hath prepared to instruments of death, he hath made ready his arrows for them that burn. <span class="stiki"><strong>For them that burn...</strong> That is, against the <a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">persecutors</a> of his <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Behold he hath been in labour with <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">injustice</a>: he hath conceived sorrow, and brought forth <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> He hath opened a pit and dug it: and he is fallen into the hole he made.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> His sorrow shall be turned on his own head: and his <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> shall come down upon his crown.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> I will give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> according to his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: and will sing to the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> the most high.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa007001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, quem cantavit Domino pro verbis Chusi, filii Jemini.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa007002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus meus, in te speravi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvum me fac ex omnibus persequentibus me, et libera me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007003vul">3</span>&nbsp;nequando rapiat ut leo animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dum non est qui redimat, neque qui salvum faciat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus meus, si feci istud,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> si est iniquitas in manibus meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007005vul">5</span>&nbsp;si reddidi retribuentibus mihi mala,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> decidam merito ab inimicis meis inanis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Persequatur inimicus animam meam, et comprehendat;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et conculcet in terra vitam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gloriam meam in pulverem deducat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Exsurge, Domine, in ira tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltare in finibus inimicorum meorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsurge, Domine Deus meus, in pr&aelig;cepto quod mandasti,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007008vul">8</span>&nbsp;et synagoga populorum circumdabit te:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et propter hanc in altum regredere:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Dominus judicat populos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Judica me, Domine, secundum justitiam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum innocentiam meam super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Consumetur nequitia peccatorum, et diriges justum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> scrutans corda et renes, Deus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Justum adjutorium meum a Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui salvos facit rectos corde.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Deus judex justus, fortis, et patiens;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> numquid irascitur per singulos dies?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Nisi conversi fueritis, gladium suum vibrabit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> arcum suum tetendit, et paravit illum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Et in eo paravit vasa mortis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sagittas suas ardentibus effecit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Ecce parturiit injustitiam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> concepit dolorem, et peperit iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Lacum aperuit, et effodit eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et incidit in foveam quam fecit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Convertetur dolor ejus in caput ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in verticem ipsius iniquitas ejus descendet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa007018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Confitebor Domino secundum justitiam ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et psallam nomini Domini altissimi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
