<h1>Psalm 8</h1> <!--ce=y-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the presses: a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>The presses...</strong> In <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a>, <em>Gittith</em>, supposed to be a musical instrument.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, our Lord, how admirable is thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> in the whole earth! For thy magnificence is elevated above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Out of the mouth of infants and of sucklings thou hast perfected praise, because of thy enemies, that thou mayst destroy the enemy and the avenger.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For I will behold thy <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, the works of thy fingers: the moon and the stars which thou hast founded.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> What is <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>, that thou art mindful of him? or the <a href="../cathen/14144a.htm">son of man</a>, that thou visitest him?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Thou hast made him a little less than the <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a>, thou hast crowned him with <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> and honour:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> And hast set him over the works of thy hands.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Thou hast subjected all things under his feet, all sheep and oxen: moreover, the beasts also of the fields.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> The birds of the air, and the fishes of the sea, that pass through the paths of the sea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, our Lord, how admirable is thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> in the whole earth!</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa008001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro torcularibus. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa008002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, Dominus noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam elevata est magnificentia tua super c&aelig;los.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Ex ore infantium et lactentium perfecisti laudem propter inimicos tuos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut destruas inimicum et ultorem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quoniam videbo c&aelig;los tuos, opera digitorum tuorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> lunam et stellas qu&aelig; tu fundasti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quid est homo, quod memor es ejus?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut filius hominis, quoniam visitas eum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Minuisti eum paulominus ab angelis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> gloria et honore coronasti eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008007vul">7</span>&nbsp;et constituisti eum super opera manuum tuarum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Omnia subjecisti sub pedibus ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oves et boves universas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> insuper et pecora campi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008009vul">9</span>&nbsp;volucres c&aelig;li, et pisces maris</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui perambulant semitas maris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa008010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Domine, Dominus noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quam admirabile est nomen tuum in universa terra!</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
