<h1>Psalm 9</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church praises God for his protection against her enemies.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used by many popular Bible translations, this psalm is split into two parts, called <strong>Psalm 9</strong> and <strong>Psalm 10</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the hidden things of the Son. A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>The hidden things of the Son...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humility</a> and sufferings of <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a>, the <a href="../cathen/14142b.htm">Son of God</a>; and of <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> <a href="../cathen/03712a.htm">Christians</a>, who are his sons by <a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">adoption</a>; are called hidden things, with regard to the children of this world, who know not the value and merit of them.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I will give praise to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, with my whole heart: I will relate all thy wonders.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> I will be glad, and rejoice in thee: I will sing to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O thou most high.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> When my enemy shall be turned back: they shall be weakened, and perish before thy face.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For thou hast maintained my judgment and my cause: thou hast sat on the throne, who judgest <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Thou hast rebuked the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>, and the <a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">wicked one</a> hath perished; thou hast blotted out their <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The swords of the enemy have failed unto the end: and their cities thou hast destroyed. Their memory hath perished with a noise:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> But the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> remaineth for ever. He hath prepared his throne in judgment:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> And he shall judge the world in equity, he shall judge the people in <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is become a refuge for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: a helper in due time in tribulation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And let them trust in thee who know thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: for thou hast not forsaken them that seek thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who dwelleth in Sion: declare his ways among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For requiring their blood, he hath remembered them: he hath not forgotten the cry of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: see my humiliation which I suffer from my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Thou that liftest me up from the gates of death, that I may declare all thy praises in the gates of the daughter of Sion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I will rejoice in thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> have stuck fast in the destruction which they prepared. Their foot hath been taken in the very snare which they hid.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall be known when he executeth judgments: the sinner hath been caught in the works of his own hands.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> shall be turned into hell, all the nations that forget <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> For the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> shall not be forgotten to the end: the patience of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> shall not perish for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, let not <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> be strengthened: let the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> be judged in thy sight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Appoint, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, a lawgiver over them: that the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> may know themselves to be but <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.
<p><span class="stiki">The Masoretic (Hebrew) version of <strong>Psalm 10</strong> begins here.</span></p>
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Why, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, hast thou retired afar off? why dost thou slight us in our wants, in the time of trouble?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Whilst the wicked <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> is <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a>, the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> is set on fire: they are caught in the counsels which they devise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> For the sinner is praised in the desires of his <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: and the unjust <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> is <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> The sinner hath provoked the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, according to the multitude of his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>, he will not seek him:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is not before his eyes: his ways are filthy at all times. Thy judgments are removed form his sight: he shall rule over all his enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> For he hath said in his heart: I shall not be moved from <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>, and shall be without <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> His mouth is full of <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">cursing</a>, and of bitterness, and of deceit: under his tongue are labour and sorrow.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> He sitteth in ambush with the rich, in <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">private places</a>, that he may kill the innocent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> His eyes are upon the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>: he lieth in wait, in secret, like a lion in his den. He lieth in ambush, that he may catch the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>: so catch the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->, whilst he draweth him to him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> In his net he will bring him down, he will crouch and fall, when he shall have power over the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> For he hath said in his heart: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath forgotten, he hath turned away his face, not to see to the end.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a>, let thy hand be exalted: forget not the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> Wherefore hath the wicked provoked <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>? for he hath said in his heart: He will not require it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> Thou seest it, for thou considerest labour and sorrow: that thou mayst deliver them into thy hands. To thee is the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> left: thou wilt be a helper to the orphan.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> Break thou the arm of the sinner and of the malignant: his <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a> shall be sought, and shall not be found.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall reign to eternity, yea, for ever and ever: ye <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> shall perish from his land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath heard the desire of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: thy ear hath heard the preparation of their heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> To judge for the fatherless and for the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a>, that <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> may no more presume to magnify himself upon earth.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

