<h1>Psalm 13</h1>
<div class="h1a">The general corruption of man before our redemption by Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 14</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa012.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 13</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> The fool hath said in his heart: There is no <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. They are corrupt, and are become abominable in their ways: there is none that doth <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, no not one.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath looked down from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> upon the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>, to see if there be any that understand and seek <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> They are all gone aside, they are become unprofitable together: there is none that doth <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: no not one. Their throat is an open sepulchre; with their tongues they acted deceitfully: the poison of asps is under their lips. Their mouth is full of <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">cursing</a> and bitterness; their feet are swift to shed blood. Destruction and unhappiness in their ways; and the way of peace they have not known: there is no fear of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> before their eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Shall not all they know that work <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>, who devour my people as they eat bread?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They have not called upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: there have they trembled for fear, where there was no fear.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is in the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>: you have confounded the counsel of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>; but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is his hope.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Who shall give out of Sion the <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>? when the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall have turned away the captivity of his people, <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> shall rejoice, and <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> shall be glad.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa013001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Dixit insipiens in corde suo: Non est Deus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Corrupti sunt, et abominabiles facti sunt in studiis suis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non est qui faciat bonum, non est usque ad unum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dominus de c&aelig;lo prospexit super filios hominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut videat si est intelligens, aut requirens Deum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Omnes declinaverunt, simul inutiles facti sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non est qui faciat bonum, non est usque ad unum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sepulchrum patens est guttur eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> linguis suis dolose agebant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Venenum aspidum sub labiis eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quorum os maledictione et amaritudine plenum est;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> veloces pedes eorum ad effundendum sanguinem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Contritio et infelicitas in viis eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et viam pacis non cognoverunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non est timor Dei ante oculos eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Nonne cognoscent omnes qui operantur iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui devorant plebem meam sicut escam panis?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dominum non invocaverunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> illic trepidaverunt timore, ubi non erat timor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Quoniam Dominus in generatione justa est:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> consilium inopis confudistis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam Dominus spes ejus est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa013007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quis dabit ex Sion salutare Isra&euml;l?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Cum averterit Dominus captivitatem plebis su&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exsultabit Jacob, et l&aelig;tabitur Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
