<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS" href="http://feeds.newadvent.org/bestoftheweb?format=xml"><link rel="icon" href="../images/icon1.ico" type="image/x-icon"><link rel="shortcut icon" href="../images/icon1.ico" type="image/x-icon"><meta name="robots" content="noodp"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="../utility/screen.css" media="screen"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="../utility/print.css" media="print"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="../utility/handheld.css" media="handheld"></head>
<body class="bible" id="psa015.htm">
<div id="capitalcity"> <script type="text/javascript" src="../utility/box0.js"></script><table summary="Logo" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="100%"><tr valign="bottom"><td align="left"><a href="../"><img height=36 width=153 border="0"alt="New Advent" src="../images/logo.gif"></a></td><td align="right"> <form id="searchbox_000299817191393086628:ifmbhlr-8x0" action="http://www.newadvent.org/utility/search.htm"> <input type="hidden" name="safe" value="active"> <input type="hidden" name="cx" value="000299817191393086628:ifmbhlr-8x0" /> <input name="q" type="text" size="25" /> <input type="submit" name="sa" value="Search" /> <input type="hidden" name="cof" value="FORID:9" /> </form><table summary="Spacer" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td height="2"></td></tr></table> <table summary="Tabs" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr> <td bgcolor="#ffffff"></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_color_on_beige" href="../">&nbsp;Home&nbsp;</a></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_color_on_beige" href="../cathen/">&nbsp;Encyclopedia&nbsp;</a></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_color_on_beige" href="../summa/">&nbsp;Summa&nbsp;</a></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_color_on_beige" href="../fathers/">&nbsp;Fathers&nbsp;</a></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_white_on_color" href="../bible/">&nbsp;Bible&nbsp;</a></td> <td class="tab"><a class="tab_color_on_beige" href="../library/">&nbsp;Library&nbsp;</a></td>  </tr></table> </td> </tr></table><table summary="Alphabetical index" width="100%" cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td class="bar_white_on_color"> <a href="../cathen/a.htm">&nbsp;A&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/b.htm">&nbsp;B&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/c.htm">&nbsp;C&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/d.htm">&nbsp;D&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/e.htm">&nbsp;E&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/f.htm">&nbsp;F&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/g.htm">&nbsp;G&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/h.htm">&nbsp;H&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/i.htm">&nbsp;I&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/j.htm">&nbsp;J&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/k.htm">&nbsp;K&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/l.htm">&nbsp;L&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/m.htm">&nbsp;M&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/n.htm">&nbsp;N&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/o.htm">&nbsp;O&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/p.htm">&nbsp;P&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/q.htm">&nbsp;Q&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/r.htm">&nbsp;R&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/s.htm">&nbsp;S&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/t.htm">&nbsp;T&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/u.htm">&nbsp;U&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/v.htm">&nbsp;V&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/w.htm">&nbsp;W&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/x.htm">&nbsp;X&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/y.htm">&nbsp;Y&nbsp;</a><a href="../cathen/z.htm">&nbsp;Z&nbsp;</a> </td></tr></table></div>
<div id="mi5"><span class="breadcrumbs"><a href="../">Home</a> > <a href="../bible/">Bible</a> > <a href="../bible/psa000.htm">Psalms</a> > Psalm 15</span></div>

<div id="shelbyville">
<script type="text/javascript" src="../utility/flanders.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="../utility/smithers.js"></script>
</div>

<div id="springfield">
<span class="navb">< <a href="../bible/psa014.htm">BACK</a> | <a href="../bible/psa016.htm">NEXT</a> ></span>
<h1>Psalm 15</h1>
<div class="h1a">Christ's future victory and triumph over the world and death.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 16</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa014.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 15</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The inscription of a title to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Preserve me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I have put my trust in thee. <span class="stiki"><strong>The inscription of a title...</strong> That is, of a pillar or monument, <em>steylographia</em>: which is as much as to say, that this <a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">psalm</a> is most worthy to be engraved on an everlasting monument.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I have said to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, for thou hast no need of my goods.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> To the saints, who are in his land, he hath made wonderful all my desires in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Their infirmities were multiplied: afterwards they made haste. I will not gather together their meetings for blood offerings: nor will I be mindful of their <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">names</a> by my lips.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the portion of my inheritance and of my cup: it is thou that wilt restore my inheritance to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The lines are fallen unto me in goodly places: for my inheritance is goodly to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I will <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who hath given me understanding: moreover, my reins also have corrected me even till night.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> I set the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> always in my sight: for he is at my right hand, that I be not moved.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Therefore my heart hath been glad, and my tongue hath rejoiced: moreover, my flesh also shall rest in hope.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Because thou wilt not leave my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> in hell; nor wilt thou give thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> one to see corruption.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<!--note missing psalm 15:11 in the vulgate-->
<!--note--><p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Thou hast made known to me the ways of life, thou shalt fill me with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> with thy countenance: at thy right hand are delights even to the end.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa015001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Tituli inscriptio, ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Conserva me, Domine, quoniam speravi in te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dixi Domino: Deus meus es tu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam bonorum meorum non eges.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Sanctis qui sunt in terra ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mirificavit omnes voluntates meas in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Multiplicat&aelig; sunt infirmitates eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> postea acceleraverunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non congregabo conventicula eorum de sanguinibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec memor ero nominum eorum per labia mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dominus pars h&aelig;reditatis me&aelig;, et calicis mei:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tu es qui restitues h&aelig;reditatem meam mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Funes ceciderunt mihi in pr&aelig;claris;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> etenim h&aelig;reditas mea pr&aelig;clara est mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Benedicam Dominum qui tribuit mihi intellectum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> insuper et usque ad noctem increpuerunt me renes mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Providebam Dominum in conspectu meo semper:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam a dextris est mihi, ne commovear.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Propter hoc l&aelig;tatum est cor meum, et exsultavit lingua mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> insuper et caro mea requiescet in spe.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa015010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam non derelinques animam meam in inferno,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec dabis sanctum tuum videre corruptionem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Notas mihi fecisti vias vit&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adimplebis me l&aelig;titia cum vultu tuo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> delectationes in dextera tua usque in finem.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
