<h1>Psalm 17</h1>
<div class="h1a">David's thanks to God for his delivery from all his enemies.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 18</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa016.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 17</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, the servant of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who spoke to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> the words of this canticle, in the day that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> delivered him from the hand of all his enemies, and from the hand of <a href="../cathen/13486d.htm">Saul</a>: and he said:</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I will <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my strength:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my <a href="../cathen/06079b.htm">firmament</a>, my refuge, and my deliverer. My <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is my helper, and in him will I put my trust. My protector, and the horn of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, and my support.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Praising, I will call upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and I shall be saved from my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The sorrows of death surrounded me: and the torrents of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> troubled me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The sorrows of hell encompassed me: and the snares of death prevented me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> In my affliction I called upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and I cried to my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: And he heard my voice from his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>: and my cry before him came into his ears.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The earth shook and trembled: the foundations of the mountains were troubled and were moved, because he was <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> with them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> There went up a smoke in his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>: and a fire flamed from his face: coals were kindled by it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> He bowed the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, and came down, and darkness was under his feet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And he ascended upon the <a href="../cathen/03646c.htm">cherubim</a>, and he flew; he flew upon the wings of the winds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And he made darkness his covert, his pavilion round about him: dark waters in the clouds of the air.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> At the brightness that was before him the clouds passed, hail and coals of fire.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> thundered from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>, and the Highest gave his voice: hail and coals of fire.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And he sent forth his arrows, and he scattered them: he multiplied lightnings, and troubled them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Then the fountains of waters appeared, and the foundations of the world were discovered: At thy rebuke, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, at the blast of the spirit of thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> He sent from on high, and took me: and received me out of many waters.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> He delivered me from my strongest enemies, and from them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> me: for they were too strong for me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> They prevented me in the day of my affliction: and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> became my protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> And he brought me forth into a large place: he saved me, because he was well pleased with me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will reward me according to my <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>; and will repay me according to the cleanness of my hands:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Because I have kept the ways of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; and have not done <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedly</a> against my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> For all his judgments are in my sight: and his justices I have not put away from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> And I shall be spotless with him: and shall keep myself from my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will reward me according to my <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: and according to the cleanness of my hands before his eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> With the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> thou wilt be <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>; and with the innocent <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> thou wilt be innocent:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> And with the <a href="../cathen/05374a.htm">elect</a> thou wilt be <a href="../cathen/05374a.htm">elect</a>: and with the perverse thou wilt be perverted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> For thou wilt save the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> people; but wilt bring down the eyes of the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> For thou lightest my lamp, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, enlighten my darkness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> For by thee I shall be delivered from temptation; and through my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> I shall go over a wall.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> As for my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, his way is undefiled: the words of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> are fire-tried: he is the protector of all that trust in him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> For who is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>? or who is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> but our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who hath girt me with strength; and made my way blameless.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> Who hath made my feet like the feet of harts: and who setteth me upon high places.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> Who teacheth my hands to <a href="../cathen/15546c.htm">war</a>: and thou hast made my arms like a brazen bow.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> And thou hast given me the protection of thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: and thy right hand hath held me up: And thy discipline hath corrected me unto the end: and thy discipline, the same shall teach me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> Thou hast enlarged my steps under me; and my feet are not weakened.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> I will pursue after my enemies, and overtake them: and I will not turn again till they are consumed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> I will break them, and they shall not be able to stand: they shall fall under my feet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> And thou hast girded me with strength unto battle; and hast subdued under me them that rose up against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse41">41</span> And thou hast made my enemies turn their back upon me, and hast destroyed them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse42">42</span> They cried, but there was none to save them, to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: but he heard them not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse43">43</span> And I shall beat them as small as the dust before the wind; I shall bring them to nought, like the dirt in the streets.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse44">44</span> Thou wilt deliver me from the contradictions of the people; thou wilt make me head of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse45">45</span> A people which I knew not, hath served me: at the hearing of the ear they have <a href="../cathen/11181c.htm">obeyed</a> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse46">46</span> The children that are strangers have lied to me, strange children have faded away, and have halted from their paths.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse47">47</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> liveth, and <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> by my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and let the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> be exalted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse48">48</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who avengest me, and subduest the people under me, my deliverer from my enraged enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse49">49</span> And thou wilt lift me up above them that rise up against me: from the unjust <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> thou wilt deliver me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse50">50</span> Therefore will I give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, among the nations, and I will sing a psalm to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse51">51</span> Giving great deliverance to his king, and showing mercy to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, his anointed: and to his seed for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa017001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Puero Domini David, qui locutus est Domino verba cantici hujus, in die qua eripuit eum Dominus de manu omnium inimicorum ejus, et de manu Saul, et dixit:</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa017002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Diligam te, Domine, fortitudo mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Dominus firmamentum meum, et refugium meum, et liberator meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus adjutor meus, et sperabo in eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> protector meus, et cornu salutis me&aelig;, et susceptor meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Laudans invocabo Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ab inimicis meis salvus ero.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Circumdederunt me dolores mortis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et torrentes iniquitatis conturbaverunt me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Dolores inferni circumdederunt me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pr&aelig;occupaverunt me laquei mortis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017007vul">7</span>&nbsp;In tribulatione mea invocavi Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ad Deum meum clamavi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaudivit de templo sancto suo vocem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et clamor meus in conspectu ejus introivit in aures ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Commota est, et contremuit terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> fundamenta montium conturbata sunt, et commota sunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam iratus est eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Ascendit fumus in ira ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ignis a facie ejus exarsit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> carbones succensi sunt ab eo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Inclinavit c&aelig;los, et descendit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et caligo sub pedibus ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et ascendit super cherubim, et volavit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> volavit super pennas ventorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et posuit tenebras latibulum suum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in circuitu ejus tabernaculum ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tenebrosa aqua in nubibus a&euml;ris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig; fulgore in conspectu ejus nubes transierunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> grando et carbones ignis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Et intonuit de c&aelig;lo Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Altissimus dedit vocem suam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> grando et carbones ignis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Et misit sagittas suas, et dissipavit eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> fulgura multiplicavit, et conturbavit eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Et apparuerunt fontes aquarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et revelata sunt fundamenta orbis terrarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab increpatione tua, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab inspiratione spiritus ir&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Misit de summo, et accepit me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et assumpsit me de aquis multis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Eripuit me de inimicis meis fortissimis, et ab his qui oderunt me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam confortati sunt super me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017019vul">19</span>&nbsp;pr&aelig;venerunt me in die afflictionis me&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factus est Dominus protector meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Et eduxit me in latitudinem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvum me fecit, quoniam voluit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017021vul">21</span>&nbsp;et retribuet mihi Dominus secundum justitiam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum puritatem manuum mearum retribuet mihi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017022vul">22</span>&nbsp;quia custodivi vias Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec impie gessi a Deo meo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017023vul">23</span>&nbsp;quoniam omnia judicia ejus in conspectu meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitias ejus non repuli a me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Et ero immaculatus cum eo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et observabo me ab iniquitate mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Et retribuet mihi Dominus secundum justitiam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum puritatem manuum mearum in conspectu oculorum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Cum sancto sanctus eris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum viro innocente innocens eris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017027vul">27</span>&nbsp;et cum electo electus eris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum perverso perverteris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Quoniam tu populum humilem salvum facies,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et oculos superborum humiliabis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017029vul">29</span>&nbsp;Quoniam tu illuminas lucernam meam, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, illumina tenebras meas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017030vul">30</span>&nbsp;Quoniam in te eripiar a tentatione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in Deo meo transgrediar murum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017031vul">31</span>&nbsp;Deus meus, impolluta via ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> eloquia Domini igne examinata:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> protector est omnium sperantium in se.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017032vul">32</span>&nbsp;Quoniam quis deus pr&aelig;ter Dominum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut quis deus pr&aelig;ter Deum nostrum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017033vul">33</span>&nbsp;Deus qui pr&aelig;cinxit me virtute,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et posuit immaculatam viam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017034vul">34</span>&nbsp;qui perfecit pedes meos tamquam cervorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super excelsa statuens me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017035vul">35</span>&nbsp;qui docet manus meas ad pr&aelig;lium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et posuisti, ut arcum &aelig;reum, brachia mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017036vul">36</span>&nbsp;et dedisti mihi protectionem salutis tu&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dextera tua suscepit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et disciplina tua correxit me in finem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et disciplina tua ipsa me docebit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017037vul">37</span>&nbsp;Dilatasti gressus meos subtus me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non sunt infirmata vestigia mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017038vul">38</span>&nbsp;Persequar inimicos meos, et comprehendam illos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non convertar donec deficiant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017039vul">39</span>&nbsp;Confringam illos, nec poterunt stare;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cadent subtus pedes meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017040vul">40</span>&nbsp;Et pr&aelig;cinxisti me virtute ad bellum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et supplantasti insurgentes in me subtus me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017041vul">41</span>&nbsp;Et inimicos meos dedisti mihi dorsum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et odientes me disperdidisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017042vul">42</span>&nbsp;Clamaverunt, nec erat qui salvos faceret;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad Dominum, nec exaudivit eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017043vul">43</span>&nbsp;Et comminuam eos ut pulverem ante faciem venti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut lutum platearum delebo eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017044vul">44</span>&nbsp;Eripies me de contradictionibus populi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> constitues me in caput gentium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017045vul">45</span>&nbsp;Populus quem non cognovi servivit mihi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in auditu auris obedivit mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017046vul">46</span>&nbsp;Filii alieni mentiti sunt mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> filii alieni inveterati sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et claudicaverunt a semitis suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017047vul">47</span>&nbsp;Vivit Dominus, et benedictus Deus meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltetur Deus salutis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017048vul">48</span>&nbsp;Deus qui das vindictas mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et subdis populos sub me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> liberator meus de inimicis meis iracundis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017049vul">49</span>&nbsp;Et ab insurgentibus in me exaltabis me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a viro iniquo eripies me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017050vul">50</span>&nbsp;Propterea confitebor tibi in nationibus, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nomini tuo psalmum dicam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa017051vul">51</span>&nbsp;magnificans salutes regis ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et faciens misericordiam christo suo David,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et semini ejus usque in s&aelig;culum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
