<h1>Psalm 20</h1>
<div class="h1a">Praise to God for Christ's exaltation after his passion.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 21</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa019.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 20</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end. A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> In thy strength, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the king shall <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>; and in thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> he shall rejoice exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thou hast given him his heart's desire: and hast not withholden from him the will of his lips.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For thou hast prevented him with blessings of sweetness: thou hast set on his head a crown of <a href="../cathen/14304c.htm">precious stones</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> He asked life of thee: and thou hast given him length of days for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> His <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> is great in thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> and great beauty shalt thou lay upon him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For thou shalt give him to be a <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a> for ever and ever: thou shalt make him joyful in gladness with thy countenance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For the king hopeth in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and through the mercy of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a> he shall not be moved.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Let thy hand be found by all thy enemies: let thy right hand find out all them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Thou shalt make them as an oven of fire, in the time of thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a>: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall trouble them in his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>, and fire shall devour them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Their fruit shalt thou destroy from the earth: and their seed from among the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> For they have intended <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> against thee: they have devised counsels which they have not been able to establish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For thou shalt make them turn their back: in thy remnants thou shalt prepare their face. <span class="stiki"><strong>In thy remnants thou shalt prepare their face...</strong> Or thou shalt set thy remnants against their faces. That is, thou shalt make them see what punishments remain for them hereafter from thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>. Instead of remnants, <a href="../cathen/08341a.htm">St. Jerome</a> renders it <em>funes</em>, that is, cords or strings, viz., of the bow of divine <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, from which <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> directs his arrows against the faces of his enemies.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Be thou exalted, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy own strength: we will sing and praise thy power.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa020001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa020002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, in virtute tua l&aelig;tabitur rex,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super salutare tuum exsultabit vehementer.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Desiderium cordis ejus tribuisti ei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et voluntate labiorum ejus non fraudasti eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quoniam pr&aelig;venisti eum in benedictionibus dulcedinis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> posuisti in capite ejus coronam de lapide pretioso.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Vitam petiit a te, et tribuisti ei longitudinem dierum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in s&aelig;culum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Magna est gloria ejus in salutari tuo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> gloriam et magnum decorem impones super eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quoniam dabis eum in benedictionem in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> l&aelig;tificabis eum in gaudio cum vultu tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Quoniam rex sperat in Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in misericordia Altissimi non commovebitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Inveniatur manus tua omnibus inimicis tuis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dextera tua inveniat omnes qui te oderunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Pones eos ut clibanum ignis in tempore vultus tui:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus in ira sua conturbabit eos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et devorabit eos ignis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Fructum eorum de terra perdes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et semen eorum a filiis hominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020012vul">12</span>&nbsp;quoniam declinaverunt in te mala;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cogitaverunt consilia qu&aelig; non potuerunt stabilire.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Quoniam pones eos dorsum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in reliquiis tuis pr&aelig;parabis vultum eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa020014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Exaltare, Domine, in virtute tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantabimus et psallemus virtutes tuas.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
