<h1>Psalm 21</h1>
<div class="h1a">Christ's passion: and the conversion of the Gentiles.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 22</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa020.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 21</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the morning protection, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, look upon me: why hast thou forsaken me? Far from my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> are the words of my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>The words of my sins...</strong> That is, the <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> of the world, which I have taken upon myself, cry out against me, and are the cause of all my sufferings.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I shall cry by day, and thou wilt not hear: and by night, and it shall not be reputed as folly in me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> But thou dwellest in the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> place, the praise of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> In thee have our fathers hoped: they have hoped, and thou hast delivered them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> They cried to thee, and they were saved: they trusted in thee, and were not confounded.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> But I am a worm, and no <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>: the reproach of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>, and the outcast of the people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> All they that saw me have laughed me to scorn: they have spoken with the lips, and wagged the head.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He hoped in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, let him deliver him: let him save him, seeing he delighteth in him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For thou art he that hast drawn me out of the womb: my hope from the breasts of my mother.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> I was cast upon thee from the womb. From my mother's womb thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Depart not from me. For tribulation is very near: for there is none to help me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Many calves have surrounded me: fat bulls have besieged me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> They have opened their mouths against me, as a lion ravening and roaring.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> I am poured out like water; and all my bones are scattered. My heart is become like wax melting in the midst of my bowels.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> My strength is dried up like a potsherd, and my tongue hath cleaved to my jaws: and thou hast brought me down into the dust of death.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> For many dogs have encompassed me: the council of the malignant hath besieged me. They have dug my hands and feet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> They have numbered all my bones. And they have looked and stared upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> They parted my garments amongst them; and upon my vesture they cast lots.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> But thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, remove not thy help to a distance from me; look towards my defence.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Deliver, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from the sword: my only one from the hand of the dog.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Save me from the lion's mouth; and my lowness from the horns of the unicorns.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> I will declare thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> to my brethren: in the midst of the church will I praise thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Ye that fear the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, praise him: all ye the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">seed of Jacob</a>, <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Let all the seed of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> fear him: because he hath not slighted nor <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a> the supplication of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>. Neither hath he turned away his face form me: and when I cried to him he heard me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> With thee is my praise in a great church: I will pay my <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vows</a> in the sight of them that fear him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> The <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> shall eat and shall be filled: and they shall praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> that seek him: their hearts shall live for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> All the ends of the earth shall remember, and shall be converted to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: And all the kindreds of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> shall <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> in his sight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> For the kingdom is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord's</a>; and he shall have dominion over the nations.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> All the fat ones of the earth have eaten and have <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adored</a>: all they that go down to the earth shall fall before him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> And to him my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> shall live: and my seed shall serve him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> There shall be declared to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> a <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> to come: and the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> shall show forth his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> to a people that shall be born, which the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath made.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

