<h1>Psalm 24</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for grace, mercy, and protection against our enemies.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 25</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa023.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 24</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> To thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, have I lifted up my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> In thee, O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I put my trust; let me not be ashamed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Neither let my enemies laugh at me: for none of them that wait on thee shall be confounded.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Let all them be confounded that act <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> things without cause. Show, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy ways to me, and teach me thy paths.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Direct me in thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>, and teach me; for thou art <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> my Saviour; and on thee have I waited all the day long.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Remember, O Lord, thy bowels of compassion; and thy mercies that are from the beginning of the world.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> of my youth and my <a href="../cathen/07648a.htm">ignorances</a> do not remember. According to thy mercy remember thou me: for thy goodness' sake, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is sweet and righteous: therefore he will give a law to sinners in the way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He will guide the mild in judgment: he will teach the meek his ways.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> All the ways of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> are mercy and <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>, to them that seek after his covenant and his testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake, O Lord, thou wilt pardon my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a>: for it is great.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Who is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that feareth the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>? He hath appointed him a law in the way he hath chosen.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> His <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> shall dwell in <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things: and his seed shall inherit the land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is a <a href="../cathen/06079b.htm">firmament</a> to them that fear him: and his covenant shall be made manifest to them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> My eyes are ever towards the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: for he shall pluck my feet out of the snare.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Look thou upon me, and have mercy on me; for I am alone and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The troubles of my heart are multiplied: deliver me from my necessities.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> See my abjection and my labour; and forgive me all my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Consider my enemies for they are multiplied, and have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> me with an <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hatred</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Deep thou my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and deliver me: I shall not be ashamed, for I have hoped in thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> The innocent and the upright have adhered to me: because I have waited on thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Deliver <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, from all his tribulations.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa024001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Ad te, Domine, levavi animam meam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Deus meus, in te confido; non erubescam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Neque irrideant me inimici mei:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> etenim universi qui sustinent te, non confundentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Confundantur omnes iniqua agentes supervacue.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Vias tuas, Domine, demonstra mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et semitas tuas edoce me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dirige me in veritate tua, et doce me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia tu es Deus salvator meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et te sustinui tota die.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Reminiscere miserationum tuarum, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et misericordiarum tuarum qu&aelig; a s&aelig;culo sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Delicta juventutis me&aelig;, et ignorantias meas, ne memineris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Secundum misericordiam tuam memento mei tu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter bonitatem tuam, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dulcis et rectus Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter hoc legem dabit delinquentibus in via.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Diriget mansuetos in judicio;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> docebit mites vias suas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Univers&aelig; vi&aelig; Domini, misericordia et veritas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> requirentibus testamentum ejus et testimonia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Propter nomen tuum, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propitiaberis peccato meo; multum est enim.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Quis est homo qui timet Dominum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> legem statuit ei in via quam elegit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Anima ejus in bonis demorabitur,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et semen ejus h&aelig;reditabit terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Firmamentum est Dominus timentibus eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et testamentum ipsius ut manifestetur illis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Oculi mei semper ad Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ipse evellet de laqueo pedes meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Respice in me, et miserere mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia unicus et pauper sum ego.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Tribulationes cordis mei multiplicat&aelig; sunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> de necessitatibus meis erue me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Vide humilitatem meam et laborem meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dimitte universa delicta mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Respice inimicos meos, quoniam multiplicati sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et odio iniquo oderunt me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Custodi animam meam, et erue me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non erubescam, quoniam speravi in te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Innocentes et recti adh&aelig;serunt mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia sustinui te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa024022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Libera, Deus, Isra&euml;l</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex omnibus tribulationibus suis.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
