<h1>Psalm 26</h1>
<div class="h1a">David's faith and hope in God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 27</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa025.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 26</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The psalm of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> before he was anointed.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my light and my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, whom shall I fear? The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the protector of my life: of whom shall I be afraid?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Whilst the wicked draw near against me, to eat my flesh. My enemies that trouble me, have themselves been weakened, and have fallen.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> If armies in camp should stand together against me, my heart shall not fear. If a battle should rise up against me, in this will I be confident.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> One thing I have asked of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, this will I seek after; that I may dwell in the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a> all the days of my life. That I may see the delight of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and may visit his <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For he hath hidden me in his tabernacle; in the day of <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a>, he hath protected me in the secret place of his tabernacle.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He hath exalted me upon a rock: and now he hath lifted up my head above my enemies. I have gone round, and have offered up in his <a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">tabernacle</a> a <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of jubilation: I will sing, and recite a psalm to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my voice, with which I have cried to thee: have mercy on me and hear me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> My heart hath said to thee: My face hath sought thee: thy face, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, will I still seek.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Turn not away thy face from me; decline not in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> from thy servant. Be thou my helper, forsake me not; do not thou <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despise</a> me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> my Saviour.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For my father and my mother have left me: but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath taken me up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Set me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, a law in thy way, and guide me in the right path, because of my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Deliver me not over to the will of them that trouble me; for <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> witnesses have risen up against me; and <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> hath lied to itself.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> I <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believe</a> to see the <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in the land of the living.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Expect the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, do manfully, and let thy heart take <a href="../cathen/06147a.htm">courage</a>, and wait thou for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa026001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, priusquam liniretur.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Dominus illuminatio mea et salus mea: quem timebo?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus protector vit&aelig; me&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a quo trepidabo?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dum appropiant super me nocentes ut edant carnes meas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui tribulant me inimici mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipsi infirmati sunt et ceciderunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Si consistant adversum me castra, non timebit cor meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> si exsurgat adversum me pr&aelig;lium, in hoc ego sperabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Unam petii a Domino, hanc requiram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut inhabitem in domo Domini omnibus diebus vit&aelig; me&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut videam voluptatem Domini, et visitem templum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quoniam abscondit me in tabernaculo suo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in die malorum protexit me in abscondito tabernaculi sui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026006vul">6</span>&nbsp;In petra exaltavit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nunc exaltavit caput meum super inimicos meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Circuivi, et immolavi in tabernaculo ejus hostiam vociferationis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantabo, et psalmum dicam Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Exaudi, Domine, vocem meam, qua clamavi ad te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> miserere mei, et exaudi me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Tibi dixit cor meum: Exquisivit te facies mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> faciem tuam, Domine, requiram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Ne avertas faciem tuam a me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne declines in ira a servo tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Adjutor meus esto; ne derelinquas me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque despicias me, Deus salutaris meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam pater meus et mater mea dereliquerunt me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus autem assumpsit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Legem pone mihi, Domine, in via tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dirige me in semitam rectam, propter inimicos meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Ne tradideris me in animas tribulantium me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam insurrexerunt in me testes iniqui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mentita est iniquitas sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Credo videre bona Domini in terra viventium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa026014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Expecta Dominum, viriliter age:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et confortetur cor tuum, et sustine Dominum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
