<h1>Psalm 27</h1>
<div class="h1a">David's prayer that his enemies may not prevail over him.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 28</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa026.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 27</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Unto thee will I cry, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, be not thou silent to me: lest if thou be silent to me, I become like them that go down into the pit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the voice of my supplication, when I <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">pray</a> to thee; when I lift up my hands to thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Draw me not away together with the wicked; and with the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> destroy me not: Who speak peace with their neighbour, but <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> are in their hearts.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Give them according to their works, and according to the wickedness of their inventions. According to the works of their hands give thou to them: render to them their reward.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Because they have not understood the works of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and the operations of his hands: thou shalt destroy them, and shalt not build them up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he hath heard the voice of my supplication.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my helper and my protector: in him hath my heart confided, and I have been helped. And my flesh hath flourished again, and with my will I will give praise to him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the strength of his people, and the protector of the <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> of his anointed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Save, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy people, and <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thy inheritance: and rule them and exalt them for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa027001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Ad te, Domine, clamabo; Deus meus, ne sileas a me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nequando taceas a me, et assimilabor descendentibus in lacum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exaudi, Domine, vocem deprecationis me&aelig; dum oro ad te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dum extollo manus meas ad templum sanctum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Ne simul trahas me cum peccatoribus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum operantibus iniquitatem ne perdas me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui loquuntur pacem cum proximo suo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mala autem in cordibus eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Da illis secundum opera eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum nequitiam adinventionum ipsorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Secundum opera manuum eorum tribue illis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> redde retributionem eorum ipsis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quoniam non intellexerunt opera Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in opera manuum ejus destrues illos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non &aelig;dificabis eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Benedictus Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam exaudivit vocem deprecationis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Dominus adjutor meus et protector meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in ipso speravit cor meum, et adjutus sum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et refloruit caro mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ex voluntate mea confitebor ei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dominus fortitudo plebis su&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et protector salvationum christi sui est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa027009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Salvum fac populum tuum, Domine, et benedic h&aelig;reditati tu&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et rege eos, et extolle illos usque in &aelig;ternum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
