<h1>Psalm 30</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of a just man under affliction.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 31</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa029.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 30</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, in an ecstasy.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> In thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, have I hoped, let me never be confounded: deliver me in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Bow down thy ear to me: make haste to deliver me. Be thou unto me a <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, a protector, and a house of refuge, to save me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For thou art my strength and my refuge; and for thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake thou wilt lead me, and nourish me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Thou wilt bring me out of this snare, which they have hidden for me: for thou art my protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Into thy hands I commend my spirit: thou hast <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Thou hast <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> them that regard vanities, to no purpose. But I have hoped in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> I will be glad and rejoice in thy mercy. For thou hast regarded my <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humility</a>, thou hast saved my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> out of distresses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> And thou hast not shut me up in the hands of the enemy: thou hast set my feet in a spacious place.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I am afflicted: my eye is troubled with <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>, my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and my belly:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For my life is wasted with grief: and my years in sighs. My strength is weakened through <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poverty<!--</a>--> and my bones are disturbed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> I am become a reproach among all my enemies, and very much to my neighbours; and a fear to my acquaintance. They that saw me without fled from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> I am forgotten as one dead from the heart. I am become as a vessel that is destroyed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> For I have heard the blame of many that dwell round about. While they assembled together against me, they consulted to take away my life.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> But I have put my trust in thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I said: Thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> My lots are in thy hands. Deliver me out of the hands of my enemies; and from them that persecute me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Make thy face to shine upon thy servant; save me in thy mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Let me not be confounded, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I have called upon thee. Let the wicked be ashamed, and be brought down to hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Let deceitful lips be made dumb. Which speak <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> against the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, with <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">pride</a> and abuse.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> O how great is the multitude of thy sweetness, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, which thou hast hidden for them that fear thee! Which thou hast wrought for them that hope in thee, in the sight of the sons of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Thou shalt hide them in the secret of thy face, from the disturbance of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>. Thou shalt protect them in thy tabernacle from the contradiction of tongues.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he hath shown his wonderful mercy to me in a fortified city.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> But I said in the excess of my mind: I am cast away from before thy eyes. Therefore thou hast heard the voice of my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, when I cried to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> O <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all ye his saints: for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will require <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>, and will repay them abundantly that act <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proudly</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Do ye manfully, and let your heart be strengthened, all ye that hope in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa030001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David, pro extasi.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa030002vul">2</span>&nbsp;In te, Domine, speravi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non confundar in &aelig;ternum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in justitia tua libera me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Inclina ad me aurem tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> accelera ut eruas me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Esto mihi in Deum protectorem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in domum refugii, ut salvum me facias:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030004vul">4</span>&nbsp;quoniam fortitudo mea et refugium meum es tu;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et propter nomen tuum deduces me et enutries me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Educes me de laqueo hoc quem absconderunt mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam tu es protector meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030006vul">6</span>&nbsp;In manus tuas commendo spiritum meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> redemisti me, Domine Deus veritatis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Odisti observantes vanitates supervacue;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem in Domino speravi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Exsultabo, et l&aelig;tabor in misericordia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam respexisti humilitatem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvasti de necessitatibus animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Nec conclusisti me in manibus inimici:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> statuisti in loco spatioso pedes meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Domine, quoniam tribulor;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> conturbatus est in ira oculus meus, anima mea, et venter meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Quoniam defecit in dolore vita mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et anni mei in gemitibus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Infirmata est in paupertate virtus mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ossa mea conturbata sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Super omnes inimicos meos factus sum opprobrium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vicinis meis valde, et timor notis meis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui videbant me foras fugerunt a me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Oblivioni datus sum, tamquam mortuus a corde;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> factus sum tamquam vas perditum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030014vul">14</span>&nbsp;quoniam audivi vituperationem multorum commorantium in circuitu.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In eo dum convenirent simul adversum me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> accipere animam meam consiliati sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Ego autem in te speravi, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dixi: Deus meus es tu;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030016vul">16</span>&nbsp;in manibus tuis sortes me&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> eripe me de manu inimicorum meorum, et a persequentibus me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Illustra faciem tuam super servum tuum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvum me fac in misericordia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Domine, non confundar, quoniam invocavi te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Erubescant impii, et deducantur in infernum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030019vul">19</span>&nbsp;muta fiant labia dolosa,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; loquuntur adversus justum iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in superbia, et in abusione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Quam magna multitudo dulcedinis tu&aelig;, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quam abscondisti timentibus te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> perfecisti eis qui sperant in te in conspectu filiorum hominum!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Abscondes eos in abscondito faciei tu&aelig; a conturbatione hominum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> proteges eos in tabernaculo tuo, a contradictione linguarum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Benedictus Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam mirificavit misericordiam suam mihi in civitate munita.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Ego autem dixi in excessu mentis me&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Projectus sum a facie oculorum tuorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ideo exaudisti vocem orationis me&aelig;, dum clamarem ad te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Diligite Dominum, omnes sancti ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam veritatem requiret Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et retribuet abundanter facientibus superbiam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa030025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Viriliter agite, et confortetur cor vestrum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnes qui speratis in Domino.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
