<h1>Psalm 32</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to praise God, and to trust in him.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 33</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa031.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 32</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Rejoice in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O ye <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>: praise becometh the upright.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Give praise to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> on the harp; sing to him with the psaltery, the instrument of ten strings.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Sing to him a new canticle, sing well unto him with a loud noise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For the <a href="../cathen/13001a.htm">word of the Lord</a> is right, and all his works are done with faithfulness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> He <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> mercy and judgment; the earth is full of the mercy of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> By the <a href="../cathen/13001a.htm">word of the Lord</a> the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> were established; and all the power of them by the spirit of his mouth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Gathering together the waters of the sea, as in a vessel; laying up the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">depths</a> in storehouses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Let all the earth fear the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and let all the inhabitants of the world be in awe of him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> For he spoke and they were made: he commanded and they were <a href="../cathen/04470a.htm">created</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> bringeth to nought the counsels of nations; and he rejecteth the devices of people, and casteth away the counsels of princes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> But the counsel of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> standeth for ever: the thoughts of his heart to all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the nation whose <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: the people whom he hath chosen for his inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath looked from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>: he hath beheld all the sons of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> From his habitation which he hath prepared, he hath looked upon all that dwell on the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> He who hath made the hearts of every one of them: who understandeth all their works.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> The king is not saved by a great army: nor shall the giant be saved by his own great strength.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Vain is the horse for safety: neither shall he be saved by the abundance of his strength.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Behold the eyes of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> are on them that fear him: and on them that hope in his mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> To deliver their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> from death; and feed them in famine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Our <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> waiteth for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: for he is our helper and protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> For in him our heart shall rejoice: and in his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> we have trusted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Let thy mercy, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, be upon us, as we have hoped in thee.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa032001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Exsultate, justi, in Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> rectos decet collaudatio.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Confitemini Domino in cithara;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in psalterio decem chordarum psallite illi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Cantate ei canticum novum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> bene psallite ei in vociferatione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia rectum est verbum Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnia opera ejus in fide.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Diligit misericordiam et judicium;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericordia Domini plena est terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Verbo Domini c&aelig;li firmati sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et spiritu oris ejus omnis virtus eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Congregans sicut in utre aquas maris;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ponens in thesauris abyssos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Timeat Dominum omnis terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab eo autem commoveantur omnes inhabitantes orbem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Quoniam ipse dixit, et facta sunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipse mandavit et creata sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Dominus dissipat consilia gentium;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> reprobat autem cogitationes populorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et reprobat consilia principum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Consilium autem Domini in &aelig;ternum manet;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cogitationes cordis ejus in generatione et generationem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Beata gens cujus est Dominus Deus ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> populus quem elegit in h&aelig;reditatem sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032013vul">13</span>&nbsp;De c&aelig;lo respexit Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> vidit omnes filios hominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032014vul">14</span>&nbsp;De pr&aelig;parato habitaculo suo</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> respexit super omnes qui habitant terram:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032015vul">15</span>&nbsp;qui finxit sigillatim corda eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui intelligit omnia opera eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Non salvatur rex per multam virtutem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gigas non salvabitur in multitudine virtutis su&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Fallax equus ad salutem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in abundantia autem virtutis su&aelig; non salvabitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Ecce oculi Domini super metuentes eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in eis qui sperant super misericordia ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032019vul">19</span>&nbsp;ut eruat a morte animas eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et alat eos in fame.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Anima nostra sustinet Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam adjutor et protector noster est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Quia in eo l&aelig;tabitur cor nostrum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine sancto ejus speravimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa032022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Fiat misericordia tua, Domine, super nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quemadmodum speravimus in te.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
