<h1>Psalm 33</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to the praise, and service of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 34</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa032.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 33</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, when he changed his countenance before <a href="../cathen/01102d.htm">Achimelech</a>, who dismissed him, and he went his way. [1 Samuel 21.]</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I will bless the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> at all times, his praise shall be always in my mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> In the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> be praised: let the meek hear and rejoice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> O magnify the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with me; and let us extol his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> together.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I sought the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he heard me; and he delivered me from all my troubles.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Come ye to him and be enlightened: and your faces shall not be confounded.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> This <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> cried, and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> heard him: and saved him out of all his troubles.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angel of the Lord</a> shall encamp round about them that fear him: and shall deliver them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> O taste, and see that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is sweet: <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that hopeth in him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Fear the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all ye his saints: for there is no want to them that fear him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The rich have wanted, and have suffered hunger: but they that seek the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall not be deprived of any <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Come, children, hearken to me: I will teach you the fear of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Who is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that desireth life: who liveth to see <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> days?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Keep thy tongue form <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>, and thy lips from speaking guile.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Turn away from <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> and do <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: seek after peace and pursue it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> The eyes of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> are upon the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>: and his ears unto their <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayers</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> But the countenance of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is against them that do <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> things: to cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> cried, and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> heard them: and delivered them out of all their troubles.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is nigh unto them that are of a <a href="../cathen/04337a.htm">contrite</a> heart: and he will save the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> of spirit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Many are the afflictions of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>; but out of them all will the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> deliver them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is nigh unto them that are of a <a href="../cathen/04337a.htm">contrite</a> heart: and he will save the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> of spirit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> The death of the wicked is very <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>: and they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall be guilty.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> of his servants: and none of them that trust in him shall offend.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa033001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Davidi, cum immutavit vultum suum coram Achimelech, et dimisit eum, et abiit.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa033002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Benedicam Dominum in omni tempore;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> semper laus ejus in ore meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033003vul">3</span>&nbsp;In Domino laudabitur anima mea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> audiant mansueti, et l&aelig;tentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Magnificate Dominum mecum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltemus nomen ejus in idipsum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Exquisivi Dominum, et exaudivit me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ex omnibus tribulationibus meis eripuit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Accedite ad eum, et illuminamini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et facies vestr&aelig; non confundentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Iste pauper clamavit, et Dominus exaudivit eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de omnibus tribulationibus ejus salvavit eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Immittet angelus Domini in circuitu timentium eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et eripiet eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Gustate et videte quoniam suavis est Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> beatus vir qui sperat in eo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Timete Dominum, omnes sancti ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam non est inopia timentibus eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Divites eguerunt, et esurierunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inquirentes autem Dominum non minuentur omni bono.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Venite, filii; audite me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> timorem Domini docebo vos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Quis est homo qui vult vitam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> diligit dies videre bonos?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Prohibe linguam tuam a malo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et labia tua ne loquantur dolum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Diverte a malo, et fac bonum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inquire pacem, et persequere eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Oculi Domini super justos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et aures ejus in preces eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Vultus autem Domini super facientes mala,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut perdat de terra memoriam eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Clamaverunt justi, et Dominus exaudivit eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ex omnibus tribulationibus eorum liberavit eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Juxta est Dominus iis qui tribulato sunt corde,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et humiles spiritu salvabit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Mult&aelig; tribulationes justorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de omnibus his liberabit eos Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Custodit Dominus omnia ossa eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> unum ex his non conteretur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Mors peccatorum pessima;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui oderunt justum delinquent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa033023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Redimet Dominus animas servorum suorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non delinquent omnes qui sperant in eo.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
