<h1>Psalm 34</h1>
<div class="h1a">David, in the person of Christ, prays against his persecutors: prophetically foreshowing the punishments that shall fall upon them.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 35</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa033.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 34</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Judge thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, them that wrong me: overthrow them that fight against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Take hold of arms and shield: and rise up to help me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Bring out the sword, and shut up the way against them that persecute me: say to my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: I am thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Let them be confounded and ashamed that seek after my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>. Let them be turned back and be confounded that devise <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Let them become as dust before the wind: and let the <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angel of the Lord</a> straiten them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Let their way become dark and slippery; and let the <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angel of the Lord</a> pursue them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For without cause they have hidden their net for me unto destruction: without cause they have upbraided my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Let the snare which he knoweth not come upon him: and let the net which he hath hidden catch him: and into that very snare let them fall.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> But my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> shall rejoice in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; and shall be delighted in his <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> All my bones shall say: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who is like to thee? Who deliverest the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> from the hand of them that are stronger than he; the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy<!--</a>--> and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> from them that strip him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Unjust witnesses rising up have asked me things I knew not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> They repaid me <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> for <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: to the depriving me of my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> But as for me, when they were troublesome to me, I was clothed with haircloth. I <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> with <a href="../cathen/05789c.htm">fasting</a>; and my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> shall be turned into my bosom.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> As a neighbour and as an own brother, so did I please: as one mourning and sorrowful so was I <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> But they rejoiced against me, and came together: scourges were gathered together upon me, and I knew not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> They were separated, and repented not: they tempted me, they scoffed at me with scorn: they gnashed upon me with their teeth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, when wilt thou look upon me? rescue thou my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from their malice: my only one from the lions.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> I will give thanks to thee in a great church; I will praise thee in a strong people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Let not them that are my enemies wrongfully rejoice over me: who have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> me without cause, and wink with the eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> For they spoke indeed peaceably to me; and speaking in the <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> of the earth they devised guile.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> And they opened their mouth wide against me; they said: Well done, well done, our eyes have seen it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Thou hast seen, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, be not thou silent: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, depart not from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Arise, and be attentive to my judgment: to my cause, my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Judge me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> according to thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and let them not rejoice over me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Let them not say in their hearts: It is well, it is well, to our mind: neither let them say: We have swallowed him up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> Let them blush: and be ashamed together, who rejoice at my <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a>. Let them be clothed with confusion and shame, who speak great things against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> Let them rejoice and be glad, who are well pleased with my <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and let them say always: The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> be magnified, who delights in the peace of his servant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> And my tongue shall meditate thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, thy praise all the day long.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa034001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Judica, Domine, nocentes me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> expugna impugnantes me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Apprehende arma et scutum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsurge in adjutorium mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Effunde frameam, et conclude adversus eos qui persequuntur me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dic anim&aelig; me&aelig;: Salus tua ego sum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Confundantur et revereantur qu&aelig;rentes animam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> avertantur retrorsum et confundantur cogitantes mihi mala.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Fiant tamquam pulvis ante faciem venti,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et angelus Domini coarctans eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Fiat via illorum tenebr&aelig; et lubricum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et angelus Domini persequens eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quoniam gratis absconderunt mihi interitum laquei sui; supervacue exprobraverunt animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Veniat illi laqueus quem ignorat,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et captio quam abscondit apprehendat eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in laqueum cadat in ipsum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Anima autem mea exsultabit in Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et delectabitur super salutari suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Omnia ossa mea dicent:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, quis similis tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> eripiens inopem de manu fortiorum ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> egenum et pauperem a diripientibus eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Surgentes testes iniqui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; ignorabam interrogabant me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Retribuebant mihi mala pro bonis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sterilitatem anim&aelig; me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Ego autem, cum mihi molesti essent, induebar cilicio;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> humiliabam in jejunio animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et oratio mea in sinu meo convertetur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Quasi proximum et quasi fratrem nostrum sic complacebam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quasi lugens et contristatus sic humiliabar.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Et adversum me l&aelig;tati sunt, et convenerunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> congregata sunt super me flagella, et ignoravi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Dissipati sunt, nec compuncti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tentaverunt me, subsannaverunt me subsannatione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> frenduerunt super me dentibus suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Domine, quando respicies?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Restitue animam meam a malignitate eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a leonibus unicam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Confitebor tibi in ecclesia magna; in populo gravi laudabo te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Non supergaudeant mihi qui adversantur mihi inique,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui oderunt me gratis, et annuunt oculis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Quoniam mihi quidem pacifice loquebantur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in iracundia terr&aelig; loquentes, dolos cogitabant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Et dilataverunt super me os suum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dixerunt: Euge, euge! viderunt oculi nostri.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Vidisti, Domine: ne sileas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, ne discedas a me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Exsurge et intende judicio meo, Deus meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus meus, in causam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Judica me secundum justitiam tuam, Domine Deus meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non supergaudeant mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Non dicant in cordibus suis: Euge, euge, anim&aelig; nostr&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec dicant: Devoravimus eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Erubescant et revereantur simul qui gratulantur malis meis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> induantur confusione et reverentia qui magna loquuntur super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Exsultent et l&aelig;tentur qui volunt justitiam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dicant semper: Magnificetur Dominus, qui volunt pacem servi ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa034028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Et lingua mea meditabitur justitiam tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die laudem tuam.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
