<h1>Psalm 36</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to despise this world; and the short prosperity of the wicked; and to trust in Providence.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 37</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa035.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 36</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Be not emulous of evildoers; nor envy them that work <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> For they shall shortly wither away as grass, and as the green herbs shall quickly fall.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Trust in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and do <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, and dwell in the land, and thou shalt be fed with its riches.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Delight in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he will give thee the requests of thy heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Commit thy way to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and trust in him, and he will do it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> And he will bring forth thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> as the light, and thy judgment as the noonday.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Be subject to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> and <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">pray</a> to him. Envy not the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> who prospereth in his way; the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> who doth <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> things.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Cease from <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a>, and leave rage; have no emulation to do <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> For evildoers shall be cut off: but they that wait upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, they shall inherit the land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For yet a little while, and the wicked shall not be: and thou shalt seek his place, and shalt not find it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> But the meek shall inherit the land, and shall delight in abundance of peace.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> The sinner shall watch the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>: and shall gnash upon him with his teeth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> But the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall laugh at him: for he foreseeth that his day shall come.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> have drawn out the sword: they have bent their bow. To cast down the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor and needy<!--</a>-->, to kill the upright of heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Let their sword enter into their own hearts, and let their bow be broken.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Better is a little to the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, than the great riches of the wicked.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> For the arms of the wicked shall be broken in pieces; but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> strengtheneth the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> knoweth the days of the undefiled; and their inheritance shall be for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> They shall not be confounded in the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> time; and in the days of famine they shall be filled:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Because the wicked shall perish. And the enemies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, presently after they shall be honoured and exalted, shall come to nothing and vanish like smoke.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> The sinner shall borrow, and not pay again; but the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> showeth mercy and shall give.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> For such as <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> him shall inherit the land: but such as <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">curse</a> him shall perish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> With the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall the steps of a <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> be directed, and he shall like well his way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> When he shall fall he shall not be bruised, for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> putteth his hand under him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> I have been young and now am old; and I have not seen the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> forsaken, nor his seed seeking bread.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> He showeth mercy, and lendeth all the day long; and his seed shall be in <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> Decline from <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> and do <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, and dwell for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> judgment, and will not forsake his saints: they shall be preserved for ever. The <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> shall be punished, and the seed of the wicked shall perish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> But the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall inherit the land, and shall dwell therein for evermore.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> The mouth of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall meditate wisdom: and his tongue shall speak judgment.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> The law of his <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is in his heart, and his steps shall not be supplanted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> watcheth the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>, and seeketh to put him to death,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> But the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will not leave him in his hands; nor condemn him when he shall be judged.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> Expect the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> and keep his way: and he will exalt thee to inherit the land: when the sinners shall perish thou shalt see.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> I have seen the wicked highly exalted, and lifted up like the <a href="../cathen/03473a.htm">cedars</a> of Libanus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> And I passed by, and lo, he was not: and I sought him and his place was not found.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> Keep innocence, and behold <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: for there are remnants for the peaceable <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> But the unjust shall be destroyed together: the remnants of the wicked shall perish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> But the <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> is from the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he is their protector in the time of trouble.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will help them and deliver them: and he will rescue them from the wicked, and save them because they have hoped in him.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

