<h1>Psalm 37</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of a penitent for the remission of his sins. The third penitential psalm.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 38</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa036.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 37</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, for a remembrance of the <a href="../cathen/13287b.htm">sabbath</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>For a remembrance...</strong> Viz., of our miseries and <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>: and to be sung on the <a href="../cathen/13287b.htm">sabbath day</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Rebuke me not, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy indignation; nor chastise me in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For thy arrows are fastened in me: and thy hand hath been strong upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> There is no health in my flesh, because of thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>: there is no peace for my bones, because of my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> are gone over my head: and as a heavy burden are become heavy upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> My sores are putrefied and corrupted, because of my foolishness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I am become miserable, and am bowed down even to the end: I walked sorrowful all the day long.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For my loins are filled with illusions; and there is no health in my flesh.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I am afflicted and <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> exceedingly: I roared with the groaning of my heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all my desire is before thee, and my groaning is not hidden from thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> My heart is troubled, my strength hath left me, and the light of my eyes itself is not with me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> My friends and my neighbours have drawn near, and stood against me. And they that were near me stood afar off:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> And they that sought my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> used <a href="../cathen/15446a.htm">violence</a>. And they that sought <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> to me spoke vain things, and studied deceits all the day long.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But I, as a deaf <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>, heard not: and as a dumb <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> not opening his mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And I became as a <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that heareth not: and that hath no reproofs in his mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> For in thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, have I hoped: thou wilt hear me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> For I said: Lest at any time my enemies rejoice over me: and whilst my feet are moved, they speak great things against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> For I am ready for scourges: and my sorrow is continually before me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> For I will declare my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and I will think for my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> But my enemies live, and are stronger than I: and they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> me wrongfully are multiplied.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> They that render <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> for <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, have detracted me, because I followed goodness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> For sake me not, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: do not thou depart from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Attend unto my help, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa037001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, in rememorationem de sabbato.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa037002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, ne in furore tuo arguas me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque in ira tua corripias me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037003vul">3</span>&nbsp;quoniam sagitt&aelig; tu&aelig; infix&aelig; sunt mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et confirmasti super me manum tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Non est sanitas in carne mea, a facie ir&aelig; tu&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non est pax ossibus meis, a facie peccatorum meorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037005vul">5</span>&nbsp;quoniam iniquitates me&aelig; supergress&aelig; sunt caput meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sicut onus grave gravat&aelig; sunt super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Putruerunt et corrupt&aelig; sunt cicatrices me&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a facie insipienti&aelig; me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Miser factus sum et curvatus sum usque in finem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die contristatus ingrediebar.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Quoniam lumbi mei impleti sunt illusionibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non est sanitas in carne mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Afflictus sum, et humiliatus sum nimis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> rugiebam a gemitu cordis mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Domine, ante te omne desiderium meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gemitus meus a te non est absconditus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Cor meum conturbatum est;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dereliquit me virtus mea, et lumen oculorum meorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ipsum non est mecum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Amici mei et proximi mei adversum me appropinquaverunt, et steterunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui juxta me erant, de longe steterunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vim faciebant qui qu&aelig;rebant animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Et qui inquirebant mala mihi, locuti sunt vanitates,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dolos tota die meditabantur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Ego autem, tamquam surdus, non audiebam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sicut mutus non aperiens os suum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Et factus sum sicut homo non audiens,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non habens in ore suo redargutiones.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Quoniam in te, Domine, speravi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tu exaudies me, Domine Deus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Quia dixi: Nequando supergaudeant mihi inimici mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dum commoventur pedes mei, super me magna locuti sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Quoniam ego in flagella paratus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dolor meus in conspectu meo semper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Quoniam iniquitatem meam annuntiabo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cogitabo pro peccato meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Inimici autem mei vivunt, et confirmati sunt super me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et multiplicati sunt qui oderunt me inique.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Qui retribuunt mala pro bonis detrahebant mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam sequebar bonitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Ne derelinquas me, Domine Deus meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne discesseris a me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa037023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Intende in adjutorium meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine Deus salutis me&aelig;.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
