<h1>Psalm 39</h1>
<div class="h1a">Christ's coming, and redeeming mankind.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 40</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa038.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 39</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> With expectation I have waited for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he was attentive to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> And he heard my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayers</a>, and brought me out of the pit of misery and the mire of dregs. And he set my feet upon a rock, and directed my steps.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And he put a new canticle into my mouth, a song to our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. Many shall see, and shall fear: and they shall hope in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> whose trust is in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; and who hath not had regard to vanities, and lying follies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Thou hast multiplied thy wonderful works, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and in thy thoughts there is no one like to thee. I have declared and I have spoken they are multiplied above number.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">Sacrifice</a> and <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">oblation</a> thou didst not desire; but thou hast pierced ears for me. Burnt <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">offering</a> and <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a> <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">offering</a> thou didst not require:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Then said I, Behold I come. In the head of the book it is written of me</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> That I should do thy will: O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I have desired it, and thy law in the midst of my heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> I have declared thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> in a great church, lo, I will not restrain my lips: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou knowest it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> I have not hid thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> within my heart: I have declared thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> and thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>. I have not concealed thy mercy and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> from a great council.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Withhold not thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy tender mercies from me: thy mercy and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> have always upheld me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> without number have surrounded me; my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> have overtaken me, and I was not able to see. They are multiplied above the hairs of my head: and my heart hath forsaken me. <span class="stiki"><strong>My iniquities...</strong> That is, the <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> of all <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">mankind</a>, which I have taken upon me.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Be pleased, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to deliver me. Look down, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to help me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Let them be confounded and ashamed together, that seek after my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> to take it away. Let them be turned backward and be ashamed that desire <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Let them immediately bear their confusion, that say to me: 'T is well, 't is well. <span class="stiki"><strong>'T is well...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a> here is an interjection of insult and derision, like the <em>Vah</em>. <a href="../bible/mat027.htm#verse49">Matthew 27:49</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Let all that seek thee rejoice and be glad in thee: and let such as <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> say always: The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> be magnified.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> But I am a beggar and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is careful for me. Thou art my helper and my protector: O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, be not slack.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa039001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa039002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exspectans exspectavi Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et intendit mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Et exaudivit preces meas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et eduxit me de lacu miseri&aelig; et de luto f&aelig;cis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et statuit super petram pedes meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et direxit gressus meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Et immisit in os meum canticum novum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> carmen Deo nostro.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Videbunt multi, et timebunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sperabunt in Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Beatus vir cujus est nomen Domini spes ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non respexit in vanitates et insanias falsas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Multa fecisti tu, Domine Deus meus, mirabilia tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cogitationibus tuis non est qui similis sit tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Annuntiavi et locutus sum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> multiplicati sunt super numerum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Sacrificium et oblationem noluisti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aures autem perfecisti mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Holocaustum et pro peccato non postulasti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039008vul">8</span>&nbsp;tunc dixi: Ecce venio.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In capite libri scriptum est de me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039009vul">9</span>&nbsp;ut facerem voluntatem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, volui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et legem tuam in medio cordis mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Annuntiavi justitiam tuam in ecclesia magna;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ecce labia mea non prohibebo: Domine, tu scisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Justitiam tuam non abscondi in corde meo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> veritatem tuam et salutare tuum dixi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non abscondi misericordiam tuam et veritatem tuam a concilio multo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Tu autem, Domine, ne longe facias miserationes tuas a me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericordia tua et veritas tua semper susceperunt me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Quoniam circumdederunt me mala quorum non est numerus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> comprehenderunt me iniquitates me&aelig;, et non potui ut viderem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Multiplicat&aelig; sunt super capillos capitis mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cor meum dereliquit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Complaceat tibi, Domine, ut eruas me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, ad adjuvandum me respice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Confundantur et revereantur simul,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui qu&aelig;runt animam meam ut auferant eam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> convertantur retrorsum et revereantur,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui volunt mihi mala.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Ferant confestim confusionem suam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui dicunt mihi: Euge, euge!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Exsultent et l&aelig;tentur super te omnes qu&aelig;rentes te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dicant semper: Magnificetur Dominus, qui diligunt salutare tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa039018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Ego autem mendicus sum et pauper;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus sollicitus est mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Adjutor meus et protector meus tu es;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, ne tardaveris.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
