<h1>Psalm 43</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church commemorates former favours, and present afflictions; under which she prays for succour.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 44</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa042.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 43</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the sons of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, to give understanding.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> We have heard, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, with our ears: our fathers have declared to us, The work thou hast wrought in their days, and in the days of old.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thy hand destroyed the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>, and thou plantedst them: thou didst afflict the people and cast them out.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For they got not the possession of the land by their own sword: neither did their own arm save them. But thy right hand and thy arm, and the light of thy countenance: because thou wast pleased with them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Thou art thyself my king and my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who commandest the saving of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Through thee we will push down our enemies with the horn: and through thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> we will <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despise</a> them that rise up against us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For I will not trust in my bow: neither shall my sword save me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> But thou hast saved us from them that afflict us: and hast put them to shame that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> In <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall we <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> all the day long: and in thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> we will give praise for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> But now thou hast cast us off, and put us to shame: and thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, wilt not go out with our armies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Thou hast made us turn our back to our enemies: and they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> us plundered for themselves.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Thou hast given us up like sheep to be eaten: thou hast <a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">scattered</a> us among the nations.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Thou hast sold thy people for no price: and there was no reckoning in the exchange of them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Thou hast made us a reproach to our neighbours, a scoff and derision to them that are round about us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Thou hast made us a byword among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>: a shaking of the head among the people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> All the day long my shame is before me: and the confusion of my face hath covered me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> At the voice of him that reproacheth and detracteth me: at the face of the enemy and persecutor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> All these things have come upon us, yet we have not forgotten thee: and we have not done <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedly</a> in thy covenant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And our heart hath not turned back: neither hast thou turned aside our steps from thy way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> For thou hast <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> us in the place of affliction: and the shadow of death hath covered us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> If we have forgotten the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and if we have spread forth our hands to a strange god:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Shall not <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> search out these things: for he knoweth the secrets of the heart. Because for thy sake we are killed all the day long: we are counted as sheep for the slaughter.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Arise, why sleepest thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>? arise, and cast us not off to the end.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Why turnest thou thy face away? and forgettest our want and our trouble?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> For our <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> down to the dust: our belly cleaveth to the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, help us and <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> us for thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa043001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Filiis Core ad intellectum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa043002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Deus, auribus nostris audivimus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> patres nostri annuntiaverunt nobis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> opus quod operatus es in diebus eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in diebus antiquis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Manus tua gentes disperdidit, et plantasti eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> afflixisti populos, et expulisti eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Nec enim in gladio suo possederunt terram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et brachium eorum non salvavit eos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sed dextera tua et brachium tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et illuminatio vultus tui, quoniam complacuisti in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Tu es ipse rex meus et Deus meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui mandas salutes Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043006vul">6</span>&nbsp;In te inimicos nostros ventilabimus cornu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine tuo spernemus insurgentes in nobis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Non enim in arcu meo sperabo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gladius meus non salvabit me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043008vul">8</span>&nbsp;salvasti enim nos de affligentibus nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et odientes nos confudisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043009vul">9</span>&nbsp;In Deo laudabimur tota die,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine tuo confitebimur in s&aelig;culum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Nunc autem repulisti et confudisti nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non egredieris, Deus, in virtutibus nostris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Avertisti nos retrorsum post inimicos nostros,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui oderunt nos diripiebant sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Dedisti nos tamquam oves escarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in gentibus dispersisti nos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Vendidisti populum tuum sine pretio,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non fuit multitudo in commutationibus eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Posuisti nos opprobrium vicinis nostris;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> subsannationem et derisum his qui sunt in circuitu nostro.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Posuisti nos in similitudinem gentibus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> commotionem capitis in populis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Tota die verecundia mea contra me est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et confusio faciei me&aelig; cooperuit me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043017vul">17</span>&nbsp;a voce exprobrantis et obloquentis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a facie inimici et persequentis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043018vul">18</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c omnia venerunt super nos; nec obliti sumus te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et inique non egimus in testamento tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Et non recessit retro cor nostrum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et declinasti semitas nostras a via tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043020vul">20</span>&nbsp;quoniam humiliasti nos in loco afflictionis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cooperuit nos umbra mortis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Si obliti sumus nomen Dei nostri,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et si expandimus manus nostras ad deum alienum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043022vul">22</span>&nbsp;nonne Deus requiret ista?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipse enim novit abscondita cordis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam propter te mortificamur tota die;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> &aelig;stimati sumus sicut oves occisionis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Exsurge; quare obdormis, Domine?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exsurge, et ne repellas in finem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Quare faciem tuam avertis?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oblivisceris inopi&aelig; nostr&aelig; et tribulationis nostr&aelig;?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Quoniam humiliata est in pulvere anima nostra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> conglutinatus est in terra venter noster.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa043026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Exsurge, Domine, adjuva nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et redime nos propter nomen tuum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
