<h1>Psalm 44</h1>
<div class="h1a">The excellence of Christ's kingdom, and the endowments of his Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 45</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa043.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 44</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for them that shall be changed, for the sons of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, for understanding. A canticle for the <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Beloved</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>For them that shall be changed...</strong> i.e., for <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">happily</a> changed, by being <a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">converted</a> to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. -- Ibid. <strong>The Beloved...</strong> Viz., <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Our Lord Jesus Christ</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> My heart hath uttered a <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> word: I speak my works to the king: My tongue is the pen of a scrivener that writeth swiftly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thou art beautiful above the sons of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>: <a href="../cathen/06689a.htm">grace</a> is poured abroad in thy lips; therefore hath <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> thee for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Gird thy sword upon thy thigh, O thou most mighty.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> With thy comeliness and thy beauty set out, proceed prosperously, and reign. Because of <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> and meekness and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: and thy right hand shall conduct thee wonderfully.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Thy arrows are sharp: under thee shall people fall, into the hearts of the king's enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Thy throne, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, is forever and ever: the sceptre of thy kingdom is a sceptre of uprightness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Thou hast <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: therefore <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, thy <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness above thy fellows.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Myrrh and stacte and cassia perfume thy garments, from the <a href="../cathen/08257b.htm">ivory</a> houses: out of which</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The daughters of kings have delighted thee in thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>. The queen stood on thy right hand, in gilded clothing; surrounded with variety.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Hearken, O daughter, and see, and incline thy ear: and forget thy people and thy father's house.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And the king shall greatly desire thy beauty; for he is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord thy God</a>, and him they shall <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> And the daughters of <a href="../cathen/15109a.htm">Tyre</a> with gifts, yea, all the rich among the people, shall entreat thy countenance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> All the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of the king's daughter is within in golden borders,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Clothed round about with varieties. After her shall virgins be brought to the king: her neighbours shall be brought to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> They shall be brought with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">gladness and rejoicing</a>: they shall be brought into the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a> of the king.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Instead of thy fathers, sons are born to thee: thou shalt make them princes over all the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> They shall remember thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> throughout all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>. Therefore shall people praise thee for ever; yea, for ever and ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa044001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro iis qui commutabuntur. Filiis Core, ad intellectum. Canticum pro dilecto.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa044002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Eructavit cor meum verbum bonum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dico ego opera mea regi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Lingua mea calamus scrib&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> velociter scribentis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Speciosus forma pr&aelig; filiis hominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> diffusa est gratia in labiis tuis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea benedixit te Deus in &aelig;ternum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Accingere gladio tuo super femur tuum, potentissime.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Specie tua et pulchritudine tua</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intende, prospere procede, et regna,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter veritatem, et mansuetudinem, et justitiam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et deducet te mirabiliter dextera tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Sagitt&aelig; tu&aelig; acut&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> populi sub te cadent,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in corda inimicorum regis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Sedes tua, Deus, in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> virga directionis virga regni tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dilexisti justitiam, et odisti iniquitatem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea unxit te Deus, Deus tuus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oleo l&aelig;titi&aelig;, pr&aelig; consortibus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Myrrha, et gutta, et casia a vestimentis tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a domibus eburneis; ex quibus delectaverunt te</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044010vul">10</span>&nbsp;fili&aelig; regum in honore tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Astitit regina a dextris tuis</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in vestitu deaurato, circumdata varietate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Audi, filia, et vide, et inclina aurem tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et obliviscere populum tuum, et domum patris tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et concupiscet rex decorem tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ipse est Dominus Deus tuus, et adorabunt eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Et fili&aelig; Tyri in muneribus vultum tuum deprecabuntur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnes divites plebis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Omnis gloria ejus fili&aelig; regis ab intus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in fimbriis aureis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044015vul">15</span>&nbsp;circumamicta varietatibus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Adducentur regi virgines post eam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> proxim&aelig; ejus afferentur tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Afferentur in l&aelig;titia et exsultatione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adducentur in templum regis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Pro patribus tuis nati sunt tibi filii;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> constitues eos principes super omnem terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa044018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Memores erunt nominis tui in omni generatione et generationem:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea populi confitebuntur tibi in &aelig;ternum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
