<h1>Psalm 45</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church in persecution trusts in the protection of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 46</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa044.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 45</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the sons of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, for the hidden.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is our refuge and strength: a helper in troubles, which have found us exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Therefore we will not fear, when the earth shall be troubled; and the mountains shall be removed into the heart of the sea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Their waters roared and were troubled: the mountains were troubled with his strength.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The stream of the river maketh the city of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> joyful: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a> hath <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">sanctified</a> his own <a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">tabernacle</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is in the midst thereof, it shall not be moved: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> will help it in the morning early.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Nations were troubled, and kingdoms were bowed down: he uttered his voice, the earth trembled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of armies is with us: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> is our protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Come and behold ye the works of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: what wonders he hath done upon earth,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Making wars to cease even to the end of the earth. He shall destroy the bow, and break the weapons: and the shield he shall burn in the fire.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Be still and see that I am <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>; I will be exalted among the nations, and I will be exalted in the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of armies is with us: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> is our protector.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa045001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, filiis Core, pro arcanis. Psalmus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa045002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Deus noster refugium et virtus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adjutor in tribulationibus qu&aelig; invenerunt nos nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Propterea non timebimus dum turbabitur terra,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et transferentur montes in cor maris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Sonuerunt, et turbat&aelig; sunt aqu&aelig; eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> conturbati sunt montes in fortitudine ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Fluminis impetus l&aelig;tificat civitatem Dei:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sanctificavit tabernaculum suum Altissimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Deus in medio ejus, non commovebitur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adjuvabit eam Deus mane diluculo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Conturbat&aelig; sunt gentes, et inclinata sunt regna:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dedit vocem suam, mota est terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dominus virtutum nobiscum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> susceptor noster Deus Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Venite, et videte opera Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; posuit prodigia super terram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045010vul">10</span>&nbsp;auferens bella usque ad finem terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Arcum conteret, et confringet arma,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et scuta comburet igni.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Vacate, et videte quoniam ego sum Deus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exaltabor in gentibus, et exaltabor in terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa045012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Dominus virtutum nobiscum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> susceptor noster Deus Jacob.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
