<h1>Psalm 46</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Gentiles are invited to praise God for the establishment of the kingdom of Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 47</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa045.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 46</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the sons of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O clap your hands, all ye nations: shout unto <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> with the voice of <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is high, terrible: a great king over all the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He hath subdued the people under jus; and the nations under our feet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> He hath chosen for us his inheritance, the beauty of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> which he hath <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is ascended with jubilee, and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with the sound of trumpet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Sing praises to our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, sing ye: sing praises to our king, sing ye.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is the king of all the earth: sing ye wisely.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall reign over the nations: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> sitteth on his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> throne.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The princes of the people are gathered together, with the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/01051a.htm">Abraham</a>: for the strong gods of the earth are exceedingly exalted.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa046001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro filiis Core. Psalmus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa046002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Omnes gentes, plaudite manibus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> jubilate Deo in voce exsultationis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046003vul">3</span>&nbsp;quoniam Dominus excelsus, terribilis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> rex magnus super omnem terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Subjecit populos nobis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gentes sub pedibus nostris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Elegit nobis h&aelig;reditatem suam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> speciem Jacob quam dilexit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ascendit Deus in jubilo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus in voce tub&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Psallite Deo nostro, psallite;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallite regi nostro, psallite:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046008vul">8</span>&nbsp;quoniam rex omnis terr&aelig; Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallite sapienter.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Regnabit Deus super gentes;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus sedet super sedem sanctam suam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa046010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Principes populorum congregati sunt cum Deo Abraham,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam dii fortes terr&aelig; vehementer elevati sunt.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
