<h1>Psalm 47</h1>
<div class="h1a">God is greatly to be praised for the establishment of his Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 48</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa046.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 47</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A psalm of a canticle, for the sons of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, on the second day of the week.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Great is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and exceedingly to be praised in the city of our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> mountain.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> With the <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> of the whole earth is mount Sion founded, on the sides of the north, the city of the great king.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> In her houses shall <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> be known, when he shall protect her.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For behold the kings of the earth assembled themselves: they gathered together.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> So they saw, and they wondered, they were troubled, they were moved:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Trembling took hold of them. There were pains as of a <a href="../cathen/15687b.htm">woman</a> in labour.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> With a vehement wind thou shalt break in pieces the ships of Tharsis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> As we have heard, so have we seen, in the city of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, in the city of our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath founded it for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> We have received thy mercy, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in the midst of thy <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> According to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, so also is thy praise unto the ends of the earth: thy right hand is full of <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Let mount Sion rejoice, and the daughters of <a href="../cathen/08536a.htm">Juda</a> be glad; because of thy judgments, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Surround Sion, and encompass her: tell lye in her towers.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Set your hearts on her strength; and distribute her houses, that ye may relate it in another <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> For this is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> unto eternity, and for ever and ever: he shall rule us for evermore.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

