<h1>Psalm 49</h1>
<div class="h1a">The coming of Christ: who prefers virtue and inward purity before the blood of victims.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 50</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa048.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 49</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A psalm for Asaph.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of gods, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath spoken: and he hath called the earth. From the rising of the sun, to the going down thereof:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Out of Sion the loveliness of his beauty.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall come manifestly: our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall come, and shall not keep silence. A fire shall burn before him: and a mighty tempest shall be round about him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He shall call heaven from above, and the earth, to judge his people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Gather ye together his saints to him: who set his covenant before <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifices</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> And the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> shall declare his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: for <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is judge.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Hear, O my people, and I will speak: O <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, and I will testify to thee: I am <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, thy <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> I will not reprove thee for thy <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifices</a>: and thy burnt <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">offerings</a> are always in my sight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I will not take calves out of thy house: nor he goats out of thy flocks.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For all the beasts of the woods are mine: the cattle on the hills, and the oxen.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> I know all the fowls of the air: and with me is the beauty of the field.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> If I should be hungry, I would not tell thee: for the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Shall I eat the flesh of bullocks? or shall I drink the blood of goats?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Offer to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> the <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of praise: and pay thy <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vows</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> But to the sinner <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath said: Why dost thou declare my justices, and take my covenant in thy mouth?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Seeing thou hast <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> discipline: and hast cast my words behind thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> If thou didst see a thief thou didst run with him: and with adulterers thou hast been a partaker.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Thy mouth hath abounded with <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>, and thy tongue framed deceits.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Sitting thou didst speak against thy brother, and didst lay a <a href="../cathen/13506d.htm">scandal</a> against thy mother's son:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> These things hast thou done, and I was silent. Thou thoughtest <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a> that I should be like to thee: but I will reprove thee, and set before thy face.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Understand these things, you that forget <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>; lest he snatch you away, and there be none to deliver you.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> The <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of praise shall <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> me: and there is the way by which I will show him the <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

