<h1>Psalm 50</h1>
<div class="h1a">The repentance and confession of David after his sin. The fourth penitential psalm.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 51</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa049.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 50</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>,</span>
<span class="pro002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> When <a href="../cathen/10711a.htm">Nathan the prophet</a> came to him, after he had <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sinned</a> with Bethsabee. [2 Samuel 12.]</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, according to thy great mercy. And according to the multitude of thy tender mercies blot out my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Wash me yet more from my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>, and cleanse me from my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For I know my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>, and my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a> is always before me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> To thee only have I <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sinned</a>, and have done <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> before thee: that thou mayst be justified in thy words, and mayst overcome when thou art judged.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For behold I was conceived in <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>; and in <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> did my mother conceive me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For behold thou hast <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: the uncertain and hidden things of thy wisdom thou hast made manifest to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Thou shalt sprinkle me with <a href="../cathen/07612a.htm">hyssop</a>, and I shall be cleansed: thou shalt wash me, and I shall be made whiter than snow.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> To my hearing thou shalt give <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy and gladness</a>: and the bones that have been <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> shall rejoice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Turn away thy face from my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>, and blot out all my <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Create a clean heart in me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and renew a right spirit within my bowels.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Cast me not away from thy face; and take not thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> spirit from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Restore unto me the <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> of thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, and strengthen me with a perfect spirit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> I will teach the unjust thy ways: and the wicked shall be converted to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Deliver me from blood, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, thou <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: and my tongue shall extol thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou wilt open my lips: and my mouth shall declare thy praise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> For if thou hadst desired <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a>, I would indeed have given it: with burnt <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">offerings</a> thou wilt not be delighted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> A <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is an afflicted spirit: a <a href="../cathen/04337a.htm">contrite</a> and <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> heart, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, thou wilt not <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despise</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Deal favourably, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> will with Sion; that the walls of <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a> may be built up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Then shalt thou accept the <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">oblations</a> and <a href="../cathen/07396b.htm">whole burnt offerings</a>: then shall they lay calves upon thy <a href="../cathen/01360a.htm">altar</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa050001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David,</span>
<span class="pro002"><span class="verse" id="psa050002vul">2</span>&nbsp;cum venit ad eum Nathan propheta, quando intravit ad Bethsabee.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa050003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Deus, secundum magnam misericordiam tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum multitudinem miserationum tuarum, dele iniquitatem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Amplius lava me ab iniquitate mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et a peccato meo munda me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quoniam iniquitatem meam ego cognosco,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et peccatum meum contra me est semper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Tibi soli peccavi, et malum coram te feci;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut justificeris in sermonibus tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vincas cum judicaris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Ecce enim in iniquitatibus conceptus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in peccatis concepit me mater mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Ecce enim veritatem dilexisti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> incerta et occulta sapienti&aelig; tu&aelig; manifestasti mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Asperges me hyssopo, et mundabor;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> lavabis me, et super nivem dealbabor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Auditui meo dabis gaudium et l&aelig;titiam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsultabunt ossa humiliata.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Averte faciem tuam a peccatis meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes iniquitates meas dele.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Cor mundum crea in me, Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et spiritum rectum innova in visceribus meis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Ne projicias me a facie tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et spiritum sanctum tuum ne auferas a me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Redde mihi l&aelig;titiam salutaris tui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et spiritu principali confirma me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Docebo iniquos vias tuas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et impii ad te convertentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Libera me de sanguinibus, Deus, Deus salutis me&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exsultabit lingua mea justitiam tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Domine, labia mea aperies,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et os meum annuntiabit laudem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Quoniam si voluisses sacrificium, dedissem utique;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> holocaustis non delectaberis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Sacrificium Deo spiritus contribulatus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cor contritum et humiliatum, Deus, non despicies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Benigne fac, Domine, in bona voluntate tua Sion,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut &aelig;dificentur muri Jerusalem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa050021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Tunc acceptabis sacrificium justiti&aelig;, oblationes et holocausta;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tunc imponent super altare tuum vitulos.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
