<h1>Psalm 54</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of a just man under persecution from the wicked. It agrees to Christ persecuted by the Jews, and betrayed by Judas.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 55</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa053.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 54</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, in verses, understanding for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, and <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despise</a> not my supplication:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Be attentive to me and hear me. I am grieved in my exercise; and am troubled,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> At the voice of the enemy, and at the tribulation of the sinner. For they have cast <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> upon me: and in <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> they were troublesome to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> My heart is troubled within me: and the fear of death is fallen upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Fear and trembling are come upon me: and darkness hath covered me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> And I said: Who will give me wings like a <a href="../cathen/05144b.htm">dove</a>, and I will fly and be at rest?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Lo, I have gone far off flying away; and I abode in the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I waited for him that hath saved me from pusillanimity of spirit, and a storm.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Cast down, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and divide their tongues; for I have seen <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> and contradiction in the city.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Day and night shall <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> surround it upon its walls: and in the midst thereof are labour,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">injustice</a>. And <a href="../cathen/15235c.htm">usury</a> and deceit have not departed from its streets.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For if my enemy had <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">reviled</a> me, I would verily have borne with it. And if he that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> me had spoken great things against me, I would perhaps have hidden my self from him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But thou a <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> of one mind, my guide, and my familiar,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Who didst take sweetmeats together with me: in the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of God</a> we walked with consent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Let death come upon them, and let them go down alive into hell. For there is <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a> in their dwellings: in the midst of them. <span class="stiki"><strong>Let death, etc...</strong> This, and such like imprecations which occur in the psalms, are delivered <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophetically</a>; that is, by way of foretelling the punishments which shall fall upon the wicked from divine <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and approving the righteous ways of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: but not by way of ill will, or uncharitable <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">curses</a>, which the <a href="../cathen/09071a.htm">law of God</a> disallows.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> But I have cried to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will save me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Evening and morning, and at noon I will speak and declare: and he shall hear my voice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> He shall <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> in peace from them that draw near to me: for among many they were with me. <span class="stiki"><strong>Among many, etc...</strong> That is, they that drew near to attack me were many in company all combined to fight against me.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall hear, and the Eternal shall <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> them. For there is no change with them, and they have not feared <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> He hath stretched forth his hand to repay. They have defiled his covenant,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> They are divided by the <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> of his countenance, and his heart hath drawn near. His words are smoother than oil, and the same are darts. <span class="stiki"><strong>They are divided, etc...</strong> Dispersed, scattered, and brought to nothing, by the <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>; who looks with indignation on their <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> and deceitful ways.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Cast thy care upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he shall sustain thee: he shall not suffer the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> to waver for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> But thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, shalt bring them down into the pit of destruction. Bloody and deceitful <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> shall not live out half their days; but I will trust in thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa054001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, in carminibus. Intellectus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa054002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exaudi, Deus, orationem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ne despexeris deprecationem meam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054003vul">3</span>&nbsp;intende mihi, et exaudi me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Contristatus sum in exercitatione mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et conturbatus sum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054004vul">4</span>&nbsp;a voce inimici, et a tribulatione peccatoris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam declinaverunt in me iniquitates,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in ira molesti erant mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Cor meum conturbatum est in me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et formido mortis cecidit super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Timor et tremor venerunt super me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et contexerunt me tenebr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Et dixi: Quis dabit mihi pennas sicut columb&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et volabo, et requiescam?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Ecce elongavi fugiens,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mansi in solitudine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Exspectabam eum qui salvum me fecit</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a pusillanimitate spiritus, et tempestate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig;cipita, Domine; divide linguas eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam vidi iniquitatem et contradictionem in civitate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Die ac nocte circumdabit eam super muros ejus iniquitas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et labor in medio ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054012vul">12</span>&nbsp;et injustitia:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non defecit de plateis ejus usura et dolus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Quoniam si inimicus meus maledixisset mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sustinuissem utique.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et si is qui oderat me super me magna locutus fuisset,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> abscondissem me forsitan ab eo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Tu vero homo unanimis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dux meus, et notus meus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054015vul">15</span>&nbsp;qui simul mecum dulces capiebas cibos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in domo Dei ambulavimus cum consensu.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Veniat mors super illos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et descendant in infernum viventes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam nequiti&aelig; in habitaculis eorum, in medio eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Ego autem ad Deum clamavi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus salvabit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Vespere, et mane, et meridie, narrabo, et annuntiabo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaudiet vocem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Redimet in pace animam meam ab his qui appropinquant mihi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam inter multos erant mecum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Exaudiet Deus, et humiliabit illos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui est ante s&aelig;cula.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non enim est illis commutatio,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non timuerunt Deum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Extendit manum suam in retribuendo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> contaminaverunt testamentum ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054022vul">22</span>&nbsp;divisi sunt ab ira vultus ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et appropinquavit cor illius.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Molliti sunt sermones ejus super oleum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ipsi sunt jacula.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Jacta super Dominum curam tuam, et ipse te enutriet;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non dabit in &aelig;ternum fluctuationem justo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa054024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Tu vero, Deus, deduces eos in puteum interitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Viri sanguinum et dolosi non dimidiabunt dies suos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem sperabo in te, Domine.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
