<h1>Psalm 55</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of David in danger and distress.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 56</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa054.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 55</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for a people that is removed at a distance form the sanctuary: for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, for an inscription of a title (or pillar) when the <a href="../cathen/12021c.htm">Philistines</a> held him in Geth.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, for <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> hath trodden me under foot; all the day long he hath afflicted me fighting against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> My enemies have trodden on me all the day long; for they are many that make <a href="../cathen/15546c.htm">war</a> against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> From the height of the day I shall fear: but I will trust in thee. <span class="stiki"><strong>The height of the day...</strong> That is, even at noonday, when the sun is the highest, I am still in danger.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> In <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> I will praise my words, in <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> I have put my trust: I will not fear what flesh can do against me. <span class="stiki"><strong>My words...</strong> The words or <a href="../cathen/12453a.htm">promises</a> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> has made in my favour.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> All the day long they detested my words: all their thoughts were against me unto <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They will dwell and hide themselves: they will watch my heel. As they have waited for my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For nothing shalt thou save them: in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> thou shalt break the people in pieces. O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, <span class="stiki"><strong>For nothing shalt thou save them...</strong> That is, since they lie in wait to ruin my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, thou shalt for no consideration favour or assist them, but execute thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> upon them.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I have declared to thee my life: thou hast set me tears in thy sight, As also in thy promise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Then shall my enemies be turned back. In what day soever I shall call upon thee, behold I know thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> In <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> will I praise the word, in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will I praise his speech. In <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> have I hoped, I will not fear what <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> can do to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> In me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, are <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vows</a> to thee, which I will pay, praises to thee:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Because thou hast delivered my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from death, my feet from falling: that I may please in the sight of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in the light of the living.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa055001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro populo qui a sanctis longe factus est. David in tituli inscriptionem, cum tenuerunt eum Allophyli in Geth.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa055002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Deus, quoniam conculcavit me homo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die impugnans, tribulavit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Conculcaverunt me inimici mei tota die,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam multi bellantes adversum me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Ab altitudine diei timebo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego vero in te sperabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055005vul">5</span>&nbsp;In Deo laudabo sermones meos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in Deo speravi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non timebo quid faciat mihi caro.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Tota die verba mea execrabantur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adversum me omnes cogitationes eorum in malum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Inhabitabunt, et abscondent;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipsi calcaneum meum observabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sicut sustinuerunt animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055008vul">8</span>&nbsp;pro nihilo salvos facies illos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in ira populos confringes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Deus, vitam meam annuntiavi tibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> posuisti lacrimas meas in conspectu tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut et in promissione tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055010vul">10</span>&nbsp;tunc convertentur inimici mei retrorsum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In quacumque die invocavero te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ecce cognovi quoniam Deus meus es.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055011vul">11</span>&nbsp;In Deo laudabo verbum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in Domino laudabo sermonem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In Deo speravi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non timebo quid faciat mihi homo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055012vul">12</span>&nbsp;In me sunt, Deus, vota tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; reddam, laudationes tibi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa055013vul">13</span>&nbsp;quoniam eripuisti animam meam de morte,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et pedes meos de lapsu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut placeam coram Deo in lumine viventium.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
