<h1>Psalm 56</h1>
<div class="h1a">The prophet prays in his affliction, and praises God for his delivery.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 57</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa055.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 56</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, destroy not, for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, for an inscription of a title, when he fled from <a href="../cathen/13486d.htm">Saul</a> into the cave. [1 Samuel 24.] <span class="stiki"><strong>Destroy not...</strong> Suffer me not to be destroyed.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, have mercy on me: for my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> trusteth in thee. And in the shadow of thy wings will I hope, until <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> pass away.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> I will cry to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> the most high; to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> who hath done <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He hath sent from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and delivered me: he hath made them a reproach that trod upon me. <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath sent his mercy and his <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> And he hath delivered my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from the midst of the young lions. I slept troubled. The sons of men, whose teeth are weapons and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Be thou exalted, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, and thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> above all the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They prepared a snare for my feet; and they bowed down my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>. They dug a pit before my face, and they are fallen into it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> My heart is ready, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, my heart is ready: I will sing, and rehearse a psalm.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Arise, O my <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>, arise psaltery and harp: I will arise early.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> I will give praise to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, among the people: I will sing a psalm to thee among the nations.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For thy mercy is magnified even to the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> unto the clouds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Be thou exalted, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: and thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> above all the earth.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa056001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, ne disperdas. David in tituli inscriptionem, cum fugeret a facie Saul in speluncam.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa056002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Deus, miserere mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in te confidit anima mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et in umbra alarum tuarum sperabo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> donec transeat iniquitas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Clamabo ad Deum altissimum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deum qui benefecit mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Misit de c&aelig;lo, et liberavit me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dedit in opprobrium conculcantes me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Misit Deus misericordiam suam et veritatem suam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056005vul">5</span>&nbsp;et eripuit animam meam de medio catulorum leonum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dormivi conturbatus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Filii hominum dentes eorum arma et sagitt&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lingua eorum gladius acutus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Exaltare super c&aelig;los, Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in omnem terram gloria tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Laqueum paraverunt pedibus meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et incurvaverunt animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Foderunt ante faciem meam foveam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et inciderunt in eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Paratum cor meum, Deus, paratum cor meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantabo, et psalmum dicam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Exsurge, gloria mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exsurge, psalterium et cithara:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exsurgam diluculo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Confitebor tibi in populis, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et psalmum dicam tibi in gentibus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056011vul">11</span>&nbsp;quoniam magnificata est usque ad c&aelig;los misericordia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et usque ad nubes veritas tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa056012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Exaltare super c&aelig;los, Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super omnem terram gloria tua.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
