<h1>Psalm 63</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer in affliction, with confidence in God that he will bring to nought the machinations of persecutors.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 64</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa062.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 63</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a psalm for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Hear O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, when I make supplication to thee: deliver my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from the fear of the enemy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thou hast protected me from the assembly of the malignant; from the multitude of the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For they have whetted their tongues like a sword; they have bent their bow a bitter thing,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> To shoot in secret the undefiled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> They will shoot at him on a sudden, and will not fear: they are resolute in <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a>. They have talked of hiding snares; they have said: Who shall see them?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They have searched after <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>: they have failed in their search. Man shall come to a deep heart: <span class="stiki"><strong>A deep heart...</strong> That is, crafty, subtle, deep projects and designs; which nevertheless shall not succeed; for <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall be exalted in bringing them to nought by his wisdom and power.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall be exalted. The arrows of children are their wounds: <span class="stiki"><strong>The arrows of children are their wounds...</strong> That is, the wounds, stripes, or blows, they seek to inflict upon the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, are but like the weak efforts of children's arrows, which can do no execution: and their tongues, that is, their speeches against them come to nothing.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> And their tongues against them are made weak. All that saw them were troubled;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> And every <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> was afraid. And they declared the works of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and understood his doings.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall rejoice in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and shall hope in him: and all the upright in heart shall be praised.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa063001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa063002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exaudi, Deus, orationem meam cum deprecor;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a timore inimici eripe animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Protexisti me a conventu malignantium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a multitudine operantium iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia exacuerunt ut gladium linguas suas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intenderunt arcum rem amaram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063005vul">5</span>&nbsp;ut sagittent in occultis immaculatum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Subito sagittabunt eum, et non timebunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> firmaverunt sibi sermonem nequam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Narraverunt ut absconderent laqueos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dixerunt: Quis videbit eos?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Scrutati sunt iniquitates;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> defecerunt scrutantes scrutinio.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Accedet homo ad cor altum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063008vul">8</span>&nbsp;et exaltabitur Deus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sagitt&aelig; parvulorum fact&aelig; sunt plag&aelig; eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063009vul">9</span>&nbsp;et infirmat&aelig; sunt contra eos lingu&aelig; eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Conturbati sunt omnes qui videbant eos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063010vul">10</span>&nbsp;et timuit omnis homo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et annuntiaverunt opera Dei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et facta ejus intellexerunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa063011vul">11</span>&nbsp;L&aelig;tabitur justus in Domino, et sperabit in eo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et laudabuntur omnes recti corde.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
