<h1>Psalm 66</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for the propagation of the Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 67</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa065.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 66</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, in hymns, a psalm of a canticle for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> May <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> have mercy on us, and <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> us: may he cause the light of his countenance to shine upon us, and may he have mercy on us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> That we may know thy way upon earth: thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> in all nations.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Let people confess to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: let all people give praise to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Let the nations be glad and rejoice: for thou judgest the people with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and directest the nations upon earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Let the people, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, confess to thee: let all the people give praise to thee:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The earth hath yielded her fruit. May <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> us,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> May <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> us: and all the ends of the earth fear him.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa066001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, in hymnis. Psalmus cantici David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa066002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Deus misereatur nostri, et benedicat nobis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> illuminet vultum suum super nos, et misereatur nostri:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066003vul">3</span>&nbsp;ut cognoscamus in terra viam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in omnibus gentibus salutare tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Confiteantur tibi populi, Deus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confiteantur tibi populi omnes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066005vul">5</span>&nbsp;L&aelig;tentur et exsultent gentes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam judicas populos in &aelig;quitate,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gentes in terra dirigis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Confiteantur tibi populi, Deus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confiteantur tibi populi omnes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Terra dedit fructum suum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> benedicat nos Deus, Deus noster!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa066008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Benedicat nos Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et metuant eum omnes fines terr&aelig;.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
