<h1>Psalm 68</h1>
<div class="h1a">Christ in his passion declares the greatness of his sufferings, and the malice of his persecutors the Jews; and foretells their reprobation.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 69</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa067.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 68</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for them that shall be changed; for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>For them that shall be changed...</strong> A psalm for <a href="../cathen/03712a.htm">Christian</a> <a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">converts</a>, to remember the <a href="../cathen/11527b.htm">passion of Christ</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Save me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: for the waters are come in even unto my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>The waters...</strong> Of afflictions and sorrows. My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is sorrowful even unto death. <a href="../bible/mat026.htm#verse38">Matthew 26:38</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> I stick fast in the mire of the deep and there is no sure standing. I am come into the depth of the sea, and a tempest hath overwhelmed me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> I have laboured with crying; my jaws are become hoarse, my eyes have failed, whilst I hope in my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They are multiplied above the hairs of my head, who <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> me without cause. My enemies are grown strong who have wrongfully persecuted me: then did I pay that which I took not away. <span class="stiki"><strong>I pay that which I took not away...</strong> <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a> in his <a href="../cathen/11527b.htm">passion</a> made <a href="../cathen/12788a.htm">restitution</a> of what he had not taken away, by suffering the punishment due to our <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>, and so repairing the injury we had done to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, thou knowest my foolishness; and my offences are not hidden from thee: <span class="stiki"><strong>My foolishness and my offences...</strong> which my enemies impute to me: or the follies and <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>, which I have taken upon myself.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Let not them be ashamed for me, who look for thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>. Let them not be confounded on my account, who seek thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Because for thy sake I have borne reproach; shame hath covered my face.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I am become a stranger to my brethren, and an alien to the sons of my mother.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For the zeal of thy house hath eaten me up: and the reproaches of them that reproached thee are fallen upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And I covered my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> in <a href="../cathen/05789c.htm">fasting</a>: and it was made a reproach to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And I made haircloth my garment: and I became a byword to them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> They that sat in the gate spoke against me: and they that drank wine made me their song.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But as for me, my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> is to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; for the time of thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> pleasure, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. In the multitude of thy mercy hear me, in the <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> of thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Draw me out of the mire, that I may not stick fast: deliver me from them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> me, and out of the deep waters.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Let not the tempest of water drown me, nor the deep water swallow me up: and let not the pit shut her mouth upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Hear me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for thy mercy is kind; look upon me according to the multitude of thy tender mercies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> And turn not away thy face from thy servant: for I am in trouble, hear me speedily.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Attend to my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and deliver it: save me because of my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Thou knowest my reproach, and my confusion, and my shame.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> In thy sight are all they that afflict me; my heart hath expected reproach and misery. And I looked for one that would grieve together with me, but there was none: and for one that would comfort me, and I found none.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> And they gave me gall for my food, and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Let their table become as a snare before them, and a recompense, and a stumbling block. <span class="stiki"><strong>Let their table, etc...</strong> What here follows in the style of an imprecation, is a <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophecy</a> of the wretched state to which the <a href="../cathen/08399a.htm">Jews</a> should be reduced in punishment of their wilful obstinacy.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Let their eyes be darkened that they see not; and their back bend thou down always.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Pour out thy indignation upon them: and let thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrathful</a> <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> take hold of them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> Let their habitation be made desolate: and let there be none to dwell in their tabernacles.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> Because they have persecuted him whom thou hast smitten; and they have added to the grief of my wounds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> Add thou <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> upon their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and let them not come into thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> Let them be blotted out of the book of the living; and with the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> let them not be written.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> But I am <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> and sorrowful: thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, hath set me up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> I will praise the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> with a canticle: and I will magnify him with praise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> And it shall please <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> better than a young calf, that bringeth forth horns and hoofs.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> Let the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> see and rejoice: seek ye <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and your <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> shall live.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath heard the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: and hath not <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a> his prisoners.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> Let the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> and the earth praise him; the sea, and every thing that creepeth therein.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> For <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> will save Sion, and the cities of <a href="../cathen/08536a.htm">Juda</a> shall be built up. And they shall dwell there, and acquire it by inheritance. <span class="stiki"><strong>Sion...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/03449a.htm">catholic</a> <a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">church</a>. The cities of <a href="../cathen/08536a.htm">Juda</a>, etc., her places of <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">worship</a>, which shall be established throughout the world. And there, viz., in this <a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">church of Christ</a>, shall his servants dwell, etc.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> And the seed of his servants shall possess it; and they that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> shall dwell therein.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa068001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro iis qui commutabuntur. David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa068002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Salvum me fac, Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam intraverunt aqu&aelig; usque ad animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Infixus sum in limo profundi et non est substantia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Veni in altitudinem maris, et tempestas demersit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Laboravi clamans, rauc&aelig; fact&aelig; sunt fauces me&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> defecerunt oculi mei, dum spero in Deum meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Multiplicati sunt super capillos capitis mei</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui oderunt me gratis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Confortati sunt qui persecuti sunt me</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inimici mei injuste;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; non rapui, tunc exsolvebam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Deus, tu scis insipientiam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et delicta mea a te non sunt abscondita.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Non erubescant in me qui exspectant te, Domine, Domine virtutum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non confundantur super me qui qu&aelig;runt te, Deus Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Quoniam propter te sustinui opprobrium;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> operuit confusio faciem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Extraneus factus sum fratribus meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et peregrinus filiis matris me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam zelus domus tu&aelig; comedit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et opprobria exprobrantium tibi ceciderunt super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et operui in jejunio animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factum est in opprobrium mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et posui vestimentum meum cilicium;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factus sum illis in parabolam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Adversum me loquebantur qui sedebant in porta,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in me psallebant qui bibebant vinum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Ego vero orationem meam ad te, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tempus beneplaciti, Deus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In multitudine misericordi&aelig; tu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exaudi me in veritate salutis tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Eripe me de luto, ut non infigar;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> libera me ab iis qui oderunt me, et de profundis aquarum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Non me demergat tempestas aqu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque absorbeat me profundum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque urgeat super me puteus os suum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Exaudi me, Domine, quoniam benigna est misericordia tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum multitudinem miserationum tuarum respice in me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Et ne avertas faciem tuam a puero tuo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam tribulor, velociter exaudi me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Intende anim&aelig; me&aelig;, et libera eam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter inimicos meos, eripe me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Tu scis improperium meum, et confusionem meam, et reverentiam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068021vul">21</span>&nbsp;in conspectu tuo sunt omnes qui tribulant me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Improperium exspectavit cor meum et miseriam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sustinui qui simul contristaretur, et non fuit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui consolaretur, et non inveni.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Et dederunt in escam meam fel,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in siti mea potaverunt me aceto.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Fiat mensa eorum coram ipsis in laqueum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in retributiones, et in scandalum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Obscurentur oculi eorum, ne videant,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dorsum eorum semper incurva.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Effunde super eos iram tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et furor ir&aelig; tu&aelig; comprehendat eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Fiat habitatio eorum deserta,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in tabernaculis eorum non sit qui inhabitet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Quoniam quem tu percussisti persecuti sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super dolorem vulnerum meorum addiderunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Appone iniquitatem super iniquitatem eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non intrent in justitiam tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068029vul">29</span>&nbsp;Deleantur de libro viventium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum justis non scribantur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068030vul">30</span>&nbsp;Ego sum pauper et dolens;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salus tua, Deus, suscepit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068031vul">31</span>&nbsp;Laudabo nomen Dei cum cantico,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et magnificabo eum in laude:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068032vul">32</span>&nbsp;et placebit Deo super vitulum novellum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cornua producentem et ungulas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068033vul">33</span>&nbsp;Videant pauperes, et l&aelig;tentur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig;rite Deum, et vivet anima vestra:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068034vul">34</span>&nbsp;quoniam exaudivit pauperes Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vinctos suos non despexit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068035vul">35</span>&nbsp;Laudent illum c&aelig;li et terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mare, et omnia reptilia in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068036vul">36</span>&nbsp;Quoniam Deus salvam faciet Sion,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et &aelig;dificabuntur civitates Juda,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et inhabitabunt ibi, et h&aelig;reditate acquirent eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa068037vul">37</span>&nbsp;Et semen servorum ejus possidebit eam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui diligunt nomen ejus habitabunt in ea.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
