<h1>Psalm 70</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for perseverance.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 71</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa069.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 70</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">psalm</a> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Of the sons of Jonadab, and the former <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14039a.htm">-->captives<!--</a>-->. In thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>-->, let me never be put to confusion: <span class="stiki"><strong>Of the sons of Jonadab...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/12676a.htm">Rechabites</a>, of whom see <a href="../bible/jer035.htm">Jeremiah 35</a>. By this addition of the seventy-two interpreters, we gather that this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> was usually sung in the <a href="../cathen/14379b.htm">synagogue</a>, in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11726a.htm">-->person<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/12676a.htm">Rechabites</a>, and of those who were first carried away into <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Deliver me in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and rescue me. Incline thy ear unto me, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Be thou unto me a <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, a protector, and a place of strength: that thou mayst make me safe. For thou art my <a href="../cathen/06079b.htm">firmament</a> and my refuge.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Deliver me, O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, out of the hand of the sinner, and out of the hand of the transgressor of the <a href="../cathen/10582c.htm">law</a> and of the <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For thou art my patience, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, from my youth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> By thee have I been <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04215b.htm">-->confirmed<!--</a>--> from the womb: from my mother's womb thou art my protector. Of thee I shall continually sing:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I am become unto many as a wonder, but thou art a strong helper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Let my mouth be filled with praise, that I may sing thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>; thy greatness all the day long.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Cast me not off in the time of old age: when my strength shall fail, do not thou forsake me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For my enemies have spoken against me; and they that watched my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> have consulted together,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Saying: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath forsaken him: pursue and take him, for there is none to deliver him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, be not thou far from me: O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, make haste to my help.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Let them be confounded and come to nothing that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04757a.htm">-->detract<!--</a>--> my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>; let them be covered with confusion and blame that seek my hurt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But I will always <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>; and will add to all thy praise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> My mouth shall show forth thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>; thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> all the day long. Because I have not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> <a href="../cathen/05295b.htm">learning</a>, <span class="stiki"><strong>Learning...</strong> As much as to say, I build not upon <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">human</a> learning, but only on the power and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I will enter into the powers of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, I will be mindful of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> alone.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Thou hast taught me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, from my youth: and till now I will declare thy wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> And unto old age and grey hairs: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, forsake me not, Until I show forth thy arm to all the <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> that is to come: Thy power,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, even to the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->highest<!--</a>--> great things thou hast done: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who is like to thee?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> How great troubles hast thou shown me, many and grievous: and turning thou hast brought me to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>-->, and hast brought me back again from the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">depths</a> of the earth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Thou hast multiplied thy magnificence; and turning to me thou hast comforted me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> For I will also <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11618c.htm">-->confess<!--</a>--> to thee thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> with the instruments of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psaltery<!--</a>-->: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I will sing to thee with the harp, thou <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> one of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> My lips shall greatly rejoice, when I shall sing to thee; and my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> which thou hast <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Yea and my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> shall <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditate<!--</a>--> on thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> all the day; when they shall be confounded and put to shame that seek <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> to me.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa070001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, filiorum Jonadab, et priorum captivorum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">In te, Domine, speravi; non confundar in &aelig;ternum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070002vul">2</span>&nbsp;In justitia tua libera me, et eripe me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inclina ad me aurem tuam, et salva me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Esto mihi in Deum protectorem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in locum munitum, ut salvum me facias:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam firmamentum meum et refugium meum es tu.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Deus meus, eripe me de manu peccatoris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de manu contra legem agentis, et iniqui:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070005vul">5</span>&nbsp;quoniam tu es patientia mea, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, spes mea a juventute mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070006vul">6</span>&nbsp;In te confirmatus sum ex utero;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> de ventre matris me&aelig; tu es protector meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in te cantatio mea semper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Tamquam prodigium factus sum multis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tu adjutor fortis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Repleatur os meum laude,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut cantem gloriam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die magnitudinem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Ne projicias me in tempore senectutis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum defecerit virtus mea, ne derelinquas me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quia dixerunt inimici mei mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui custodiebant animam meam consilium fecerunt in unum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070011vul">11</span>&nbsp;dicentes: Deus dereliquit eum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> persequimini et comprehendite eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia non est qui eripiat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Deus, ne elongeris a me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, in auxilium meum respice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Confundantur et deficiant detrahentes anim&aelig; me&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> operiantur confusione et pudore qui qu&aelig;runt mala mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Ego autem semper sperabo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et adjiciam super omnem laudem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Os meum annuntiabit justitiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die salutare tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam non cognovi litteraturam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070016vul">16</span>&nbsp;introibo in potentias Domini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, memorabor justiti&aelig; tu&aelig; solius.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Deus, docuisti me a juventute mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et usque nunc pronuntiabo mirabilia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Et usque in senectam et senium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus, ne derelinquas me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> donec annuntiem brachium tuum generationi omni qu&aelig; ventura est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> potentiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070019vul">19</span>&nbsp;et justitiam tuam, Deus, usque in altissima;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; fecisti magnalia, Deus: quis similis tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Quantas ostendisti mihi tribulationes multas et malas!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et conversus vivificasti me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de abyssis terr&aelig; iterum reduxisti me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Multiplicasti magnificentiam tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et conversus consolatus es me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Nam et ego confitebor tibi in vasis psalmi veritatem tuam, Deus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallam tibi in cithara, sanctus Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Exsultabunt labia mea cum cantavero tibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et anima mea quam redemisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa070024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Sed et lingua mea tota die meditabitur justitiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum confusi et reveriti fuerint qui qu&aelig;runt mala mihi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
