<h1>Psalm 71</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prophecy of the coming of Christ, and of his kingdom: prefigured by Solomon and his happy reign.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 72</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa070.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 71</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> on <a href="../cathen/14135b.htm">Solomon</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Give to the king thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and to the king's son thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: To judge thy people with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> with <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let the mountains receive peace for the people: and the hills <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He shall <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> of the people, and he shall <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> the children of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: and he shall <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> the oppressor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> And he shall continue with the sun and before the moon, throughout all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He shall come down like rain upon the fleece; and as <!--note original show-->showers falling gently upon the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> In his days shall <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> spring up, and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->abundance<!--</a>--> of peace, till the moon be taken away.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And he shall rule from sea to sea, and from the river unto the ends of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Before him the <a href="../cathen/05566a.htm">Ethiopians</a> shall fall down: and his enemies shall lick the ground.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The kings of Tharsis and the islands shall offer presents: the kings of the <a href="../cathen/01663a.htm">Arabians</a> and of <a href="../cathen/13285c.htm">Saba</a> shall bring gifts:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And all kings of the earth shall <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> him: all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> shall serve him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> For he shall deliver the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> from the mighty: and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy<!--</a>--> that had no helper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> He shall spare the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor and needy<!--</a>-->: and he shall <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> He shall <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> from <a href="../cathen/15235c.htm">usuries</a> and <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and their <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">names</a> shall be <a href="../cathen/07462a.htm">honourable</a> in his sight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And he shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01663a.htm">-->Arabia<!--</a>-->, for him they shall always <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a>: they shall <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> him all the day.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> And there shall be a <a href="../cathen/06079b.htm">firmament</a> on the earth on the tops of mountains, above <a href="../cathen/09104a.htm">Libanus</a> shall the fruit thereof be exalted: and they of the city shall flourish like the grass of the earth. <span class="stiki"><strong>A firmament on the earth, etc...</strong> This may be understood of the <a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">church of Christ</a>, ever firm and visible: and of the flourishing condition of its congregation.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Let his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> be <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> for evermore: his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> continueth before the sun. And in him shall all the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15039a.htm">-->tribes<!--</a>--> of the earth be <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a>: all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> shall magnify him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, who alone doth wonderful things.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of his majesty for ever: and the whole earth shall be filled with his majesty. So be it. So be it.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro001"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> The praises of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, the son of Jesse, are ended. <span class="stiki"><strong>Are ended...</strong> By this it appears that this <a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">psalm</a>, though placed here, was in order of time the last of those which <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> composed.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>

