<h1>Psalm 72</h1>
<div class="h1a">The temptation of the weak, upon seeing the prosperity of the wicked, is overcome by the consideration of the justice of God, who will quickly render to every one according to his works.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 73</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa071.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 72</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for Asaph.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">How <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> to <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, to them that are of a right heart!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> But my feet were almost moved; my steps had well nigh slipped.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Because I had a <a href="../cathen/15753a.htm">zeal</a> on occasion of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>, seeing the prosperity of sinners.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For there is no regard to their death, nor is there strength in their stripes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They are not in the labour of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>: neither shall they be scourged like other <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Therefore <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">pride</a> hath held them fast: they are covered with their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> and their <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> hath come forth, as it were from fatness: they have passed into the affection of the heart. <span class="stiki"><strong>Fatness...</strong> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Abundance and temporal prosperity<!--</a>-->, which hath encouraged them in their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and made them give themselves up to their irregular affections.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> They have thought and spoken <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a>: they have spoken <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> on high.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> They have set their mouth against <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>: and their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> hath passed through the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Therefore <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> my people return here and full days shall be found in them. <span class="stiki"><strong>Return here...</strong> or hither. The weak among the servants of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> be apt often to return to this thought, and will be shocked when they consider the full days, that is, the long and prosperous <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>; and will be <a href="../cathen/14504a.htm">tempted</a> to make the reflections against <a href="../cathen/12510a.htm">providence</a> which are set down in the following <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verses<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And they said: How doth <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a>? and is there <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knowledge</a> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Behold these are sinners; and yet, abounding in the world they have obtained <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15571a.htm">-->riches<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> And I said: Then have I in vain <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justified<!--</a>--> my heart, and <a href="../cathen/15557b.htm">washed my hands</a> among the innocent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And I have been scourged all the day; and my chastisement hath been in the mornings.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> If I said: I will speak thus; behold I should condemn the <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> of thy children. <span class="stiki"><strong>If I said, etc...</strong> That is, if I should indulge such thoughts as these.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I studied that I might <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> this thing, it is a labour in my sight:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Until I go into the sanctuary of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and understand concerning their last ends.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> But indeed for <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->deceits<!--</a>--> thou hast put it to them: when they were lifted up thou hast cast them down. <span class="stiki"><strong>Thou hast put it to them...</strong> In punishment of their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->deceits<!--</a>-->, or for <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->deceiving<!--</a>--> them, thou hast brought <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> upon them in their last end, which, in their prosperity they never apprehended.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> How are they brought to desolation? they have suddenly ceased to be: they have perished by <!--nnn--><!--<a href="../cathen/12673b.htm">-->reason<!--</a>--> of their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> As the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05154a.htm">-->dream<!--</a>--> of them that awake, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; so in thy city thou shalt bring their image to nothing.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> For my heart hath been inflamed, and my reins have been changed:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> And I am brought to nothing, and I <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knew</a> not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> I am become as a beast before thee: and I am always with thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> Thou hast held me by my right hand; and by thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> thou hast conducted me, and with thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> thou hast received me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> For what have I in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>? and besides thee what do I desire upon earth?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> For thee my flesh and my heart hath fainted away: thou art the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of my heart, and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> that is my portion for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> For behold they that go far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that are disloyal to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> But it is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> for me to adhere to my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, to put my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a>: That I may declare all thy praises, in the gates of the daughter of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa072001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Quam bonus Isra&euml;l Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> his qui recto sunt corde!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Mei autem pene moti sunt pedes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pene effusi sunt gressus mei:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072003vul">3</span>&nbsp;quia zelavi super iniquos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pacem peccatorum videns.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia non est respectus morti eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et firmamentum in plaga eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072005vul">5</span>&nbsp;In labore hominum non sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum hominibus non flagellabuntur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ideo tenuit eos superbia;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> operti sunt iniquitate et impietate sua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Prodiit quasi ex adipe iniquitas eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> transierunt in affectum cordis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Cogitaverunt et locuti sunt nequitiam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> iniquitatem in excelso locuti sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Posuerunt in c&aelig;lum os suum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lingua eorum transivit in terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Ideo convertetur populus meus hic,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dies pleni invenientur in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et dixerunt: Quomodo scit Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et si est scientia in excelso?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Ecce ipsi peccatores, et abundantes in s&aelig;culo</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> obtinuerunt divitias.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Et dixi: Ergo sine causa justificavi cor meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lavi inter innocentes manus meas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072014vul">14</span>&nbsp;et fui flagellatus tota die,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et castigatio mea in matutinis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Si dicebam: Narrabo sic;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ecce nationem filiorum tuorum reprobavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Existimabam ut cognoscerem hoc;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> labor est ante me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072017vul">17</span>&nbsp;donec intrem in sanctuarium Dei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et intelligam in novissimis eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Verumtamen propter dolos posuisti eis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dejecisti eos dum allevarentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Quomodo facti sunt in desolationem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> subito defecerunt: perierunt propter iniquitatem suam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Velut somnium surgentium, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in civitate tua imaginem ipsorum ad nihilum rediges.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Quia inflammatum est cor meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et renes mei commutati sunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072022vul">22</span>&nbsp;et ego ad nihilum redactus sum, et nescivi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072023vul">23</span>&nbsp;ut jumentum factus sum apud te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ego semper tecum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Tenuisti manum dexteram meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in voluntate tua deduxisti me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cum gloria suscepisti me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Quid enim mihi est in c&aelig;lo?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et a te quid volui super terram?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Defecit caro mea et cor meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus cordis mei, et pars mea, Deus in &aelig;ternum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Quia ecce qui elongant se a te peribunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> perdidisti omnes qui fornicantur abs te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa072028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Mihi autem adh&aelig;rere Deo bonum est;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ponere in Domino Deo spem meam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut annuntiem omnes pr&aelig;dicationes tuas</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in portis fili&aelig; Sion.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
