<h1>Psalm 73</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of the Church under grievous persecutions.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 74</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa072.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 73</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Understanding for Asaph.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, why hast thou cast us off unto the end: why is thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> enkindled against the sheep of thy pasture?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Remember thy congregation, which thou hast possessed from the beginning. The sceptre of thy inheritance which thou hast <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a>: mount Sion in which thou hast dwelt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Lift up thy hands against their <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">pride</a> unto the end; see what things the enemy hath done <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedly</a> in the sanctuary.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> thee have made their boasts, in the midst of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14133a.htm">-->solemnity<!--</a>-->. They have set up their ensigns for <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10338a.htm">-->signs<!--</a>-->, <span class="stiki"><strong>Their ensigns, etc...</strong> They have fixed their colours for <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10338a.htm">-->signs<!--</a>--> and trophies, both on the gates, and on the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->highest<!--</a>--> top of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>: and they <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knew</a> not, that is, they regarded not the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">sanctity</a> of the place. This <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> manifestly foretells the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/09493b.htm">Machabees</a>, and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13321a.htm">-->profanation<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a> by Antiochus.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> And they <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knew</a> not both in the going out and on the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->highest<!--</a>--> top. As with axes in a wood of trees,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> They have cut down at once the gates thereof, with axe and hatchet they have brought it down.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They have set fire to thy sanctuary: they have defiled the dwelling place of thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> on the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> They said in their heart, the whole <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05782a.htm">-->kindred<!--</a>--> of them together: Let us abolish all the festival days of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> from the land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Our <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10338a.htm">-->signs<!--</a>--> we have not seen, there is now no <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophet</a>: and he will <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> us no more.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> How long, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, shall the enemy reproach: is the adversary to provoke thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> for ever?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Why dost thou turn away thy hand: and thy right hand out of the midst of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01055a.htm">-->bosom<!--</a>--> for ever?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> But <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is our king before ages: he hath wrought <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> in the midst of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Thou by thy strength didst make the sea firm: thou didst crush the heads of the dragons in the waters. <span class="stiki"><strong>The sea firm...</strong> By making the waters of the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a> stand like firm walls, whilst <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> passed through: and destroying the <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egyptians</a> called here dragons from their cruelty, in the same waters, with their king: casting up their bodies on the shore to be stripped by the <a href="../cathen/05566a.htm">Ethiopians</a> inhabiting in those days the coast of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01663a.htm">-->Arabia<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Thou hast broken the heads of the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->dragon<!--</a>-->: thou hast given him to be meat for the people of the <a href="../cathen/05566a.htm">Ethiopians</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Thou hast broken up the fountains and the torrents: thou hast dried up the Ethan rivers. <span class="stiki"><strong>Ethan rivers...</strong> That is, rivers which run with strong streams. This was verified in <a href="../cathen/08501a.htm">Jordan</a> (<a href="../bible/jos003.htm">Joshua 3</a>) and in Arnon (<a href="../bible/num021.htm#verse14">Numbers 21:14</a>).</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Thine is the day, and thine is the night: thou hast made the morning light and the sun.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Thou hast made all the borders of the earth: the summer and the spring were formed by thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Remember this, the enemy hath reproached the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and a foolish people hath provoked thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Deliver not up to beasts the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11618c.htm">-->confess<!--</a>--> to thee: and forget not to the end the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Have regard to thy covenant: for they that are the obscure of the earth have been filled with dwellings of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>The obscure of the earth...</strong> Mean and ignoble wretches have been filled, that is, enriched, with houses of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>, that is, with our estates and <a href="../cathen/12462a.htm">possessions</a>, which they have <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a> acquired.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Let not the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> be turned away with confusion: the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor and needy<!--</a>--> shall praise thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> thy own <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03459a.htm">-->cause<!--</a>-->: remember thy reproaches with which the foolish <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> hath reproached thee all the day.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> Forget not the voices of thy enemies: the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">pride</a> of them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> thee <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01767a.htm">-->ascendeth<!--</a>--> continually.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

