<h1>Psalm 74</h1>
<div class="h1a">There is a just judgment to come: therefore let the wicked take care.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 75</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa073.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 74</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, corrupt not, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> for Asaph. <span class="stiki"><strong>Corrupt not...</strong> It is <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believed</a> to have been the beginning of some ode or <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07595a.htm">-->hymn<!--</a>-->, to the tune of which this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> was to be sung. <a href="../cathen/02084a.htm">St. Augustine</a> and other fathers take it to be an <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04394a.htm">-->admonition<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/07409a.htm">spirit of God</a>, not to faint or fail in our <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>: but to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11711a.htm">-->persevere<!--</a>--> with constancy in <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: because <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> will not fail in his due <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> to render to every <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> according to his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> We <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: we <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> praise, and we <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> call upon thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>. We <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> relate thy wondrous <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> When I shall take a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>-->, I will <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> justices. <span class="stiki"><strong>When I shall take a time...</strong> In proper times: particularly at the last day, when the earth shall melt away at the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the great <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Judge<!--</a>-->: the same who originally laid the foundations of it, and as it were established its pillars.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> The earth is melted, and all that dwell therein: I have established the pillars thereof.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I said to the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>: Do not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->act<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedly</a>: and to the sinners: Lift not up the horn.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Lift not up your horn on high: speak not <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> against <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">desert</a> hills:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>-->. One he putteth down, and another he lifteth up:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> For in the hand of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> there is a cup of strong <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01358a.htm">-->wine<!--</a>--> full of mixture. And he hath poured it out from this to that: but the dregs thereof are not emptied: all the sinners of the earth shall drink.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> But I will declare for ever: I will sing to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And I will break all the horns of sinners: but the horns of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall be exalted.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa074001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, ne corrumpas. Psalmus cantici Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa074002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Confitebimur tibi, Deus, confitebimur,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et invocabimus nomen tuum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> narrabimus mirabilia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Cum accepero tempus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego justitias judicabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Liquefacta est terra et omnes qui habitant in ea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego confirmavi columnas ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dixi iniquis: Nolite inique agere:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et delinquentibus: Nolite exaltare cornu:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074006vul">6</span>&nbsp;nolite extollere in altum cornu vestrum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nolite loqui adversus Deum iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quia neque ab oriente, neque ab occidente,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque a desertis montibus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074008vul">8</span>&nbsp;quoniam Deus judex est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Hunc humiliat, et hunc exaltat:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074009vul">9</span>&nbsp;quia calix in manu Domini vini meri, plenus misto.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et inclinavit ex hoc in hoc;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> verumtamen f&aelig;x ejus non est exinanita:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> bibent omnes peccatores terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Ego autem annuntiabo in s&aelig;culum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantabo Deo Jacob:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa074011vul">11</span>&nbsp;et omnia cornua peccatorum confringam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltabuntur cornua justi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
