<h1>Psalm 76</h1>
<div class="h1a">The faithful have recourse to God in trouble of mind, with confidence in his mercy and power.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 77</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa075.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 76</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for Idithun, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with my voice; to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> with my voice, and he gave ear to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> In the days of my trouble I sought <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, with my hands lifted up to him in the night, and I was not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->deceived<!--</a>-->. My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> refused to be comforted:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> I remembered <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and was delighted, and was exercised, and my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> swooned away.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> My eyes prevented the watches: I was troubled, and I spoke not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> I thought upon the days of old: and I had in my <a href="../cathen/10321a.htm">mind</a> the <a href="../cathen/05551b.htm">eternal</a> years.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> And I <a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">meditated</a> in the night with my own heart: and I was exercised and I swept my <a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">spirit</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Will <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> then cast off for ever? or will he never be more favourable again?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Or will he cut off his mercy for ever, from <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Or will <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> forget to show mercy? or will he in his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> shut up his mercies?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And I said, Now have I begun: this is the change of the right hand of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> I remembered the works of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: for I will be mindful of thy wonders from the beginning.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> And I will meditate on all thy works: and will be employed in thy inventions.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Thy way, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, is in the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> place: who is the great <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> like our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Thou art the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> that dost wonders. Thou hast made thy power <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> With thy arm thou hast <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> thy people the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">children of Jacob</a> and of <a href="../cathen/08506a.htm">Joseph</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The waters saw thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, the waters saw thee: and they were <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->afraid<!--</a>-->, and the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">depths</a> were troubled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Great was the noise of the waters: the clouds sent out a sound. For thy arrows pass:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> The voice of thy thunder in a wheel. Thy lightnings enlightened the world: the earth shook and trembled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Thy way is in the sea, and thy paths in many waters: and thy footsteps shall not be <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Thou hast conducted thy people like sheep, by the hand of <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> and <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa076001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro Idithun. Psalmus Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa076002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Voce mea ad Dominum clamavi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> voce mea ad Deum, et intendit mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076003vul">3</span>&nbsp;In die tribulationis me&aelig; Deum exquisivi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> manibus meis nocte contra eum, et non sum deceptus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Renuit consolari anima mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076004vul">4</span>&nbsp;memor fui Dei, et delectatus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exercitatus sum, et defecit spiritus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Anticipaverunt vigilias oculi mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> turbatus sum, et non sum locutus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Cogitavi dies antiquos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et annos &aelig;ternos in mente habui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Et meditatus sum nocte cum corde meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exercitabar, et scopebam spiritum meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Numquid in &aelig;ternum projiciet Deus?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut non apponet ut complacitior sit adhuc?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076009vul">9</span>&nbsp;aut in finem misericordiam suam abscindet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a generatione in generationem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076010vul">10</span>&nbsp;aut obliviscetur misereri Deus?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut continebit in ira sua misericordias suas?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et dixi: Nunc c&oelig;pi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> h&aelig;c mutatio dexter&aelig; Excelsi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Memor fui operum Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia memor ero ab initio mirabilium tuorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076013vul">13</span>&nbsp;et meditabor in omnibus operibus tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in adinventionibus tuis exercebor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Deus, in sancto via tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quis deus magnus sicut Deus noster?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Tu es Deus qui facis mirabilia:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> notam fecisti in populis virtutem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Redemisti in brachio tuo populum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> filios Jacob et Joseph.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Viderunt te aqu&aelig;, Deus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> viderunt te aqu&aelig;, et timuerunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et turbat&aelig; sunt abyssi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Multitudo sonitus aquarum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> vocem dederunt nubes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Etenim sagitt&aelig; tu&aelig; transeunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076019vul">19</span>&nbsp;vox tonitrui tui in rota.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Illuxerunt coruscationes tu&aelig; orbi terr&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> commota est, et contremuit terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076020vul">20</span>&nbsp;In mari via tua, et semit&aelig; tu&aelig; in aquis multis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vestigia tua non cognoscentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa076021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Deduxisti sicut oves populum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in manu Moysi et Aaron.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
