<h1>Psalm 78</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church in time of persecution prays for relief. It seems to belong to the time of the Maccabees.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 79</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa077.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 78</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for Asaph.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, the <a href="../cathen/11388a.htm">heathens</a> are come into thy inheritance, they have defiled thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>: they have made <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a> as a place to keep fruit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> They have given the dead bodies of thy servants to be meat for the fowls of the air: the flesh of thy <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a> for the beasts of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> They have poured out their blood as water, round about <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a> and there was none to <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->bury<!--</a>--> them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> We are become a reproach to our neighbours: a scorn and derision to them that are round about us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> How long, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, wilt thou be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> for ever: shall thy <a href="../cathen/15753a.htm">zeal</a> be kindled like a fire?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Pour out thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> upon the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> that have not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> thee: and upon the kingdoms that have not called upon thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Because they have devoured <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>; and have laid waste his place.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Remember not our former <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>: let thy mercies speedily prevent us, for we are become exceeding <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Help us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, our saviour: and for the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, deliver us: and forgive us our <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> for thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Lest they should say among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>: Where is their <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>? And let him be made <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> before our eyes, By the revenging the blood of thy servants, which hath been shed:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Let the sighing of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12430a.htm">-->prisoners<!--</a>--> come in before thee. According to the greatness of thy arm, take <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12462a.htm">-->possession<!--</a>--> of the children of them that have been <a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">put to death</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And render to our neighbours sevenfold in their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01055a.htm">-->bosom<!--</a>-->: the reproach wherewith they have reproached thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> But we thy people, and the sheep of thy pasture, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> give thanks to thee for ever. We <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> show forth thy praise, unto <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa078001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Deus, venerunt gentes in h&aelig;reditatem tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> polluerunt templum sanctum tuum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> posuerunt Jerusalem in pomorum custodiam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Posuerunt morticina servorum tuorum escas volatilibus c&aelig;li;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> carnes sanctorum tuorum bestiis terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Effuderunt sanguinem eorum tamquam aquam in circuitu Jerusalem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non erat qui sepeliret.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Facti sumus opprobrium vicinis nostris;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> subsannatio et illusio his qui in circuitu nostro sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Usquequo, Domine, irasceris in finem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> accendetur velut ignis zelus tuus?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Effunde iram tuam in gentes qu&aelig; te non noverunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in regna qu&aelig; nomen tuum non invocaverunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078007vul">7</span>&nbsp;quia comederunt Jacob,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et locum ejus desolaverunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Ne memineris iniquitatum nostrarum antiquarum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cito anticipent nos misericordi&aelig; tu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia pauperes facti sumus nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Adjuva nos, Deus salutaris noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et propter gloriam nominis tui, Domine, libera nos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et propitius esto peccatis nostris, propter nomen tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Ne forte dicant in gentibus: Ubi est Deus eorum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et innotescat in nationibus coram oculis nostris</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ultio sanguinis servorum tuorum qui effusus est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Intro&euml;at in conspectu tuo gemitus compeditorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum magnitudinem brachii tui posside filios mortificatorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078012vul">12</span>&nbsp;et redde vicinis nostris septuplum in sinu eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> improperium ipsorum quod exprobraverunt tibi, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa078013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Nos autem populus tuus, et oves pascu&aelig; tu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confitebimur tibi in s&aelig;culum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in generationem et generationem annuntiabimus laudem tuam.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
