<h1>Psalm 79</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for the Church in tribulation, commemorating God's former favours.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 80</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa078.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 79</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for them that shall be changed, a testimony for Asaph, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>-->.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Give ear, O thou that rulest <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>: thou that leadest <a href="../cathen/08506a.htm">Joseph</a> like a sheep. Thou that sittest upon the <a href="../cathen/03646c.htm">cherubims</a>, shine forth</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Before Ephraim, <a href="../cathen/02480b.htm">Benjamin</a>, and <a href="../cathen/09583c.htm">Manasses</a>. Stir up thy might, and come to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">-->Convert<!--</a>--> us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and show us thy face, and we shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->saved<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, how long wilt thou be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> against the <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> of thy servant?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> How long wilt thou feed us with the bread of tears: and give us for our drink tears in measure?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Thou hast made us to be a contradiction to our neighbours: and our enemies have scoffed at us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, <a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">convert</a> us: and show thy face, and we shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->saved<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Thou hast brought a vineyard out of <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>: thou hast cast out the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> and planted it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Thou wast the guide of its journey in its sight: thou plantedst the roots thereof, and it filled the land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The shadow of it covered the hills: and the branches thereof the <a href="../cathen/03473a.htm">cedars</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> It stretched forth its branches unto the sea, and its boughs unto the river.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Why hast thou broken down the hedge thereof, so that all they who pass by the way do pluck it?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The boar out of the wood hath laid it waste: and a singular wild beast hath devoured it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Turn again, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, look down from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>, and see, and visit this vineyard:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> And <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfect<!--</a>--> the same which thy right hand hath planted: and upon the <a href="../cathen/14144a.htm">son of man</a> whom thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04215b.htm">-->confirmed<!--</a>--> for thyself.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Things set on fire and dug down shall perish at the rebuke of thy countenance. <span class="stiki"><strong>Things set on fire, etc...</strong> So this vineyard of thine, almost consumed already, must perish, if thou continue thy rebukes.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Let thy hand be upon the <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">man of thy right hand</a>: and upon the <a href="../cathen/14144a.htm">son of man</a> whom thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04215b.htm">-->confirmed<!--</a>--> for thyself. <span class="stiki"><strong>The man of thy right hand...</strong> <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And we depart not from thee, thou shalt quicken us: and we <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> call upon thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, <a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">convert</a> us and show thy face, and we shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->saved<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa079001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro iis qui commutabuntur. Testimonium Asaph, psalmus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa079002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Qui regis Isra&euml;l, intende;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui deducis velut ovem Joseph.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Qui sedes super cherubim, manifestare</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079003vul">3</span>&nbsp;coram Ephraim, Benjamin, et Manasse.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Excita potentiam tuam, et veni,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut salvos facias nos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Deus, converte nos, et ostende faciem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salvi erimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus virtutum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quousque irasceris super orationem servi tui?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079006vul">6</span>&nbsp;cibabis nos pane lacrimarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et potum dabis nobis in lacrimis in mensura?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Posuisti nos in contradictionem vicinis nostris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et inimici nostri subsannaverunt nos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Deus virtutum, converte nos, et ostende faciem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salvi erimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Vineam de &AElig;gypto transtulisti:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ejecisti gentes, et plantasti eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Dux itineris fuisti in conspectu ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> plantasti radices ejus, et implevit terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Operuit montes umbra ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et arbusta ejus cedros Dei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Extendit palmites suos usque ad mare,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et usque ad flumen propagines ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Ut quid destruxisti maceriam ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vindemiant eam omnes qui pr&aelig;tergrediuntur viam?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Exterminavit eam aper de silva,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et singularis ferus depastus est eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Deus virtutum, convertere,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> respice de c&aelig;lo, et vide,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et visita vineam istam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079016vul">16</span>&nbsp;et perfice eam quam plantavit dextera tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super filium hominis quem confirmasti tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Incensa igni et suffossa,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab increpatione vultus tui peribunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Fiat manus tua super virum dexter&aelig; tu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super filium hominis quem confirmasti tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Et non discedimus a te:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> vivificabis nos, et nomen tuum invocabimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa079020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus virtutum, converte nos, et ostende faciem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salvi erimus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
