<h1>Psalm 80</h1>
<div class="h1a">An invitation to a solemn praising of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 81</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa079.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 80</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the winepresses, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for Asaph himself. <span class="stiki"><strong>For the winepresses, etc...</strong> Torcularibus. It either signifies a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10648a.htm">-->musical<!--</a>--> instrument, or that this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> was to be sung at the feast of the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>--> after the gathering in of the vintage.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Rejoice to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> our helper: sing aloud to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Take a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>-->, and bring hither the timbrel: the pleasant <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psaltery<!--</a>--> with the harp.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Blow up the trumpet on the new moon, on the noted day of your <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14133a.htm">-->solemnity<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For it is a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>--> in <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, and a <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11279a.htm">-->ordained<!--</a>--> it for a testimony in <a href="../cathen/08506a.htm">Joseph</a>, when he came out of the land of <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>: he heard a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> which he <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knew</a> not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He removed his back from the burdens: his hands had served in baskets.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Thou calledst upon me in affliction, and I delivered thee: I heard thee in the secret place of tempest: I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12454c.htm">-->proved<!--</a>--> thee at the waters of contradiction. <span class="stiki"><strong>In the secret place of tempest...</strong> <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a>, <em>of thunder</em>. When thou soughtest to hide thyself from the tempest: or, when I came down to <a href="../cathen/14011a.htm">mount Sina</a>, hidden from thy eyes in a storm of thunder.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Hear, O my people, and I will testify to thee: O <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, if thou wilt hearken to me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<!--note--><span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> There shall be no new <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->god<!--</a>--> in thee: neither shalt thou <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> a strange <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->god<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For I am the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord thy God</a>, who brought thee out of the land of <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>: open thy mouth wide, and I will fill it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> But my people heard not my voice: and <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> hearkened not to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> So I let them go according to the desires of their heart: they shall walk in their own inventions.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> If my people had heard me: if <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> had walked in my ways:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> I should soon have <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> their enemies, and laid my hand on them that troubled them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> The enemies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->lied<!--</a>--> to him: and their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> shall be for ever. <span class="stiki"><strong>Their time shall be forever...</strong> Impenitent sinners shall suffer for ever.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> And he fed them with the fat of wheat, and filled them with honey out of the rock.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa080001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro torcularibus. Psalmus ipsi Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa080002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exsultate Deo adjutori nostro;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> jubilate Deo Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Sumite psalmum, et date tympanum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psalterium jucundum cum cithara.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Buccinate in neomenia tuba,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in insigni die solemnitatis vestr&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080005vul">5</span>&nbsp;quia pr&aelig;ceptum in Isra&euml;l est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et judicium Deo Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Testimonium in Joseph posuit illud,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum exiret de terra &AElig;gypti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> linguam quam non noverat, audivit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Divertit ab oneribus dorsum ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> manus ejus in cophino servierunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080008vul">8</span>&nbsp;In tribulatione invocasti me, et liberavi te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Exaudivi te in abscondito tempestatis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> probavi te apud aquam contradictionis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Audi, populus meus, et contestabor te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Isra&euml;l, si audieris me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080010vul">10</span>&nbsp;non erit in te deus recens,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque adorabis deum alienum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Ego enim sum Dominus Deus tuus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui eduxi te de terra &AElig;gypti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dilata os tuum, et implebo illud.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et non audivit populus meus vocem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Isra&euml;l non intendit mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Et dimisi eos secundum desideria cordis eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ibunt in adinventionibus suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Si populus meus audisset me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Isra&euml;l si in viis meis ambulasset,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080015vul">15</span>&nbsp;pro nihilo forsitan inimicos eorum humiliassem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super tribulantes eos misissem manum meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Inimici Domini mentiti sunt ei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et erit tempus eorum in s&aelig;cula.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa080017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Et cibavit eos ex adipe frumenti,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de petra melle saturavit eos.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
