<h1>Psalm 81</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to judges and men in power.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 82</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa080.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 81</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for Asaph.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath stood in the congregation of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->: and being in the midst of them he <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgeth<!--</a>--> gods.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> How long <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> you <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a>: and accept the <a href="../cathen/11726a.htm">persons</a> of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Judge<!--</a>--> for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/11322b.htm">fatherless</a>: do <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> to the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a> and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Rescue the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->; and deliver the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy<!--</a>--> out of the hand of the sinner.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They have not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> nor understood: they walk on in darkness: all the foundations of the earth shall be moved.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> I have said: You are <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>--> and all of you the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of the most <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->High<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> But you like <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> shall die: and shall fall like one of the princes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> thou the earth: for thou shalt inherit among all the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa081001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Deus stetit in synagoga deorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in medio autem deos dijudicat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Usquequo judicatis iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et facies peccatorum sumitis?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Judicate egeno et pupillo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> humilem et pauperem justificate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Eripite pauperem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et egenum de manu peccatoris liberate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Nescierunt, neque intellexerunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in tenebris ambulant:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> movebuntur omnia fundamenta terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ego dixi: Dii estis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et filii Excelsi omnes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Vos autem sicut homines moriemini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sicut unus de principibus cadetis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa081008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Surge, Deus, judica terram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam tu h&aelig;reditabis in omnibus gentibus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
