<h1>Psalm 82</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer against the enemies of God's Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 83</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa081.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 82</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who shall be like to thee? hold not thy peace, neither be thou still, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For lo, thy enemies have made a noise: and they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> thee have lifted up the head.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> They have taken a <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">malicious</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04435a.htm">-->counsel<!--</a>--> against thy people, and have consulted against thy <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They have said: Come and let us destroy them, so that they be not a nation: and let the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> be remembered no more.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> For they have contrived with one <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04283a.htm">-->consent<!--</a>-->: they have made a covenant together against thee,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">-->tabernacle<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/07638a.htm">Edomites</a>, and the <a href="../cathen/08192a.htm">Ishmahelites</a>: <a href="../cathen/10409b.htm">Moab</a>, and the Agarens,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Gebal, and <a href="../cathen/01431b.htm">Ammon</a> and <a href="../cathen/01377c.htm">Amalec</a>: the <a href="../cathen/12021c.htm">Philistines</a>, with the inhabitants of <a href="../cathen/15109a.htm">Tyre</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Yea, and the <a href="../cathen/02007c.htm">Assyrian</a> also is joined with them: they are come to the aid of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/09366a.htm">Lot</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Do to them as thou didst to <a href="../cathen/09513b.htm">Madian</a> and to Sisara: as to Jabin at the brook of Cisson.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Who perished at Endor: and became as dung for the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Make their princes like Oreb, and Zeb, and Zebee, and Salmana. All their princes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Who have said: Let us possess the sanctuary of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> for an inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, make them like a wheel; and as stubble before the wind.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> As fire which burneth the wood: and as a flame burning mountains:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> So shalt thou pursue them with thy tempest: and shalt trouble them in thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Fill their faces with shame; and they shall seek thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Let them be ashamed and troubled for ever and ever: and let them be confounded and perish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And let them <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: thou alone art the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a> over all the earth.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa082001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum Psalmi Asaph.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa082002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Deus, quis similis erit tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne taceas, neque compescaris, Deus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082003vul">3</span>&nbsp;quoniam ecce inimici tui sonuerunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui oderunt te extulerunt caput.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Super populum tuum malignaverunt consilium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et cogitaverunt adversus sanctos tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dixerunt: Venite, et disperdamus eos de gente,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non memoretur nomen Isra&euml;l ultra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Quoniam cogitaverunt unanimiter;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> simul adversum te testamentum disposuerunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082007vul">7</span>&nbsp;tabernacula Idum&aelig;orum et Ismahelit&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Moab et Agareni,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Gebal, et Ammon, et Amalec;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> alienigen&aelig; cum habitantibus Tyrum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Etenim Assur venit cum illis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facti sunt in adjutorium filiis Lot.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Fac illis sicut Madian et Sisar&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut Jabin in torrente Cisson.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Disperierunt in Endor;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facti sunt ut stercus terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Pone principes eorum sicut Oreb,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Zeb, et Zebee, et Salmana:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnes principes eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082013vul">13</span>&nbsp;qui dixerunt: H&aelig;reditate possideamus sanctuarium Dei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Deus meus, pone illos ut rotam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sicut stipulam ante faciem venti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Sicut ignis qui comburit silvam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sicut flamma comburens montes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082016vul">16</span>&nbsp;ita persequeris illos in tempestate tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in ira tua turbabis eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Imple facies eorum ignominia,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qu&aelig;rent nomen tuum, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Erubescant, et conturbentur in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et confundantur, et pereant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa082019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Et cognoscant quia nomen tibi Dominus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tu solus Altissimus in omni terra.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
