<h1>Psalm 83</h1>
<div class="h1a">The soul aspires after heaven; rejoicing in the mean time, in being in the communion of God's Church upon earth.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 84</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa082.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 83</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the winepresses, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> How lovely are thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> longeth and fainteth for the <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. My heart and my flesh have rejoiced in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">living God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For the sparrow hath found herself a house, and the turtle a nest for herself where she may <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08748a.htm">-->lay<!--</a>--> her young ones: Thy <a href="../cathen/01360a.htm">altars</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, my king and my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> are they that dwell in thy house, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: they shall praise thee for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> whose help is from thee: in his heart he hath disposed to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01767a.htm">-->ascend<!--</a>--> by steps, <span class="stiki"><strong>In his heart he hath disposed to ascend by steps, etc...</strong> Ascensiones in corde suo disposuit. As by steps <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01767a.htm">-->ascended<!--</a>--> to the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple of God</a> situated on a hill; so the <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> <a href="../cathen/03712a.htm">Christian</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01767a.htm">-->ascends<!--</a>--> towards the <a href="../cathen/05551b.htm">eternal</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a> by <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03539b.htm">-->certain<!--</a>--> steps of <a href="../cathen/15472a.htm">virtue</a> disposed or ordered within the heart: and this whilst he <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->lives<!--</a>--> as yet in the body, in this vale of tears, the place which <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> hath set: that is, which he hath brought himself to: being cast out of <a href="../cathen/14519a.htm">paradise</a> for his <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> In the vale of tears, in the place which he hath set.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">-->lawgiver<!--</a>--> shall give a <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a>, they shall go from <a href="../cathen/15472a.htm">virtue</a> to <a href="../cathen/15472a.htm">virtue</a>: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>--> shall be seen in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, hear my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>: give ear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Behold, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> our protector: and look on the face of thy <a href="../cathen/10212c.htm">Christ</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For better is one day in thy <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> above thousands. I have chosen to be an abject in the house of my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, rather than to dwell in the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>--> of sinners.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> For <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> mercy and <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will give <a href="../cathen/06689a.htm">grace</a> and <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> He will not deprive of <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things them that walk in innocence: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that trusteth in thee.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa083001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, pro torcularibus filiis Core. Psalmus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa083002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Quam dilecta tabernacula tua, Domine virtutum!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Concupiscit, et deficit anima mea in atria Domini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cor meum et caro mea exsultaverunt in Deum vivum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Etenim passer invenit sibi domum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et turtur nidum sibi, ubi ponat pullos suos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> altaria tua, Domine virtutum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> rex meus, et Deus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Beati qui habitant in domo tua, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in s&aelig;cula s&aelig;culorum laudabunt te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Beatus vir cujus est auxilium abs te:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ascensiones in corde suo disposuit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083007vul">7</span>&nbsp;in valle lacrimarum, in loco quem posuit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Etenim benedictionem dabit legislator;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ibunt de virtute in virtutem:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> videbitur Deus deorum in Sion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus virtutum, exaudi orationem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> auribus percipe, Deus Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Protector noster, aspice, Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et respice in faciem christi tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Quia melior est dies una in atriis tuis super millia;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> elegi abjectus esse in domo Dei mei</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> magis quam habitare in tabernaculis peccatorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Quia misericordiam et veritatem diligit Deus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> gratiam et gloriam dabit Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa083013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Non privabit bonis eos qui ambulant in innocentia:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine virtutum, beatus homo qui sperat in te.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
