<h1>Psalm 84</h1>
<div class="h1a">The coming of Christ, to bring peace and salvation to man.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 85</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa083.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 84</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>-->.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou hast <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> thy land: thou hast turned away the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thou hast forgiven the <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> of thy people: thou hast covered all their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Thou hast mitigated all thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a>: thou hast turned away from the <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> of thy indignation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">-->Convert<!--</a>--> us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> our saviour: and turn off thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> from us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Wilt thou be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> with us for ever: or wilt thou extend thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> from <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Thou wilt turn, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and bring us to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>-->: and thy people shall rejoice in thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Show us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy mercy; and grant us thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> I will hear what the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> speak in me: for he will speak peace unto his people: And unto his <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>: and unto them that are <a href="../cathen/04347a.htm">converted</a> to the heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Surely his <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> is near to them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him: that <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> may dwell in our land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Mercy and <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> have met each other: <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> and peace have <a href="../cathen/08663a.htm">kissed</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">Truth</a> is sprung out of the earth: and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> hath looked down from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will give <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">goodness</a>: and our earth shall yield her fruit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">-->Justice<!--</a>--> shall walk before him: and shall set his steps in the way.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa084001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem, filiis Core. Psalmus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa084002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Benedixisti, Domine, terram tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> avertisti captivitatem Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Remisisti iniquitatem plebis tu&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> operuisti omnia peccata eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Mitigasti omnem iram tuam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> avertisti ab ira indignationis tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Converte nos, Deus salutaris noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et averte iram tuam a nobis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Numquid in &aelig;ternum irasceris nobis?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut extendes iram tuam a generatione in generationem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Deus, tu conversus vivificabis nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et plebs tua l&aelig;tabitur in te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Ostende nobis, Domine, misericordiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salutare tuum da nobis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Audiam quid loquatur in me Dominus Deus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam loquetur pacem in plebem suam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super sanctos suos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in eos qui convertuntur ad cor.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Verumtamen prope timentes eum salutare ipsius,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut inhabitet gloria in terra nostra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Misericordia et veritas obviaverunt sibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justitia et pax osculat&aelig; sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Veritas de terra orta est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitia de c&aelig;lo prospexit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Etenim Dominus dabit benignitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et terra nostra dabit fructum suum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa084014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Justitia ante eum ambulabit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ponet in via gressus suos.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
<blockquote class="copyright">Transcribed as part of the <a href="http://vulsearch.sourceforge.net">Clementine Vulgate Project</a><br>Please notify the original transcriber (little.mouth@soon.com) of any errors in this Latin edition</blockquote>

