<h1>Psalm 85</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for God's grace to assist us to the end.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 86</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa084.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 85</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Incline thy ear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and hear me: for I am <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy and poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Preserve my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, for I am <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>: <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> thy servant, O my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, that trusteth in thee. <span class="stiki"><strong>I am holy...</strong> I am by my office and profession <a href="../cathen/04673a.htm">dedicated</a> to thy service.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Have mercy on me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I have cried to thee all the day.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Give <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> to the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> of thy servant, for to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, I have lifted up my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, art sweet and mild: and plenteous in mercy to all that call upon thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Give ear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>: and attend to the voice of my petition.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I have called upon thee in the day of my trouble: because thou hast heard me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> There is none among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>--> like unto thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and there is none according to thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> All the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> thou hast made shall come and <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> before thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and they shall <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For thou art great and dost wonderful things: thou art <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> alone.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Conduct me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in thy way, and I will walk in thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: let my heart rejoice that it may <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> I will praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, with my whole heart, and I will <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> for ever:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For thy mercy is great towards me: and thou hast delivered my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> out of the lower hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> are <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12789a.htm">-->risen<!--</a>--> up against me, and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14383a.htm">-->assembly<!--</a>--> of the mighty have sought my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: and they have not set thee before their eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, art a <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of compassion, and merciful, patient, and of much mercy, and <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">true</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> O look upon me, and have mercy on me: give thy command to thy servant, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> the son of thy handmaid.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Show me a token for <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: that they who <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> me may see, and be confounded, because thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, hast helped me and hast comforted me.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa085001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Oratio ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Inclina, Domine, aurem tuam et exaudi me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam inops et pauper sum ego.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Custodi animam meam, quoniam sanctus sum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salvum fac servum tuum, Deus meus, sperantem in te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Miserere mei, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ad te clamavi tota die;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085004vul">4</span>&nbsp;l&aelig;tifica animam servi tui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ad te, Domine, animam meam levavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quoniam tu, Domine, suavis et mitis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mult&aelig; misericordi&aelig; omnibus invocantibus te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Auribus percipe, Domine, orationem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et intende voci deprecationis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085007vul">7</span>&nbsp;In die tribulationis me&aelig; clamavi ad te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia exaudisti me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Non est similis tui in diis, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non est secundum opera tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Omnes gentes quascumque fecisti venient,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et adorabunt coram te, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et glorificabunt nomen tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam magnus es tu, et faciens mirabilia;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tu es Deus solus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Deduc me, Domine, in via tua, et ingrediar in veritate tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> l&aelig;tetur cor meum, ut timeat nomen tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Confitebor tibi, Domine Deus meus, in toto corde meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et glorificabo nomen tuum in &aelig;ternum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085013vul">13</span>&nbsp;quia misericordia tua magna est super me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et eruisti animam meam ex inferno inferiori.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Deus, iniqui insurrexerunt super me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et synagoga potentium qu&aelig;sierunt animam meam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non proposuerunt te in conspectu suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Et tu, Domine Deus, miserator et misericors;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> patiens, et mult&aelig; misericordi&aelig;, et verax.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Respice in me, et miserere mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> da imperium tuum puero tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salvum fac filium ancill&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa085017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Fac mecum signum in bonum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut videant qui oderunt me, et confundantur:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam tu, Domine, adjuvisti me, et consolatus es me.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
