<h1>Psalm 86</h1>
<div class="h1a">The glory of the Church of Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 87</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa085.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 86</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>-->.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">The foundations thereof are the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> mountains: <span class="stiki"><strong>The holy mountains...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/01626c.htm">apostles</a> and <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophets</a> (<a href="../bible/eph002.htm#verse20">Ephesians 2:20</a>).</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> the gates of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>--> above all the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">-->Glorious<!--</a>--> things are said of thee, O city of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> I will be mindful of Rahab and of <a href="../cathen/02179b.htm">Babylon</a> <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knowing</a> me. Behold the foreigners, and <a href="../cathen/15109a.htm">Tyre</a>, and the people of the <a href="../cathen/05566a.htm">Ethiopians</a>, these were there. <span class="stiki"><strong>Rahab...</strong> <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>, etc. To this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, which is the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->church<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, many shall resort from all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Shall not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>--> say: This <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> and that <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> is born in her? and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">-->Highest<!--</a>--> himself hath founded her. <span class="stiki"><strong>Shall not Sion say, etc...</strong> The meaning is, that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, viz., the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->church<!--</a>-->, shall not only be able to commemorate this or that particular <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11726a.htm">-->person<!--</a>--> of renown born in her, but also to <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> in great multitudes of people and princes of her <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07402a.htm">-->communion<!--</a>-->; who have been foretold in the writings of the <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophets</a>, and registered in the writings of the <a href="../cathen/01626c.htm">apostles</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall tell in his writings of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->peoples<!--</a>--> and of princes, of them that have been in her.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The dwelling in thee is as it were of all rejoicing.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa086001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Filiis Core. Psalmus cantici.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Fundamenta ejus in montibus sanctis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086002vul">2</span>&nbsp;diligit Dominus portas Sion super omnia tabernacula Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Gloriosa dicta sunt de te, civitas Dei!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Memor ero Rahab et Babylonis, scientium me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ecce alienigen&aelig;, et Tyrus, et populus &AElig;thiopum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> hi fuerunt illic.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Numquid Sion dicet: Homo et homo natus est in ea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ipse fundavit eam Altissimus?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Dominus narrabit in scripturis populorum et principum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> horum qui fuerunt in ea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa086007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Sicut l&aelig;tantium omnium</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> habitatio est in te.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
