<h1>Psalm 87</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of one under grievous affliction: it agrees to Christ in his passion, and alludes to his death and burial.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 88</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa086.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 87</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core</a>: unto the end, for Maheleth, to answer understanding of Eman the Ezrahite. <span class="stiki"><strong>Maheleth...</strong> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10648a.htm">-->musical<!--</a>--> instrument, or chorus of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10648a.htm">-->musicians<!--</a>-->, to answer one another. -- Ibid. <strong>Understanding...</strong> Or a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of instruction, composed by Eman the Ezrahite, or by <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, in his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: I have cried in the day, and in the night before thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> come in before thee: incline thy ear to my petition.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is filled with <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a>: and my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>--> hath drawn nigh to hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I am counted among them that go down to the pit: I am become as a <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> without help,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Free among the dead. Like the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slain<!--</a>--> sleeping in the sepulchres, whom thou rememberest no more: and they are cut off from thy hand.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They have laid me in the lower pit: in the dark places, and in the shadow of death.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> is strong over me: and all thy waves thou hast brought in upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Thou hast put away my acquaintance far from me: they have set me an <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">-->abomination<!--</a>--> to themselves. I was delivered up, and came not forth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> My eyes languished through <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poverty<!--</a>-->. All the day I cried to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I stretched out my hands to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Wilt thou show wonders to the dead? or shall physicians raise to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>-->, and give praise to thee?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Shall any one in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07425a.htm">-->sepulchre<!--</a>--> declare thy mercy: and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> in destruction?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Shall thy wonders be <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> in the dark; and thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> in the land of forgetfulness?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But I, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, have cried to thee: and in the morning my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> shall prevent thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, why castest thou off my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>: why turnest thou away thy face from me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I am <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->, and in labours from my youth: and being exalted have been <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> and troubled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> hath come upon me: and thy terrors have troubled me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> They have come round about me like water all the day: they have compassed me about together.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Friend and neighbour thou hast put far from me: and my acquaintance, because of misery.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa087001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum Psalmi, filiis Core, in finem, pro Maheleth ad respondendum. Intellectus Eman Ezrahit&aelig;.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa087002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, Deus salutis me&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in die clamavi et nocte coram te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Intret in conspectu tuo oratio mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inclina aurem tuam ad precem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia repleta est malis anima mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vita mea inferno appropinquavit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087005vul">5</span>&nbsp;&AElig;stimatus sum cum descendentibus in lacum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> factus sum sicut homo sine adjutorio,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087006vul">6</span>&nbsp;inter mortuos liber;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut vulnerati dormientes in sepulchris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quorum non es memor amplius,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ipsi de manu tua repulsi sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Posuerunt me in lacu inferiori,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in tenebrosis, et in umbra mortis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Super me confirmatus est furor tuus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes fluctus tuos induxisti super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Longe fecisti notos meos a me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> posuerunt me abominationem sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Traditus sum, et non egrediebar;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087010vul">10</span>&nbsp;oculi mei languerunt pr&aelig; inopia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Clamavi ad te, Domine, tota die;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> expandi ad te manus meas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Numquid mortuis facies mirabilia?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut medici suscitabunt, et confitebuntur tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Numquid narrabit aliquis in sepulchro misericordiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et veritatem tuam in perditione?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Numquid cognoscentur in tenebris mirabilia tua?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitia tua in terra oblivionis?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Et ego ad te, Domine, clamavi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mane oratio mea pr&aelig;veniet te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Ut quid, Domine, repellis orationem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> avertis faciem tuam a me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Pauper sum ego, et in laboribus a juventute mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exaltatus autem, humiliatus sum et conturbatus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087017vul">17</span>&nbsp;In me transierunt ir&aelig; tu&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et terrores tui conturbaverunt me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087018vul">18</span>&nbsp;circumdederunt me sicut aqua tota die;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> circumdederunt me simul.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa087019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Elongasti a me amicum et proximum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et notos meos a miseria.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
