<h1>Psalm 88</h1>
<div class="h1a">The perpetuity of the Church of Christ, in consequence of the promise of God: which, notwithstanding, God permits her to suffer sometimes most grievous afflictions.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 89</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa087.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 88</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Of understanding, for Ethan the Ezrahite.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> I will sing for ever. I will show forth thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> with my mouth to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For thou hast said: Mercy shall be built up for ever in the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> shall be prepared in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> I have made a covenant with my <a href="../cathen/05374a.htm">elect</a>: I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">-->sworn<!--</a>--> to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> my servant:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Thy seed <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I settle for ever. And I will build up thy throne unto <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> shall <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11618c.htm">-->confess<!--</a>--> thy wonders, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->church<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For who in the clouds can be compared to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: or who among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall be like to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who is <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorified</a> in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14383a.htm">-->assembly<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>: great and terrible above all them that are about him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord God</a> of <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>, who is like to thee? thou art mighty, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> is round about thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Thou rulest the power of the sea: and appeasest the motion of the waves thereof.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Thou hast <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> one, as one that is <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slain<!--</a>-->: with the arm of thy strength thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">-->scattered<!--</a>--> thy enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Thine are the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, and thine is the earth: the world and the fulness thereof thou hast founded:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> The north and the sea thou hast <a href="../cathen/04470a.htm">created</a>. <a href="../cathen/14551a.htm">Thabor</a> and <a href="../cathen/07288a.htm">Hermon</a> shall rejoice in thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Thy arm is with might. Let thy hand be strengthened, and thy right hand exalted:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">-->Justice<!--</a>--> and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> are the preparation of thy throne. Mercy and <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> shall go before thy face:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the people that <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knoweth</a> jubilation. They shall walk, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in the light of thy countenance:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> And in thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> they shall rejoice all the day, and in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> they shall be exalted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> For thou art the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of their strength: and in thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> pleasure shall our horn be exalted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> For our protection is of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and of our king the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> one of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Then thou spokest in a <a href="../cathen/15477a.htm">vision</a> to thy <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>, and saidst: I have laid help upon one that is mighty, and have exalted one chosen out of my people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> I have found <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> my servant: with my <a href="../cathen/11229a.htm">holy oil</a> I have <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->anointed<!--</a>--> him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> For my hand shall help him: and my arm shall strengthen him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> The enemy shall have no advantage over him: nor the son of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> have power to hurt him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> And I will cut down his enemies before his face; and them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> him I will put to flight.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> And my <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> and my mercy shall be with him: and in my <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> shall his horn be exalted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> And I will set his hand in the sea; and his right hand in the rivers.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> He shall cry out to me: Thou art my father: my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and the support of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> And I will make him my <a href="../cathen/06081a.htm">firstborn</a>, high above the kings of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> I will keep my mercy for him for ever: and my covenant <a href="../cathen/05752c.htm">faithful</a> to him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> And I will make his seed to endure for evermore: and his throne as the days of <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> And if his children forsake my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->, and walk not in my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> If they <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13321a.htm">-->profane<!--</a>--> my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">-->justices<!--</a>-->: and keep not my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> I will visit their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> with a rod and their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> with stripes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> But my mercy I will not take away from him: nor <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I suffer my <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> to fail.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> Neither <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13321a.htm">-->profane<!--</a>--> my covenant: and the words that proceed from my mouth I will not make void.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> Once have I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">-->sworn<!--</a>--> by my <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holiness</a>: I will not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->lie<!--</a>--> unto <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> His seed shall endure for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> And his throne as the sun before me: and as the moon <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfect<!--</a>--> for ever, and a <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->faithful<!--</a>--> witness in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> But thou hast rejected and <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a>: thou hast been <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> with my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->anointed<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> Thou hast overthrown the covenant of thy servant: thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13321a.htm">-->profaned<!--</a>--> his sanctuary on the earth. <span class="stiki"><strong>Overthrown the covenant, etc...</strong> All this seems to relate to the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/02179b.htm">Babylon</a>, in which, for the <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a> of the people and their princes, <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> seemed to have set aside for a while the covenant he made with <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse41">41</span> Thou hast broken down all his hedges: thou hast made his strength <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse42">42</span> All that pass by the way have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14564b.htm">-->robbed<!--</a>--> him: he is become a reproach to his neighbours.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse43">43</span> Thou hast set up the right hand of them that oppress him: thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse44">44</span> Thou hast turned away the help of his sword; and hast not assisted him in battle.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse45">45</span> Thou hast made his <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->purification<!--</a>--> to cease: and thou hast cast his throne down to the ground.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse46">46</span> Thou hast shortened the days of his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>-->: thou hast covered him with confusion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse47">47</span> How long, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, turnest thou away unto the end? shall thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> burn like fire?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse48">48</span> Remember what my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->substance<!--</a>--> is: for hast thou made all the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> in vain?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse49">49</span> Who is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that shall live, and not see death: that shall deliver his <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> from the hand of hell?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse50">50</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, where are thy ancient mercies, according to what thou didst <a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">swear</a> to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> in thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse51">51</span> Be mindful, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, of the reproach of thy servants (which I have held in my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01055a.htm">-->bosom<!--</a>-->) of many <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse52">52</span> Wherewith thy enemies have reproached, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; wherewith they have reproached the change of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->anointed<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse53">53</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> for evermore. So be it. So be it.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa088001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Intellectus Ethan Ezrahit&aelig;.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa088002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Misericordias Domini in &aelig;ternum cantabo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in generationem et generationem annuntiabo veritatem tuam in ore meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Quoniam dixisti: In &aelig;ternum misericordia &aelig;dificabitur in c&aelig;lis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pr&aelig;parabitur veritas tua in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Disposui testamentum electis meis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> juravi David servo meo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Usque in &aelig;ternum pr&aelig;parabo semen tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et &aelig;dificabo in generationem et generationem sedem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Confitebuntur c&aelig;li mirabilia tua, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> etenim veritatem tuam in ecclesia sanctorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quoniam quis in nubibus &aelig;quabitur Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> similis erit Deo in filiis Dei?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Deus, qui glorificatur in consilio sanctorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> magnus et terribilis super omnes qui in circuitu ejus sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus virtutum, quis similis tibi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> potens es, Domine, et veritas tua in circuitu tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Tu dominaris potestati maris;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> motum autem fluctuum ejus tu mitigas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Tu humiliasti, sicut vulneratum, superbum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in brachio virtutis tu&aelig; dispersisti inimicos tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Tui sunt c&aelig;li, et tua est terra:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> orbem terr&aelig;, et plenitudinem ejus tu fundasti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088013vul">13</span>&nbsp;aquilonem et mare tu creasti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Thabor et Hermon in nomine tuo exsultabunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088014vul">14</span>&nbsp;tuum brachium cum potentia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Firmetur manus tua, et exaltetur dextera tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088015vul">15</span>&nbsp;justitia et judicium pr&aelig;paratio sedis tu&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericordia et veritas pr&aelig;cedent faciem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Beatus populus qui scit jubilationem:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, in lumine vultus tui ambulabunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088017vul">17</span>&nbsp;et in nomine tuo exsultabunt tota die,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in justitia tua exaltabuntur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Quoniam gloria virtutis eorum tu es,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in beneplacito tuo exaltabitur cornu nostrum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Quia Domini est assumptio nostra,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sancti Isra&euml;l regis nostri.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Tunc locutus es in visione sanctis tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dixisti: Posui adjutorium in potente,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltavi electum de plebe mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Inveni David, servum meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oleo sancto meo unxi eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Manus enim mea auxiliabitur ei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et brachium meum confortabit eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Nihil proficiet inimicus in eo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et filius iniquitatis non apponet nocere ei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Et concidam a facie ipsius inimicos ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et odientes eum in fugam convertam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Et veritas mea et misericordia mea cum ipso,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine meo exaltabitur cornu ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Et ponam in mari manum ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in fluminibus dexteram ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Ipse invocabit me: Pater meus es tu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, et susceptor salutis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Et ego primogenitum ponam illum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> excelsum pr&aelig; regibus terr&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088029vul">29</span>&nbsp;In &aelig;ternum servabo illi misericordiam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et testamentum meum fidele ipsi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088030vul">30</span>&nbsp;Et ponam in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi semen ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et thronum ejus sicut dies c&aelig;li.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088031vul">31</span>&nbsp;Si autem dereliquerint filii ejus legem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in judiciis meis non ambulaverint;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088032vul">32</span>&nbsp;si justitias meas profanaverint,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mandata mea non custodierint:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088033vul">33</span>&nbsp;visitabo in virga iniquitates eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in verberibus peccata eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088034vul">34</span>&nbsp;misericordiam autem meam non dispergam ab eo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque nocebo in veritate mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088035vul">35</span>&nbsp;neque profanabo testamentum meum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qu&aelig; procedunt de labiis meis non faciam irrita.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088036vul">36</span>&nbsp;Semel juravi in sancto meo, si David mentiar:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088037vul">37</span>&nbsp;semen ejus in &aelig;ternum manebit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et thronus ejus sicut sol in conspectu meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088038vul">38</span>&nbsp;et sicut luna perfecta in &aelig;ternum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et testis in c&aelig;lo fidelis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088039vul">39</span>&nbsp;Tu vero repulisti et despexisti;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> distulisti christum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088040vul">40</span>&nbsp;Evertisti testamentum servi tui;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> profanasti in terra sanctuarium ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088041vul">41</span>&nbsp;Destruxisti omnes sepes ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> posuisti firmamentum ejus formidinem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088042vul">42</span>&nbsp;Diripuerunt eum omnes transeuntes viam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> factus est opprobrium vicinis suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088043vul">43</span>&nbsp;Exaltasti dexteram deprimentium eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> l&aelig;tificasti omnes inimicos ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088044vul">44</span>&nbsp;Avertisti adjutorium gladii ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non es auxiliatus ei in bello.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088045vul">45</span>&nbsp;Destruxisti eum ab emundatione,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sedem ejus in terram collisisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088046vul">46</span>&nbsp;Minorasti dies temporis ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> perfudisti eum confusione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088047vul">47</span>&nbsp;Usquequo, Domine, avertis in finem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exardescet sicut ignis ira tua?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088048vul">48</span>&nbsp;Memorare qu&aelig; mea substantia:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> numquid enim vane constituisti omnes filios hominum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088049vul">49</span>&nbsp;Quis est homo qui vivet et non videbit mortem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> eruet animam suam de manu inferi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088050vul">50</span>&nbsp;Ubi sunt misericordi&aelig; tu&aelig; antiqu&aelig;, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut jurasti David in veritate tua?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088051vul">51</span>&nbsp;Memor esto, Domine, opprobrii servorum tuorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quod continui in sinu meo, multarum gentium:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088052vul">52</span>&nbsp;quod exprobraverunt inimici tui, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quod exprobraverunt commutationem christi tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa088053vul">53</span>&nbsp;Benedictus Dominus in &aelig;ternum. Fiat, fiat.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
