<h1>Psalm 90</h1>
<div class="h1a">The just is secure under the protection of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 91</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa089.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 90</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The praise of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">He that dwelleth in the aid of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>, shall abide under the protection of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> He shall say to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: Thou art my protector, and my refuge: my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, in him <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I trust.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For he hath delivered me from the snare of the hunters: and from the sharp word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He will overshadow thee with his shoulders: and under his wings thou shalt trust.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> His <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> shall compass thee with a shield: thou shalt not be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->afraid<!--</a>--> of the terror of the night.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Of the arrow that flieth in the day, of the business that walketh about in the dark: of invasion, or of the noonday <a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">devil</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> A thousand shall fall at thy side, and ten thousand at thy right hand: but it shall not come nigh thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> But thou shalt consider with thy eyes: and shalt see the reward of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Because thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, art my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>: thou hast made the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a> thy refuge.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> There shall no <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> come to thee: nor shall the scourge come near thy dwelling.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For he hath given his <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a> charge over thee; to keep thee in all thy ways.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> In their hands they shall bear thee up: lest thou dash thy foot against a stone.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Thou shalt walk upon the asp and the basilisk: and thou shalt trample under foot the lion and the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->dragon<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Because he <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in me I will deliver him: I will protect him because he hath <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> my <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> He shall cry to me, and I will hear him: I am with him in tribulation, I will deliver him, and I will <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glorify</a> him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I will fill him with length of days; and I will show him my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa090001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Laus cantici David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Qui habitat in adjutorio Altissimi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in protectione Dei c&aelig;li commorabitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dicet Domino: Susceptor meus es tu, et refugium meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus, sperabo in eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Quoniam ipse liberavit me de laqueo venantium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et a verbo aspero.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Scapulis suis obumbrabit tibi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sub pennis ejus sperabis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Scuto circumdabit te veritas ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non timebis a timore nocturno;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090006vul">6</span>&nbsp;a sagitta volante in die,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a negotio perambulante in tenebris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab incursu, et d&aelig;monio meridiano.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Cadent a latere tuo mille, et decem millia a dextris tuis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad te autem non appropinquabit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Verumtamen oculis tuis considerabis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et retributionem peccatorum videbis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Quoniam tu es, Domine, spes mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Altissimum posuisti refugium tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Non accedet ad te malum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et flagellum non appropinquabit tabernaculo tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Quoniam angelis suis mandavit de te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut custodiant te in omnibus viis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090012vul">12</span>&nbsp;In manibus portabunt te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne forte offendas ad lapidem pedem tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Super aspidem et basiliscum ambulabis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et conculcabis leonem et draconem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Quoniam in me speravit, liberabo eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> protegam eum, quoniam cognovit nomen meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Clamabit ad me, et ego exaudiam eum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum ipso sum in tribulatione:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> eripiam eum, et glorificabo eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa090016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Longitudine dierum replebo eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ostendam illi salutare meum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
