<h1>Psalm 91</h1>
<div class="h1a">God is to be praised for his wondrous works.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 92</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa090.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 91</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> on the <a href="../cathen/13287b.htm">sabbath day</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> It is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> to give praise to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and to sing to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> To show forth thy mercy in the morning, and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> in the night:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Upon an instrument of ten strings, upon the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psaltery<!--</a>-->: with a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> upon the harp.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For thou hast given me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, a delight in thy doings: and in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of thy hands I shall rejoice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, how great are thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->! thy thoughts are exceeding deep.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The senseless <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> shall not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a>: nor <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> the fool understand these things.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> When the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> shall spring up as grass: and all the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> shall appear: That they may perish for ever and ever:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> But thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, art most high for evermore.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For behold thy enemies, O lord, for behold thy enemies shall perish: and all the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">-->scattered<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> But my horn shall be exalted like that of the unicorn: and my old age in plentiful mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> My eye also hath looked down upon my enemies: and my ear shall hear of the downfall of the malignant that rise up against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow up like the <a href="../cathen/03473a.htm">cedar</a> of <a href="../cathen/09104a.htm">Libanus</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> They that are planted in the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a> shall flourish in the <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of our God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> They shall still increase in a fruitful old age: and shall be well treated,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> That they may show, That the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a> is righteous, and there is no <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> in him.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa091001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus cantici, in die sabbati.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa091002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Bonum est confiteri Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et psallere nomini tuo, Altissime:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091003vul">3</span>&nbsp;ad annuntiandum mane misericordiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et veritatem tuam per noctem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091004vul">4</span>&nbsp;in decachordo, psalterio;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum cantico, in cithara.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quia delectasti me, Domine, in factura tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in operibus manuum tuarum exsultabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Quam magnificata sunt opera tua, Domine!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nimis profund&aelig; fact&aelig; sunt cogitationes tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Vir insipiens non cognoscet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et stultus non intelliget h&aelig;c.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Cum exorti fuerint peccatores sicut f&oelig;num,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et apparuerint omnes qui operantur iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut intereant in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091009vul">9</span>&nbsp;tu autem Altissimus in &aelig;ternum, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quoniam ecce inimici tui, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ecce inimici tui peribunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dispergentur omnes qui operantur iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et exaltabitur sicut unicornis cornu meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et senectus mea in misericordia uberi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Et despexit oculus meus inimicos meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in insurgentibus in me malignantibus audiet auris mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Justus ut palma florebit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut cedrus Libani multiplicabitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Plantati in domo Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in atriis domus Dei nostri florebunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Adhuc multiplicabuntur in senecta uberi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et bene patientes erunt:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa091016vul">16</span>&nbsp;ut annuntient quoniam rectus Dominus Deus noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non est iniquitas in eo.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
