<h1>Psalm 93</h1>
<div class="h1a">God shall judge and punish the oppressors of his people.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 94</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa092.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 93</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself on the fourth day of the week.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> to whom revenge belongeth: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of revenge hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->acted<!--</a>--> freely.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Lift up thyself, thou that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08549a.htm">-->judgest<!--</a>--> the earth: render a reward to the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> How long shall sinners, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: how long shall sinners <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Shall they utter, and speak <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: shall all speak who work <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">injustice</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Thy people, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, they have brought low: and they have afflicted thy inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> They have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slain<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/15617c.htm">widow</a> and the stranger: and they have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->murdered<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/11322b.htm">fatherless</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> And they have said: The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall not see: neither shall the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> understand.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Understand, ye senseless among the people: and, you fools, be wise at last.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? or he that formed the eye, doth he not consider?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> He that chastiseth <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->, shall he not rebuke: he that teacheth <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knowledge</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knoweth</a> the thoughts of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>, that they are vain.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> whom thou shalt instruct, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and shalt teach him out of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> That thou mayst give him rest from the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> days: till a pit be dug for the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>Rest from the evil days...</strong> That thou mayst mitigate the sorrows, to which he is exposed, during the short and <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> days of his mortality.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will not cast off his people: neither <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> he forsake his own inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Until <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> be turned into <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->: and they that are near it are all the upright in heart. <span class="stiki"><strong>Until justice be turned into judgment, etc...</strong> By being put in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">-->execution<!--</a>-->; which <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> be agreeable to all the upright in heart.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Who shall rise up for me against the evildoers? or who shall stand with me against the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Unless the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> had been my helper, my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> had almost dwelt in hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> If I said: My foot is moved: thy mercy, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, assisted me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> According to the multitude of my sorrows in my heart, thy comforts have given <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> to my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Doth the seat of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> stick to thee, who framest labour in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>-->? <span class="stiki"><strong>Doth the seat of iniquity stick to thee, etc...</strong> That is, wilt thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who art always <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, admit of the seat of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: that is, of <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">injustice</a>, or <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judges<!--</a>-->, to have any partnership with thee? Thou who framest, or makest, labour in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>-->, that is, thou who <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11189a.htm">-->obligest<!--</a>--> us to labour with all diligence to keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> They <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> hunt after the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, and will condemn innocent blood.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> But the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my refuge: and my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> the help of my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> And he will render them their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and in their <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">malice</a> he will destroy them: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> destroy them.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa093001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus ipsi David, quarta sabbati.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Deus ultionum Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus ultionum libere egit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Exaltare, qui judicas terram;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> redde retributionem superbis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Usquequo peccatores, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> usquequo peccatores gloriabuntur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093004vul">4</span>&nbsp;effabuntur et loquentur iniquitatem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> loquentur omnes qui operantur injustitiam?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Populum tuum, Domine, humiliaverunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et h&aelig;reditatem tuam vexaverunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Viduam et advenam interfecerunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et pupillos occiderunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Et dixerunt: Non videbit Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec intelliget Deus Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Intelligite, insipientes in populo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et stulti, aliquando sapite.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Qui plantavit aurem non audiet?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut qui finxit oculum non considerat?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Qui corripit gentes non arguet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui docet hominem scientiam?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Dominus scit cogitationes hominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam van&aelig; sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Beatus homo quem tu erudieris, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de lege tua docueris eum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093013vul">13</span>&nbsp;ut mitiges ei a diebus malis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> donec fodiatur peccatori fovea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Quia non repellet Dominus plebem suam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et h&aelig;reditatem suam non derelinquet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093015vul">15</span>&nbsp;quoadusque justitia convertatur in judicium:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui juxta illam, omnes qui recto sunt corde.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Quis consurget mihi adversus malignantes?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut quis stabit mecum adversus operantes iniquitatem?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Nisi quia Dominus adjuvit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> paulominus habitasset in inferno anima mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Si dicebam: Motus est pes meus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericordia tua, Domine, adjuvabat me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Secundum multitudinem dolorum meorum in corde meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> consolationes tu&aelig; l&aelig;tificaverunt animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Numquid adh&aelig;ret tibi sedes iniquitatis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui fingis laborem in pr&aelig;cepto?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Captabunt in animam justi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sanguinem innocentem condemnabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Et factus est mihi Dominus in refugium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Deus meus in adjutorium spei me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa093023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Et reddet illis iniquitatem ipsorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in malitia eorum disperdet eos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> disperdet illos Dominus Deus noster.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
