<h1>Psalm 94</h1>
<div class="h1a">An invitation to adore and serve God, and to hear his voice.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 95</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa093.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 94</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>Praise of a canticle for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Come let us praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>: let us <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joyfully</a> sing to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> our saviour.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Let us come before his <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> with thanksgiving; and make a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyful<!--</a>--> noise to him with <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalms<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is a great <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and a great <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->King<!--</a>--> above all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For in his hand are all the ends of the earth: and the heights of the mountains are his.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For the sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Come let us <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> and fall down: and weep before the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> that made us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> For he is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a>: and we are the people of his pasture and the sheep of his hand.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Today if you shall hear his voice, harden not your hearts:</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> As in the provocation, according to the day of <a href="../cathen/14504a.htm">temptation</a> in the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>: where your fathers <a href="../cathen/14504a.htm">tempted</a> me, they <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12454c.htm">-->proved<!--</a>--> me, and saw my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Forty years long was I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">-->offended<!--</a>--> with that <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>, and I said: These always <a href="../cathen/05525a.htm">err</a> in heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And these <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> have not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> my ways: so I <a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">swore</a> in my <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> that they shall not enter into my rest.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa094001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Laus cantici ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Venite, exsultemus Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> jubilemus Deo salutari nostro;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094002vul">2</span>&nbsp;pr&aelig;occupemus faciem ejus in confessione,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in psalmis jubilemus ei:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094003vul">3</span>&nbsp;quoniam Deus magnus Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et rex magnus super omnes deos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia in manu ejus sunt omnes fines terr&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et altitudines montium ipsius sunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094005vul">5</span>&nbsp;quoniam ipsius est mare, et ipse fecit illud,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et siccam manus ejus formaverunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Venite, adoremus, et procidamus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ploremus ante Dominum qui fecit nos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094007vul">7</span>&nbsp;quia ipse est Dominus Deus noster,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nos populus pascu&aelig; ejus, et oves manus ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Hodie si vocem ejus audieritis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nolite obdurare corda vestra</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="psa094009vul">9</span>&nbsp;sicut in irritatione,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum diem tentationis in deserto,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ubi tentaverunt me patres vestri:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> probaverunt me, et viderunt opera mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Quadraginta annis offensus fui generationi illi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dixi: Semper hi errant corde.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa094011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Et isti non cognoverunt vias meas:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut juravi in ira mea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Si introibunt in requiem meam.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
