<h1>Psalm 95</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to praise God for the coming of Christ and his kingdom.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 96</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa094.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 95</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself, when the house was built after the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>-->.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> a new <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>-->: sing to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all the earth. <span class="stiki"><strong>When the house was built, etc...</strong> Alluding to that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>-->, and then ordered to be sung: but principally relating to the building of the <a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">church of Christ</a>, after our <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redemption</a> from the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">Satan</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> and <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: show forth his <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> from day to day.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Declare his <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>: his wonders among all people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is great, and exceedingly to be praised: he is to be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->feared<!--</a>--> above all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For all the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> are <a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">devils</a>: but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> made the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Praise and beauty are before him: <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holiness</a> and majesty in his sanctuary.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Bring ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O ye <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05782a.htm">-->kindreds<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>, bring ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> and <a href="../cathen/07462a.htm">honour</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Bring to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> unto his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>. Bring up <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifices</a>, and come into his <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">Adore</a> ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">court</a>. Let all the earth be moved at his <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Say ye among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath reigned. For he hath corrected the world, which shall not be moved: he will <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the people with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Let the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> rejoice, and let the earth be glad, let the sea be moved, and the fulness thereof:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> The fields and all things that are in them shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyful<!--</a>-->. Then shall all the trees of the woods rejoice</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Before the face of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, because he cometh: because he cometh to <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the earth. He shall <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the world with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and the people with his <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa095001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum ipsi David, quando domus &aelig;dificabatur post captivitatem.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Cantate Domino canticum novum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantate Domino omnis terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Cantate Domino, et benedicite nomini ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> annuntiate de die in diem salutare ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Annuntiate inter gentes gloriam ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in omnibus populis mirabilia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quoniam magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> terribilis est super omnes deos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quoniam omnes dii gentium d&aelig;monia;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus autem c&aelig;los fecit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Confessio et pulchritudo in conspectu ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sanctimonia et magnificentia in sanctificatione ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Afferte Domino, patri&aelig; gentium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> afferte Domino gloriam et honorem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095008vul">8</span>&nbsp;afferte Domino gloriam nomini ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Tollite hostias, et introite in atria ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095009vul">9</span>&nbsp;adorate Dominum in atrio sancto ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Commoveatur a facie ejus universa terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095010vul">10</span>&nbsp;dicite in gentibus, quia Dominus regnavit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Etenim correxit orbem terr&aelig;, qui non commovebitur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> judicabit populos in &aelig;quitate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095011vul">11</span>&nbsp;L&aelig;tentur c&aelig;li, et exsultet terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> commoveatur mare et plenitudo ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095012vul">12</span>&nbsp;gaudebunt campi, et omnia qu&aelig; in eis sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Tunc exsultabunt omnia ligna silvarum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa095013vul">13</span>&nbsp;a facie Domini, quia venit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam venit judicare terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Judicabit orbem terr&aelig; in &aelig;quitate,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et populos in veritate sua.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
