<h1>Psalm 96</h1>
<div class="h1a">All are invited to rejoice at the glorious coming and reign of Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 97</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa095.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 96</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For the same <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, when his land was restored again to him.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath reigned, let the earth rejoice: let many islands be glad.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Clouds and darkness are round about him: <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> are the establishment of his throne. <span class="stiki"><strong>Clouds and darkness...</strong> The coming of <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a> in the clouds with great terror and majesty to <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the world, is here <a href="../cathen/12477a.htm">prophesied</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> A fire shall go before him, and shall burn his enemies round about.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> His lightnings have shone forth to the world: the earth saw and trembled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The mountains melted like wax, at the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: at the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of all the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> declared his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: and all people saw his <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Let them be all confounded that <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> graven things, and that <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> in their <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a>. <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">Adore</a> him, all you his <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>--> heard, and was glad. And the daughters of <a href="../cathen/08536a.htm">Juda</a> rejoiced, because of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> For thou art the most high <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> over all the earth: thou art exalted exceedingly above all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> You that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> preserveth the <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a> of his <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>, he will deliver them out of the hand of the sinner.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Light is <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12789a.htm">-->risen<!--</a>--> to the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, and <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> to the right of heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Rejoice, ye <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and give praise to the remembrance of his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holiness</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

