<h1>Psalm 97</h1>
<div class="h1a">All are again invited to praise the Lord, for the victories of Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 98</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa096.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 97</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> a new <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>-->: because he hath done wonderful things. His right hand hath wrought for him <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, and his arm is <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath made <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> his <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: he hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13001a.htm">-->revealed<!--</a>--> his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> in the sight of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> He hath remembered his mercy and his <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> toward the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">house of Israel</a>. All the ends of the earth have seen the <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> of our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Sing <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joyfully</a> to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, all the earth; make melody, rejoice and sing.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Sing praise to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> on the harp, on the harp, and with the voice of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> With long trumpets, and sound of cornet. Make a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyful<!--</a>--> noise before the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> our king:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Let the sea be moved and the fullness thereof: the world and they that dwell therein.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The rivers shall clap their hands, the mountains shall rejoice together</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> at the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: because he cometh to <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the earth. He shall <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> the world with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, and the people with equity.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa097001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Cantate Domino canticum novum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mirabilia fecit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Salvavit sibi dextera ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et brachium sanctum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Notum fecit Dominus salutare suum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in conspectu gentium revelavit justitiam suam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Recordatus est misericordi&aelig; su&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et veritatis su&aelig; domui Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Viderunt omnes termini terr&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salutare Dei nostri.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Jubilate Deo, omnis terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cantate, et exsultate, et psallite.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Psallite Domino in cithara;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in cithara et voce psalmi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097006vul">6</span>&nbsp;in tubis ductilibus, et voce tub&aelig; corne&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Jubilate in conspectu regis Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097007vul">7</span>&nbsp;moveatur mare, et plenitudo ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> orbis terrarum, et qui habitant in eo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa097008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Flumina plaudent manu;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> simul montes exsultabunt</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="psa097009vul">9</span>&nbsp;a conspectu Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam venit judicare terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Judicabit orbem terrarum in justitia,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et populos in &aelig;quitate.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
