<h1>Psalm 98</h1>
<div class="h1a">The reign of the Lord in Zion: that is, of Christ in his Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 99</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa097.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 98</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath reigned, let the people be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a>: he that sitteth on the <a href="../cathen/03646c.htm">cherubims</a>: let the earth be moved. <span class="stiki"><strong>Let the people be angry...</strong> Though many enemies <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">-->rage<!--</a>-->, and the whole earth be stirred up to oppose the <a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">reign of Christ</a>, he shall still prevail.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The lord is great in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, and high above all people.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let them give praise to thy great <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: for it is terrible and <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And the king's <a href="../cathen/07462a.htm">honour</a> <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->. Thou hast prepared directions: thou hast done <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> in <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>Loveth judgment...</strong> Requireth discretion. -- Ibid. <strong>Directions...</strong> Most right and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->laws<!--</a>--> to direct <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Exalt ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a>, and <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> his <a href="../cathen/01721a.htm">footstool</a>, for it is <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>Adore his footstool...</strong> The <a href="../cathen/01721a.htm">ark of the covenant</a> was called, in the <a href="../cathen/14526a.htm">Old Testament</a>, <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God's</a> footstool: over which he was understood to sit, on his propitiatory, or mercy seat, as on a throne, between the wings of the <a href="../cathen/03646c.htm">cherubims</a>, in the sanctuary: to which the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">children of Israel</a> paid a great <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05188b.htm">-->veneration<!--</a>-->. But as this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> evidently relates to <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a>, and the <a href="../cathen/14530a.htm">New Testament</a>, where the <a href="../cathen/01721a.htm">ark</a> has no place, the <a href="../cathen/06001a.htm">holy fathers</a> understand this text, of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">-->worship<!--</a>--> paid by the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->church<!--</a>--> to the <a href="../cathen/05584a.htm">body and blood of Christ</a> in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">-->sacred<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/10662a.htm">mysteries</a>: inasmuch as the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">-->humanity<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/08374c.htm">Christ</a> is, as it were, the footstool of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">-->divinity<!--</a>-->. So <a href="../cathen/01383c.htm">St. Ambrose</a>, L. <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->3<!--</a>-->. De Spiritu Sancto, c. <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->12<!--</a>-->. And <a href="../cathen/02084a.htm">St. Augustine</a> upon this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> and <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a> among his <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priests</a>: and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08647b.htm">-->Samuel<!--</a>--> among them that call upon his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>. They called upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and he heard them: <span class="stiki"><strong>Moses and Aaron among his priests...</strong> By this it is evident, that <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> also was a <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priest</a>, and indeed the chief <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priest</a>, inasmuch as he <a href="../cathen/04276a.htm">consecrated</a> <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a>, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">-->offered<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> for him. <a href="../bible/lev008.htm">Leviticus 8</a>. So that his pre-eminence over <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a> makes nothing for <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08748a.htm">-->lay<!--</a>--> church headship.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He spoke to them in the <a href="../cathen/12099b.htm">pillar of the cloud</a>. They kept his testimonies, and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>--> which he gave them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Thou didst hear them, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a>: thou wast a merciful <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> to them, and taking vengeance on all their inventions. <span class="stiki"><strong>All their inventions...</strong> that is, all the enterprises of their enemies against them, as in the case of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Core, Dathan, and Abiron</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Exalt ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a>, and <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> at his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> mountain: for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord our God</a> is <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa098001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Dominus regnavit: irascantur populi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui sedet super cherubim: moveatur terra.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dominus in Sion magnus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et excelsus super omnes populos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Confiteantur nomini tuo magno,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam terribile et sanctum est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098004vul">4</span>&nbsp;et honor regis judicium diligit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Tu parasti directiones;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> judicium et justitiam in Jacob tu fecisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Exaltate Dominum Deum nostrum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et adorate scabellum pedum ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam sanctum est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Moyses et Aaron in sacerdotibus ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Samuel inter eos qui invocant nomen ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> invocabant Dominum, et ipse exaudiebat eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098007vul">7</span>&nbsp;in columna nubis loquebatur ad eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Custodiebant testimonia ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et pr&aelig;ceptum quod dedit illis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Domine Deus noster, tu exaudiebas eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus, tu propitius fuisti eis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ulciscens in omnes adinventiones eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa098009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Exaltate Dominum Deum nostrum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et adorate in monte sancto ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam sanctus Dominus Deus noster.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
