<h1>Psalm 99</h1>
<div class="h1a">All are invited to rejoice in God the creator of all.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 100</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa098.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 99</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of praise.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Sing <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joyfully</a> to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, all the earth: serve ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">gladness</a>. Come in before his <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> with exceeding great <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">-->Know<!--</a>--> ye that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> he is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: he made us, and not we ourselves. We are his people and the sheep of his pasture.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Go ye into his gates with praise, into his <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> with <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07595a.htm">-->hymns<!--</a>-->: and give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to him. Praise ye his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is sweet, his mercy endureth for ever, and his <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa099001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus in confessione.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa099002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Jubilate Deo, omnis terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> servite Domino in l&aelig;titia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Introite in conspectu ejus in exsultatione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa099003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Scitote quoniam Dominus ipse est Deus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipse fecit nos, et non ipsi nos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> populus ejus, et oves pascu&aelig; ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa099004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Introite portas ejus in confessione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> atria ejus in hymnis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confitemini illi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Laudate nomen ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa099005vul">5</span>&nbsp;quoniam suavis est Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et usque in generationem et generationem veritas ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
