<h1>Psalm 100</h1>
<div class="h1a">The prophet exhorts all by his example, to follow mercy and justice.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 101</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa099.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 100</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Mercy and judgment I will sing to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I will sing,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> And I will understand in the unspotted way, when thou shalt come to me. I walked in the innocence of my heart, in the midst of my house. <span class="stiki"><strong>I will understand, etc...</strong> That is, I will apply my <a href="../cathen/10321a.htm">mind</a>, I will do my endeavour, to <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> and to follow the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfect<!--</a>--> way of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->: not trusting to my own strength, but relying on thy coming to me by thy <a href="../cathen/06689a.htm">grace</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> I will not set before my eyes any <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> thing: I <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>.</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> The perverse heart did not cleave to me: and the malignant, that turned aside from me, I would not <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that in private <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04757a.htm">-->detracted<!--</a>--> his neighbour, him did I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">-->persecute<!--</a>-->. With him that had a <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> eye, and an unsatiable heart, I would not eat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> My eyes were upon the <a href="../cathen/05752c.htm">faithful</a> of the earth, to sit with me: the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that walked in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfect<!--</a>--> way, he served me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He that worketh <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">pride</a> shall not dwell in the midst of my house: he that speaketh <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> things did not prosper before my eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> In the morning I <a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">put to death</a> all the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> of the land: that I might cut off all the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> from the city of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa100001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Misericordiam et judicium cantabo tibi, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100002vul">2</span>&nbsp;et intelligam in via immaculata: quando venies ad me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Perambulabam in innocentia cordis mei, in medio domus me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Non proponebam ante oculos meos rem injustam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facientes pr&aelig;varicationes odivi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non adh&aelig;sit mihi</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="psa100004vul">4</span>&nbsp;cor pravum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> declinantem a me malignum non cognoscebam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Detrahentem secreto proximo suo, hunc persequebar:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> superbo oculo, et insatiabili corde, cum hoc non edebam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Oculi mei ad fideles terr&aelig;, ut sedeant mecum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ambulans in via immaculata, hic mihi ministrabat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Non habitabit in medio domus me&aelig; qui facit superbiam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui loquitur iniqua non direxit in conspectu oculorum meorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa100008vul">8</span>&nbsp;In matutino interficiebam omnes peccatores terr&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut disperderem de civitate Domini omnes operantes iniquitatem.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
