<h1>Psalm 101</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for one in affliction: the fifth penitential psalm.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 102</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa100.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 101</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> The <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>, when he was anxious, and poured out his supplication before the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>: and let my cry come to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Turn not away thy face from me: in the day when I am in trouble, incline thy ear to me. In what day soever I shall call upon thee, hear me speedily.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For my days are vanished like smoke, and my bones are grown dry like fuel for the fire.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I am smitten as grass, and my heart is withered: because I forgot to eat my bread.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Through the voice of my groaning, my bone hath cleaved to my flesh.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I am become like to a pelican of the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>: I am like a night raven in the house. <span class="stiki"><strong>A pelican, etc...</strong> I am become through grief, like birds that affect solitude and darkness.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> I have watched, and am become as a sparrow all alone on the housetop.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> All the day long my enemies reproached me: and they that praised me did <a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">swear</a> against me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For I did eat ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Because of thy <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">anger</a> and indignation: for having lifted me up thou hast thrown me down.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> My days have declined like a shadow, and I am withered like grass.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> But thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, endurest for ever: and thy memorial to all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Thou shalt arise and have mercy on <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: for it is <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> to have mercy on it, for the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> is come.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> For the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14304c.htm">-->stones<!--</a>--> thereof have pleased thy servants: and they shall have pity on the earth thereof.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> All the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> shall <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and all the kings of the earth thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath built up <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: and he shall be seen in his <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> He hath had regard to the <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> of the <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humble</a>: and he hath not <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a> their petition.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Let these things be written unto another <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>: and the people that shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04470a.htm">-->created<!--</a>--> shall praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Because he hath looked forth from his high sanctuary: from <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath looked upon the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> That he might hear the groans of them that are in fetters: that he might release the children of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slain<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> That they may declare the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: and his praise in <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> When the people assemble together, and kings, to serve the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> He answered him in the way of his strength: Declare unto me the fewness of my days. <span class="stiki"><strong>He answered him in the way of his strength...</strong> That is, the people, mentioned in the foregoing <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verse<!--</a>-->, or the penitent, in whose <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11726a.htm">-->person<!--</a>--> this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> is delivered, answered the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in the way of his strength: that is, according to the best of his power and strength: or when he was in the flower of his age and strength: inquiring after the fewness of his days: to <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> if he should live long enough to see the <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">happy</a> restoration of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, etc.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Call me not away in the midst of my days: thy years are unto <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> In the beginning, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou foundedst the earth: and the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> are the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of thy hands.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> They shall perish but thou remainest: and all of them shall grow old like a garment: And as a vesture thou shalt change them, and they shall be changed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> But thou art always the selfsame, and thy years shall not fail.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> The children of thy servants shall continue and their seed shall be directed for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

