<h1>Psalm 102</h1>
<div class="h1a">Thanksgiving to God for his mercies.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 103</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa101.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 102</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: and let all that is within me <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and never forget all he hath done for thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Who forgiveth all thy <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>: who healeth all thy diseases.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Who <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemeth</a> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>--> from destruction: who crowneth thee with mercy and compassion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Who <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/02055a.htm">-->satisfieth<!--</a>--> thy desire with <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things: thy youth shall be renewed like the eagle's.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> doth mercies, and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> for all that suffer wrong.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He hath made his ways <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> to <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a>: his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->wills<!--</a>--> to the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">children of Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is compassionate and merciful: longsuffering and plenteous in mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He will not always be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a>: nor <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> he threaten for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> He hath not dealt with us according to our <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>: nor rewarded us according to our <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For according to the height of the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> above the earth: he hath strengthened his mercy towards them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> As far as the east is from the west, so far hath he removed our <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> from us.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> As a father hath compassion on his children, so hath the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> compassion on them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> For he <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knoweth</a> our frame. He remembereth that we are dust:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">-->Man's<!--</a>--> days are as grass, as the flower of the field so shall he flourish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> For the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> shall pass in him, and he shall not be: and he shall <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> his place no more.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> But the mercy of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is from <a href="../cathen/05551b.htm">eternity</a> and unto <a href="../cathen/05551b.htm">eternity</a> upon them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him: And his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> unto children's children,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> To such as keep his covenant, And are mindful of his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> to do them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> The lord hath prepared his throne in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>: and his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">-->kingdom<!--</a>--> shall rule over all.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all ye his <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a>: you that are mighty in strength, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">-->execute<!--</a>--> his word, hearkening to the voice of his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11279a.htm">-->orders<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all ye his <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>: you <a href="../cathen/10326a.htm">ministers</a> of his that do his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->: in every place of his dominion, O my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thou the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

