<h1>Psalm 105</h1>
<div class="h1a">A confession of the manifold sins and ingratitudes of the Israelites.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 106</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa104.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 105</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Who shall declare the powers of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>? who shall set forth all his praises?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> are they that keep judgment, and do <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> at all times.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Remember us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, in the favour of thy people: visit us with thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> That we may see the <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> of thy chosen, that we may rejoice in the <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> of thy nation: that thou mayst be praised with thy inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> We have <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sinned</a> with our fathers: we have acted <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a>, we have wrought <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Our fathers understood not thy wonders in <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>: they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies: And they provoked to <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> going up to the sea, even the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And he saved them for his own <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake: that he might make his power <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> And he rebuked the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a> and it was dried up: and he led them through the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">depths</a>, as in a <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> And he saved them from the hand of them that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> them: and he <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> them from the hand of the enemy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And the water covered them that afflicted them: there was not one of them left.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And they <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believed</a> his words: and they sang his praises.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> They had quickly done, they forgot his works: and they waited not for his counsel.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And they <a href="../cathen/04462a.htm">coveted</a> their desire in the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">desert</a>: and they <a href="../cathen/14504a.htm">tempted</a> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> in the place without water.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And he gave them their request: and sent fulness into their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">souls</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> And they provoked <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> in the camp, <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a> the <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> one of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The earth opened and swallowed up <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Dathan</a>: and covered the congregation of <a href="../cathen/04361a.htm">Abiron</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> And a fire was kindled in their congregation: the flame burned the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> They made also a <a href="../cathen/06628b.htm">calf</a> in <a href="../cathen/14011a.htm">Horeb</a>: and they <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adored</a> the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07664a.htm">-->graven thing<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> And they changed their <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> into the likeness of a calf that eateth grass.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> They forgot <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who saved them, who had done great things in <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Wondrous works in the land of <a href="../cathen/03566b.htm">Cham</a>: terrible things in the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> And he said that he would destroy them: had not <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> his chosen stood before him in the breach: To turn away his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>, lest he should destroy them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> And they set at nought the desirable land. They <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believed</a> not his word,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> And they murmured in their tents: they hearkened not to the voice of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> And he lifted up his hand over them: to overthrow them in the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">desert</a>;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> And to cast down their seed among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->, and to <a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">scatter</a> them in the countries.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> They also were initiated to <a href="../cathen/02388b.htm">Beelphegor</a>: and ate the <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifices</a> of the dead. <span class="stiki"><strong>Initiated...</strong> That is, they <a href="../cathen/04673a.htm">dedicated</a>, or <a href="../cathen/04276a.htm">consecrated</a> themselves to the <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idol</a> of the <a href="../cathen/10409b.htm">Moabites</a> and <a href="../cathen/09513b.htm">Madianites</a>, called <a href="../cathen/02388b.htm">Beelphegor</a>, or Baal-Peor (<a href="../bible/num025.htm#verse3">Numbers 25:3</a>). -- Ibid. <strong>The dead...</strong> Viz., <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a> without life.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> And they provoked him with their inventions: and destruction was multiplied among them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> Then Phinees stood up, and pacified him: and the slaughter ceased.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> And it was reputed to him unto <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>, to <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> for evermore.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> They provoked him also at the waters of contradiction: and <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a> was afflicted for their sakes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> Because they exasperated his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>-->. And he distinguished with his lips. <span class="stiki"><strong>He distinguished with his lips...</strong> <a href="../cathen/10596a.htm">Moses</a>, by occasion of the people's rebellion and incredulity, was guilty of distinguishing with his lips; when, instead of speaking to the rock, as <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> had commanded, he said to the people, with a certain hesitation in his <a href="../cathen/05752c.htm">faith</a>, Hear ye, rebellious and incredulous: Can we from this rock bring out water for you? (<a href="../bible/num020.htm#verse10">Numbers 20:10</a>)</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> They did not destroy the nations of which the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> spoke unto them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> And they were mingled among the <a href="../cathen/11388a.htm">heathens</a>, and learned their works:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> And served their <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a>, and it became a stumbling block to them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> And they <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrificed</a> their sons, and their daughters to <a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">devils</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> And they <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->shed innocent blood<!--</a>-->: the blood of their sons and of their daughters which they <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrificed</a> to the <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a> of <a href="../cathen/03569b.htm">Chanaan</a>. And the land was polluted with blood,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> And was defiled with their works: and they went aside after their own inventions.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> And the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> was exceedingly <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a> with his people: and he abhorred his inheritance.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse41">41</span> And he delivered them into the hands of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->: and they that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> them had dominion over them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse42">42</span> And their enemies afflicted them: and they were humbled under their hands:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse43">43</span> Many times did he deliver them. But they provoked him with their counsel: and they were brought low by their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse44">44</span> And he saw when they were in tribulation: and he heard their <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse45">45</span> And he was mindful of his covenant: and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse46">46</span> And he gave them unto mercies, in the sight of all those that had made them captives.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse47">47</span> Save us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and gather us from among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->: That we may give thanks to thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, and may <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> in thy praise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse48">48</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say: So be it, so be it.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

