<h1>Psalm 106</h1>
<div class="h1a">All are invited to give thanks to God for his perpetual providence over men.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 107</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa105.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 106</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Let them say so that have been <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> by the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, whom he hath <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> from the hand of the enemy: and gathered out of the countries.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> From the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->rising<!--</a>--> and from the setting of the sun, from the north and from the sea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> They wandered in a <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>, in a place without water: they found not the way of a city for their habitation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They were hungry and thirsty: their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> fainted in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> And they cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in their tribulation: and he delivered them out of their distresses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> And he led them into the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Let the mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to him: and his wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> to the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> For he hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/02055a.htm">-->satisfied<!--</a>--> the empty <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, and hath filled the hungry <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> with <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Such as sat in darkness and in the shadow of death: bound in want and in iron.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Because they had exasperated the words of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: and provoked the counsel of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">most High</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And their heart was <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> with labours: they were weakened, and there was none to help them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Then they cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in their affliction: and he delivered them out of their distresses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And he brought them out of darkness, and the shadow of death; and broke their bonds in sunder.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Let the mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to him, and his wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> to the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Because he hath broken gates of brass, and burst iron bars.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> He took them out of the way of their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: for they were brought low for their <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">injustices</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">-->abhorred<!--</a>--> all manner of meat: and they drew nigh even to the gates of death.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> And they cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in their affliction: and he delivered them out of their distresses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> He sent his word, and healed them: and delivered them from their destructions.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Let the mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to him: and his wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> to the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> And let them <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> the <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of praise: and declare his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> They that go down to the sea in ships, doing business in the great waters:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> These have seen the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and his wonders in the deep.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> He said the word, and there arose a storm of wind: and the waves thereof were lifted up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> They mount up to the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, and they go down to the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">depths</a>: their <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> pined away with <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> They were troubled, and reeled like a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01274a.htm">-->drunken<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>; and all their wisdom was swallowed up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> And they cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in their affliction: and he brought them out of their distresses.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> And he turned the storm into a breeze: and its waves were still.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> And they rejoiced because they were still: and he brought them to the haven which they wished for.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> Let the mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to him, and his wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> to the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> And let them exalt him in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->church<!--</a>--> of the people: and praise him in the chair of the ancients.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> He hath turned rivers into a <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a>: and the sources of waters into dry ground:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> A fruitful land into barrenness, for the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wickedness</a> of them that dwell therein.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> He hath turned a <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">wilderness</a> into <a href="../cathen/12235a.htm">pools</a> of waters, and a dry land into water springs.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> And hath placed there the hungry; and they made a city for their habitation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> Anti they sowed fields, and planted vineyards: and they yielded fruit of birth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> And he <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> them, and they were multiplied exceedingly: and their cattle he suffered not to decrease.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> Then they were brought to be few: and they were afflicted through the trouble of <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evils</a> and sorrow.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">-->Contempt<!--</a>--> was poured forth upon their princes: and he <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03459a.htm">-->caused<!--</a>--> them to wander where there was no passing, and out of the way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse41">41</span> And he helped the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> out of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poverty<!--</a>-->: and made him <a href="../cathen/05782a.htm">families</a> like a flock of sheep.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse42">42</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall see, and shall rejoice, and all <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> shall stop her mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse43">43</span> Who is wise, and will keep these things; and will understand the mercies of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>?</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

