<h1>Psalm 107</h1>
<div class="h1a">The prophet praises God for benefits received.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 108</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa106.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 107</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>--> of a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> My heart is ready, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, my heart is ready: I will sing, and will give praise, with my <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Arise, my <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>; arise, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psaltery<!--</a>--> and harp: I will arise in the morning early.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> I will praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, among the people: and I will sing unto thee among the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For thy mercy is great above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> even unto the clouds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Be thou exalted, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>, and thy <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> over all the earth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> That thy beloved may be delivered. <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->Save<!--</a>--> with thy right hand and hear me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> hath spoken in his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holiness</a>. I will rejoice, and I will divide <a href="../cathen/13771b.htm">Sichem</a> and I will mete out the vale of <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Galaad is mine: and <a href="../cathen/09583c.htm">Manasses</a> is mine and Ephraim the protection of my head. <a href="../cathen/08536a.htm">Juda</a> is my king:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> <a href="../cathen/10409b.htm">Moab</a> the pot of my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>. Over <a href="../cathen/07638a.htm">Edom</a> I will stretch out my shoe: the aliens are become my friends.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Who <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> bring me into the strong city? who <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> lead me into <a href="../cathen/07638a.htm">Edom</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Wilt not thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who hast cast us off? and wilt not thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, go forth with our armies?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> O grant us help from trouble: for vain is the help of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Through <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> we shall do mightily: and he will bring our enemies to nothing.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

