<span class="navb">< <a href="../bible/psa108.htm">BACK</a> | <a href="../bible/psa110.htm">NEXT</a> ></span>
<h1>Psalm 109</h1>
<div class="h1a">Christ's exaltation and everlasting priesthood.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 110</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa108.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 109</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> said to my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: Sit thou at my right hand: Until I make thy enemies thy footstool.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will send forth the sceptre of thy power out of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: rule thou in the midst of thy enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> With thee is the principality in the day of thy strength: in the brightness of the <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>: from the womb before the <a href="../cathen/09410a.htm">day star</a> I begot thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">-->sworn<!--</a>-->, and he will not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11618b.htm">-->repent<!--</a>-->: Thou art a <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priest</a> for ever according to the order of <a href="../cathen/10156b.htm">Melchisedech</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> at thy right hand hath broken kings in the day of his <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He shall <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judge<!--</a>--> among <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->, he shall fill ruins: he shall crush the heads in the land of many.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He shall drink of the torrent in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa109001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Dixit Dominus Domino meo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sede a dextris meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> donec ponam inimicos tuos scabellum pedum tuorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Virgam virtutis tu&aelig; emittet Dominus ex Sion:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dominare in medio inimicorum tuorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Tecum principium in die virtutis tu&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in splendoribus sanctorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex utero, ante luciferum, genui te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Juravit Dominus, et non p&oelig;nitebit eum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Tu es sacerdos in &aelig;ternum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum ordinem Melchisedech.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dominus a dextris tuis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confregit in die ir&aelig; su&aelig; reges.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Judicabit in nationibus, implebit ruinas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> conquassabit capita in terra multorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa109007vul">7</span>&nbsp;De torrente in via bibet;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea exaltabit caput.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
