<div id="springfield">
<span class="navb">< <a href="../bible/psa109.htm">BACK</a> | <a href="../bible/psa111.htm">NEXT</a> ></span>
<h1>Psalm 110</h1>
<div class="h1a">God is to be praised for his graces, and benefits to his Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 111</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa109.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 110</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> I will praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, with my whole heart; in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13444a.htm">-->council<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, and in the congregation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Great are the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: sought out according to all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->wills<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> His work is praise and magnificence: and his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> continueth for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> He hath made a remembrance of his wonderful <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->, being a merciful and gracious <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> He hath given food to them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him. He will be mindful for ever of his covenant:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He will show forth to his people the power of his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> That he may give them the inheritance of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>: the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of his hands are <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> All his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> are <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->faithful<!--</a>-->: <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04215b.htm">-->confirmed<!--</a>--> for ever and ever, made in <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> and equity.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He hath sent <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redemption</a> to his people: he hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commanded<!--</a>--> his covenant for ever. <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">-->Holy<!--</a>--> and terrible is his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The fear of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the beginning of wisdom. A <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> understanding to all that do it: his praise continueth for ever and ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa110001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Confitebor tibi, Domine, in toto corde meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in consilio justorum, et congregatione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Magna opera Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exquisita in omnes voluntates ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Confessio et magnificentia opus ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitia ejus manet in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Memoriam fecit mirabilium suorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericors et miserator Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Escam dedit timentibus se;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> memor erit in s&aelig;culum testamenti sui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Virtutem operum suorum annuntiabit populo suo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110007vul">7</span>&nbsp;ut det illis h&aelig;reditatem gentium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Opera manuum ejus veritas et judicium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Fidelia omnia mandata ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confirmata in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facta in veritate et &aelig;quitate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Redemptionem misit populo suo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mandavit in &aelig;ternum testamentum suum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sanctum et terribile nomen ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa110010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Initium sapienti&aelig; timor Domini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intellectus bonus omnibus facientibus eum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudatio ejus manet in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
