<h1>Psalm 111</h1>
<div class="h1a">The good man is happy.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 112</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa110.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 111</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="preface"></span> <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>, of the returning of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01209d.htm">-->Aggeus<!--</a>--> and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Zacharias<!--</a>-->.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->feareth<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: he shall delight exceedingly in his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> His seed shall be mighty upon earth: the <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> of the righteous shall be <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">Glory</a> and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15571a.htm">-->wealth<!--</a>--> shall be in his house: and his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> remaineth for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> To the righteous a light is <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12789a.htm">-->risen<!--</a>--> up in darkness: he is merciful, and compassionate and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Acceptable is the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> that showeth mercy and lendeth: he shall order his words with <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Because he shall not be moved for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall be in everlasting remembrance: he shall not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> hearing. His heart is ready to <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> His heart is strengthened, he shall not be moved until he look over his enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He hath distributed, he hath given to the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->: his <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> remaineth for ever and ever: his horn shall be exalted in <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> shall see, and shall be <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">angry</a>, he shall gnash with his teeth and pine away: the desire of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> shall perish.
 <span class="stiki"><strong>PREFACE. Of the returning, etc...</strong> This is in the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13722a.htm">-->Greek<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/09019a.htm">Latin</a>, but not in the <a href="../cathen/07175a.htm">Hebrew</a>. It signifies that this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> was proper to be sung at the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> of the return of the people from their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>-->; to inculcate to them, how <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">happy</a> they might be, if they would be constant in the service of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span></span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa111000vul"></span>&nbsp;Alleluja, reversionis Agg&aelig;i et Zachari&aelig;.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa111001vul">1</span>Beatus vir qui timet Dominum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in mandatis ejus volet nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Potens in terra erit semen ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> generatio rectorum benedicetur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Gloria et diviti&aelig; in domo ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitia ejus manet in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Exortum est in tenebris lumen rectis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> misericors, et miserator, et justus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Jucundus homo qui miseretur et commodat;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> disponet sermones suos in judicio:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111006vul">6</span>&nbsp;quia in &aelig;ternum non commovebitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111007vul">7</span>&nbsp;In memoria &aelig;terna erit justus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab auditione mala non timebit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Paratum cor ejus sperare in Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111008vul">8</span>&nbsp;confirmatum est cor ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non commovebitur donec despiciat inimicos suos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Dispersit, dedit pauperibus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justitia ejus manet in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cornu ejus exaltabitur in gloria.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa111010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Peccator videbit, et irascetur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dentibus suis fremet et tabescet:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> desiderium peccatorum peribit.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
