<h1>Psalm 113</h1>
<div class="h1a">God has shown his power in delivering his people: idols are vain. The Hebrews divide this into two psalms.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in many popular Bible translations, this psalm is split into two parts, called <strong>Psalm 114</strong> and <strong>Psalm 115</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> When <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> went out of <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>, the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">house of Jacob</a> from a barbarous people:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> <a href="../cathen/08544a.htm">Judea</a> was made his sanctuary, <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> his dominion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> The sea saw and fled: <a href="../cathen/08501a.htm">Jordan</a> was turned back.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> The mountains skipped like rams, and the hills like the lambs of the flock.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> What ailed thee, O thou sea, that thou didst flee: and thou, O <a href="../cathen/08501a.htm">Jordan</a>, that thou wast turned back?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Ye mountains, that ye skipped like rams, and ye hills, like lambs of the flock?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> At the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> the earth was moved, at the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->presence<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Who turned the rock into <a href="../cathen/12235a.htm">pools</a> of water, and the stony hill into fountains of waters.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Not to us, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, not to us; but to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For thy mercy, and for thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth's</a> sake: lest the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> should say: Where is their <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> But our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>: he hath done all things whatsoever he would.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> The <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> are silver and gold, the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of the hands of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> They have mouths and speak not: they have eyes and see not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> They have ears and hear not: they have noses and smell not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> They have hands and feel not: they have feet and walk not: neither shall they cry out through their throat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Let them that make them become like unto them: and all such as trust in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">house of Israel</a> hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: he is their helper and their protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The house of <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a> hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: he is their helper and their protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> They that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: he is their helper and their protector.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath been mindful of us, and hath <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> us. He hath <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">house of Israel</a>: he hath <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> the house of <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> He hath <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> all that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, both little and great.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> May the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> add <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessings</a> upon you: upon you, and upon your children.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be you of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who made <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> The <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> of <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord's</a>: but the earth he has given to the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> The dead shall not praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: nor any of them that go down to hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> But we that live <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: from this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>--> now and for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa113001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">In exitu Isra&euml;l de &AElig;gypto,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> domus Jacob de populo barbaro,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113002vul">2</span>&nbsp;facta est Jud&aelig;a sanctificatio ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Isra&euml;l potestas ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Mare vidit, et fugit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Jordanis conversus est retrorsum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Montes exsultaverunt ut arietes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et colles sicut agni ovium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quid est tibi, mare, quod fugisti?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tu, Jordanis, quia conversus es retrorsum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113006vul">6</span>&nbsp;montes, exsultastis sicut arietes?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et colles, sicut agni ovium?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113007vul">7</span>&nbsp;A facie Domini mota est terra,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a facie Dei Jacob:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113008vul">8</span>&nbsp;qui convertit petram in stagna aquarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et rupem in fontes aquarum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Non nobis, Domine, non nobis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sed nomini tuo da gloriam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113010vul">10</span>&nbsp;super misericordia tua et veritate tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nequando dicant gentes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Ubi est Deus eorum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Deus autem noster in c&aelig;lo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnia qu&aelig;cumque voluit fecit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Simulacra gentium argentum et aurum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> opera manuum hominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Os habent, et non loquentur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oculos habent, et non videbunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Aures habent, et non audient;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nares habent, et non odorabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Manus habent, et non palpabunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pedes habent, et non ambulabunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non clamabunt in gutture suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Similes illis fiant qui faciunt ea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes qui confidunt in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Domus Isra&euml;l speravit in Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adjutor eorum et protector eorum est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Domus Aaron speravit in Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adjutor eorum et protector eorum est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Qui timent Dominum speraverunt in Domino; adjutor eorum et protector eorum est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Dominus memor fuit nostri,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et benedixit nobis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Benedixit domui Isra&euml;l;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> benedixit domui Aaron.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Benedixit omnibus qui timent Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pusillis cum majoribus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Adjiciat Dominus super vos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super vos et super filios vestros.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Benedicti vos a Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui fecit c&aelig;lum et terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113024vul">24</span>&nbsp;C&aelig;lum c&aelig;li Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> terram autem dedit filiis hominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Non mortui laudabunt te, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque omnes qui descendunt in infernum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa113026vul">26</span>&nbsp;sed nos qui vivimus, benedicimus Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex hoc nunc et usque in s&aelig;culum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
