<h1>Psalm 115</h1>
<div class="h1a">This in the Hebrew is joined with the foregoing psalm, and continues to express the faith and gratitude of the psalmist.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in many popular Bible translations, the psalm below is combined with the <strong><a href="../bible/psa114.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> to form <strong>Psalm 116</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="other"></span> <em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> I have <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believed</a>, therefore have I spoken; but I have been <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> I said in my excess: Every <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> is a <a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">liar</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> What shall I render to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for all the things that he hath rendered to me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> I will take the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03561a.htm">-->chalice<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>; and I will call upon the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> I will pay my <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vows</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> before all his people:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> Precious in the sight of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is the death of his <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for I am thy servant: I am thy servant, and the son of thy handmaid. Thou hast broken my bonds:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> I will <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> to thee the <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a> of praise, and I will call upon the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> I will pay my <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vows</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in the sight of all his people:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> In the <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a>, in the midst of thee, O <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa115001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Credidi, propter quod locutus sum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem humiliatus sum nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Ego dixi in excessu meo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Omnis homo mendax.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Quid retribuam Domino</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pro omnibus qu&aelig; retribuit mihi?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Calicem salutaris accipiam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nomen Domini invocabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Vota mea Domino reddam</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> coram omni populo ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Pretiosa in conspectu Domini</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mors sanctorum ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115007vul">7</span>&nbsp;O Domine, quia ego servus tuus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego servus tuus, et filius ancill&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dirupisti vincula mea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115008vul">8</span>&nbsp;tibi sacrificabo hostiam laudis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nomen Domini invocabo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Vota mea Domino reddam</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in conspectu omnis populi ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa115010vul">10</span>&nbsp;in atriis domus Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in medio tui, Jerusalem.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
