<div id="springfield">
<span class="navb">< <a href="../bible/psa116.htm">BACK</a> | <a href="../bible/psa118.htm">NEXT</a> ></span>
<h1>Psalm 117</h1>
<div class="h1a">The psalmist praises God for his delivery from evils: puts his whole trust in him; and foretells the coming of Christ.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 118</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa116.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 117</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Give praise to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Let <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> now say, that he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: that his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let the house of <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a> now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Let them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> In my trouble I called upon the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> heard me, and enlarged me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my helper: I will not <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> what <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> can do unto me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my helper: and I will look over my enemies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> It is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> to confide in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, rather than to have confidence in <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> It is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> to trust in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, rather than to trust in princes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> All <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>--> compassed me about; and, in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> I have been revenged on them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Surrounding me they compassed me about: and in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> I have been revenged on them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> They surrounded me like bees, and they burned like fire among thorns: and in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> I was revenged on them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Being pushed I was overturned that I might fall: but the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> supported me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is my strength and my praise: and he is become my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> The voice of rejoicing and of <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> is in the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->tabernacles<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> The right hand of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath wrought strength: the right hand of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath exalted me: the right hand of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath wrought strength.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> I shall not die, but live: and shall declare the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> chastising hath chastised me: but he hath not delivered me over to death.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Open ye to me the gates of <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: I will go in to them, and give praise to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> This is the gate of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> shall enter into it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> I will give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to thee because thou hast heard me: and art become my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> The stone which the builders rejected; the same is become the <a href="../cathen/14303a.htm">head of the corner</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> This is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord's</a> doing, and it is wonderful in our eyes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> This is the day which the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath made: let us be glad and rejoice therein.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> me: O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, give <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> success.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be he that cometh in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. We have <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> you out of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and he hath shone upon us. Appoint a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14133a.htm">-->solemn<!--</a>--> day, with shady boughs, even to the <a href="../cathen/01354a.htm">horn of the altar</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> Thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and I will praise thee: thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and I will exalt thee. I will praise thee, because thou hast heard me, and art become my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> O praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa117001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Confitemini Domino, quoniam bonus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in s&aelig;culum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dicat nunc Isra&euml;l: Quoniam bonus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in s&aelig;culum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Dicat nunc domus Aaron:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam in s&aelig;culum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Dicant nunc qui timent Dominum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam in s&aelig;culum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117005vul">5</span>&nbsp;De tribulatione invocavi Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaudivit me in latitudine Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Dominus mihi adjutor;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non timebo quid faciat mihi homo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Dominus mihi adjutor,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ego despiciam inimicos meos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Bonum est confidere in Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quam confidere in homine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Bonum est sperare in Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quam sperare in principibus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Omnes gentes circuierunt me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine Domini, quia ultus sum in eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Circumdantes circumdederunt me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine Domini, quia ultus sum in eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Circumdederunt me sicut apes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exarserunt sicut ignis in spinis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in nomine Domini, quia ultus sum in eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Impulsus eversus sum, ut caderem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus suscepit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Fortitudo mea et laus mea Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factus est mihi in salutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Vox exsultationis et salutis</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in tabernaculis justorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Dextera Domini fecit virtutem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dextera Domini exaltavit me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dextera Domini fecit virtutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Non moriar, sed vivam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et narrabo opera Domini.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Castigans castigavit me Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et morti non tradidit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Aperite mihi portas justiti&aelig;:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ingressus in eas confitebor Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117020vul">20</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c porta Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justi intrabunt in eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Confitebor tibi quoniam exaudisti me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factus es mihi in salutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Lapidem quem reprobaverunt &aelig;dificantes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> hic factus est in caput anguli.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117023vul">23</span>&nbsp;A Domino factum est istud,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et est mirabile in oculis nostris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117024vul">24</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c est dies quam fecit Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exsultemus, et l&aelig;temur in ea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117025vul">25</span>&nbsp;O Domine, salvum me fac;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> o Domine, bene prosperare.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Benedictus qui venit in nomine Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> benediximus vobis de domo Domini.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Deus Dominus, et illuxit nobis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Constituite diem solemnem in condensis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> usque ad cornu altaris.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Deus meus es tu, et confitebor tibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus meus es tu, et exaltabo te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Confitebor tibi quoniam exaudisti me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et factus es mihi in salutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa117029vul">29</span>&nbsp;Confitemini Domino, quoniam bonus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in s&aelig;culum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
