<h1>Psalm 118</h1>
<div class="h1a">Of the excellence of virtue consisting in the love and observance of the commandments of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 119</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa117.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 118</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<p align=center><strong>ALEPH</strong></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> are the undefiled in the way, who walk in the <a href="../cathen/14779c.htm">law</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. <span class="stiki"><strong>Aleph...</strong> The first eight <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verses<!--</a>--> of this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> in the original begin with Aleph, which is the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the first <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05509a.htm">-->letter<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a> alphabet. The second eight <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verses<!--</a>--> begin with Beth, the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the second <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05509a.htm">-->letter<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a> alphabet; and so to the end of the whole alphabet, in all twenty-two <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05509a.htm">-->letters<!--</a>-->, each <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05509a.htm">-->letter<!--</a>--> having eight <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verses<!--</a>-->. This order is variously expounded by the <a href="../cathen/06001a.htm">holy fathers</a>; which shows the difficulty of understanding the <a href="../cathen/13635b.htm">holy scriptures</a>, and consequently with what <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humility</a>, and submission to the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03744a.htm">-->Church<!--</a>--> they are to be read.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> are they that search his testimonies: that seek him with their whole heart. <span class="stiki"><strong>His testimonies...</strong> The <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> are called his testimonies, because they testify his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> unto us. Note here, that in almost every <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->verse<!--</a>--> of this <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> (which in <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11151a.htm">-->number<!--</a>--> are <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->176<!--</a>-->) the word and <a href="../cathen/14779c.htm">law</a> of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and the <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> and observance of it, is perpetually inculcated, under a variety of denominations, all signifying the same thing.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For they that work <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>, have not walked in his ways.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commanded<!--</a>--> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> to be kept most diligently.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> O! that my ways may be directed to keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Then shall I not be confounded, when I shall look into all thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I will praise thee with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> I will keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->: O! do not thou utterly forsake me.
<p align=center><strong>BETH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> By what doth a young <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">-->man<!--</a>--> correct his way? by observing thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> With my whole heart have I sought after thee: let me not stray from thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Thy words have I hidden in my heart, that I may not <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sin</a> against thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> art thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> With my lips I have pronounced all the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> I have been delighted in the way of thy testimonies, as in all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15571a.htm">-->riches<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> I will <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditate<!--</a>--> on thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->: and I will consider thy ways.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I will think of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->: I will not forget thy words.
<p align=center><strong>GIMEL</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Give bountifully to thy servant, enliven me: and I shall keep thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Open thou my eyes: and I will consider the wondrous things of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> I am a sojourner on the earth: hide not thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> from me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath <a href="../cathen/04462a.htm">coveted</a> to long for thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->, at all times.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Thou hast rebuked the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a>: they are <a href="../cathen/09569a.htm">cursed</a> who decline from thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> Remove from me reproach and <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">contempt</a>: because I have sought after thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> For princes sat, and spoke against me: but thy servant was employed in thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> For thy testimonies are my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->: and thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>--> my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04435a.htm">-->counsel<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>DALETH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath cleaved to the pavement: quicken thou me according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> I have declared my ways, and thou hast heard me: teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> Make me to understand the way of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->: and I shall be exercised in thy wondrous <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse28">28</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath slumbered through heaviness: strengthen thou me in thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse29">29</span> Remove from me the way of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and out of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> have mercy on me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse30">30</span> I have chosen the way of <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> I have not forgotten.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse31">31</span> I have stuck to thy testimonies, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: put me not to shame.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse32">32</span> I have run the way of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->, when thou didst enlarge my heart.
<p align=center><strong>HE</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse33">33</span> Set before me for a <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> the way of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and I will always seek after it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse34">34</span> Give me understanding, and I will search thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->; and I will keep it with my whole heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse35">35</span> Lead me into the path of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->; for this same I have desired.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse36">36</span> Incline my heart into thy testimonies and not to <a href="../cathen/04462a.htm">covetousness</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse37">37</span> Turn away my eyes that they may not behold vanity: quicken me in thy way.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse38">38</span> Establish thy word to thy servant, in thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse39">39</span> Turn away my reproach, which I have apprehended: for thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> are delightful.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse40">40</span> Behold I have longed after thy <a href="../cathen/12372b.htm">precepts</a>: quicken me in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.
<p align=center><strong>VAU</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse41">41</span> Let thy mercy also come upon me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse42">42</span> So shall I answer them that reproach me in any thing; that I have trusted in thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse43">43</span> And take not thou the word of <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> utterly out of my mouth: for in thy words, I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse44">44</span> So shall I always keep thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->, for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse45">45</span> And I walked at large: because I have sought after thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse46">46</span> And I spoke of thy testimonies before kings: and I was not ashamed.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse47">47</span> I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditated<!--</a>--> also on thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->, which I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse48">48</span> And I lifted up my hands to thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->, which I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a>: and I was exercised in thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>ZAIN</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse49">49</span> Be thou mindful of thy word to thy servant, in which thou hast given me <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse50">50</span> This hath comforted me in my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">-->humiliation<!--</a>-->: because thy word hath enlivened me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse51">51</span> The <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> did iniquitously altogether: but I declined not from thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse52">52</span> I remembered, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of old: and I was comforted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse53">53</span> A fainting hath taken hold of me, because of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> that forsake thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse54">54</span> Thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>--> were the subject of my song, in the place of my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12085a.htm">-->pilgrimage<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse55">55</span> In the night I have remembered thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and have kept thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse56">56</span> This happened to me: because I sought after thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>HETH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse57">57</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my portion, I have said, I would keep thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse58">58</span> I entreated thy face with all my heart: have mercy on me according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse59">59</span> I have thought on my ways: and turned my feet unto thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse60">60</span> I am ready, and am not troubled: that I may keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse61">61</span> The cords of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> have encompassed me: but I have not forgotten thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse62">62</span> I rose at midnight to give praise to thee; for the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justification<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse63">63</span> I am a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->partaker<!--</a>--> with all them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> thee, and that keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse64">64</span> The earth, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, is full of thy mercy: teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>TETH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse65">65</span> Thou hast done well with thy servant, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse66">66</span> Teach me <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">goodness</a> and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/05030a.htm">-->discipline<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knowledge</a>; for I have <a href="../cathen/02408b.htm">believed</a> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse67">67</span> Before I was <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">-->offended<!--</a>-->; therefore have I kept thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse68">68</span> Thou art <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>; and in thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">goodness</a> teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse69">69</span> The <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> of the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> hath been multiplied over me: but I will seek thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> with my whole heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse70">70</span> Their heart is curdled like milk: but I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditated<!--</a>--> on thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse71">71</span> It is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> for me that thou hast <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> me, that I may learn thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse72">72</span> The <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> of thy mouth is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> to me, above thousands of gold and silver.
<p align=center><strong>JOD</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse73">73</span> Thy hands have made me and formed me: give me understanding, and I will learn thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse74">74</span> They that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> thee shall see me, and shall be glad: because I have greatly <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse75">75</span> I <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, that thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> are equity: and in thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> thou hast <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse76">76</span> O! let thy mercy be for my comfort, according to thy word unto thy servant.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse77">77</span> Let thy tender mercies come unto me, and I shall live: for thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> is my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse78">78</span> Let the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> be ashamed, because they have done <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a> towards me: but I will be employed in thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse79">79</span> Let them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> thee turn to me: and they that <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse80">80</span> Let my heart be undefiled in thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->, that I may not be confounded.
<p align=center><strong>CAPH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse81">81</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath fainted after thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: and in thy word I have very much <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse82">82</span> My eyes have failed for thy word, saying: When wilt thou comfort me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse83">83</span> For I am become like a bottle in the frost: I have not forgotten thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse84">84</span> How many are the days of thy servant: when wilt thou <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">-->execute<!--</a>--> judgment on them that persecute me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse85">85</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> have told me fables: but not as thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse86">86</span> All thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->statutes<!--</a>--> are <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: they have <a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">persecuted</a> me <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjustly</a>, do thou help me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse87">87</span> They had almost made an end of me upon earth: but I have not forsaken thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse88">88</span> Quicken thou me according to thy mercy: and I shall keep the testimonies of thy mouth.
<p align=center><strong>LAMED</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse89">89</span> For ever, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thy word standeth firm in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse90">90</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> unto all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>: thou hast founded the earth, and it continueth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse91">91</span> By thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09053a.htm">-->ordinance<!--</a>--> the day goeth on: for all things serve thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse92">92</span> Unless thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> had been my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->, I had then perhaps perished in my abjection.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse93">93</span> Thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>--> I will never forget: for by them thou hast given me <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse94">94</span> I am thine, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> thou me: for I have sought thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse95">95</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> have waited for me to destroy me: but I have understood thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse96">96</span> I have seen an end of all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfection<!--</a>-->: thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>--> is exceeding broad.
<p align=center><strong>MEM</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse97">97</span> O how have I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>! it is my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>--> all the day.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse98">98</span> Through thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandment<!--</a>-->, thou hast made me wiser than my enemies: for it is ever with me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse99">99</span> I have understood more than all my teachers: because thy testimonies are my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse100">100</span> I have had understanding above ancients: because I have sought thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse101">101</span> I have restrained my feet from every <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> way: that I may keep thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse102">102</span> I have not declined from thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->, because thou hast set me a <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse103">103</span> How sweet are thy words to my palate! more than honey to my mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse104">104</span> By thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> I have had understanding: therefore have I <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> every way of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.
<p align=center><strong>NUN</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse105">105</span> Thy word is a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08770a.htm">-->lamp<!--</a>--> to my feet, and a light to my paths.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse106">106</span> I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">-->sworn<!--</a>--> and am determined to keep the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse107">107</span> I have been <a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">humbled</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, exceedingly: quicken thou me according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse108">108</span> The free <a href="../cathen/11215d.htm">offerings</a> of my mouth make acceptable, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and teach me thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse109">109</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is continually in my hands: and I have not forgotten thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse110">110</span> Sinners have laid a snare for me: but I have not <a href="../cathen/05525a.htm">erred</a> from thy <a href="../cathen/12372b.htm">precepts</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse111">111</span> I have purchased thy testimonies for an inheritance for ever: because they are the <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a> of my heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse112">112</span> I have inclined my heart to do thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>--> for ever, for the reward.
<p align=center><strong>SAMECH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse113">113</span> I have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> the <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a>: and have <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse114">114</span> Thou art my helper and my protector: and in thy word I have greatly <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse115">115</span> Depart from me, ye malignant: and I will search the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> of my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse116">116</span> Uphold me according to thy word, and I shall live: and let me not be confounded in my expectation.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse117">117</span> Help me, and I shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->saved<!--</a>-->: and I will <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditate<!--</a>--> always on thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse118">118</span> Thou hast <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a> all them that fall off from thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->; for their thought is <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse119">119</span> I have accounted all the sinners of the earth prevaricators: therefore have I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse120">120</span> Pierce thou my flesh with thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>-->: for I am <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->afraid<!--</a>--> of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>AIN</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse121">121</span> I have done <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: give me not up to them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14035b.htm">-->slander<!--</a>--> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse122">122</span> Uphold thy servant unto <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: let not the <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> <a href="../cathen/03190c.htm">calumniate</a> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse123">123</span> My eyes have fainted after thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: and for the word of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse124">124</span> Deal with thy servant according to thy mercy: and teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse125">125</span> I am thy servant: give me understanding that I may <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse126">126</span> It is <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14726a.htm">-->time<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to do: they have dissipated thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse127">127</span> Therefore have I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> above gold and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14304c.htm">-->topaz<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse128">128</span> Therefore was I directed to all thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->: I have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> all <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> ways.
<p align=center><strong>PHE</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse129">129</span> Thy testimonies are wonderful: therefore my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath sought them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse130">130</span> The declaration of thy words giveth light: and giveth understanding to little ones.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse131">131</span> I opened my mouth, and panted: because I longed for thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse132">132</span> Look thou upon me, and have mercy on me according to the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> of them that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse133">133</span> Direct my steps according to thy word: and let no <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a> have dominion over me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse134">134</span> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Redeem<!--</a>--> me from the <a href="../cathen/03190c.htm">calumnies</a> of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>: that I may keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse135">135</span> Make thy face to shine upon thy servant: and teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse136">136</span> My eyes have sent forth springs of water: because they have not kept thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.
<p align=center><strong>SADE</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse137">137</span> Thou art <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> is right.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse138">138</span> Thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commanded<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> thy testimonies: and thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse139">139</span> My <a href="../cathen/15753a.htm">zeal</a> hath made me pine away: because my enemies forgot thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse140">140</span> Thy word is exceedingly refined: and thy servant hath <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse141">141</span> I am very young and <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a>; but I forget not thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse142">142</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> is <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> for ever: and thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> is the <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse143">143</span> Trouble and anguish have found me: thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> are my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse144">144</span> Thy testimonies are <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> for ever: give me understanding, and I shall live.
<p align=center><strong>COPH</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse145">145</span> I cried with my whole heart, hear me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I will seek thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse146">146</span> I cried unto thee, <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> me: that I may keep thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse147">147</span> I prevented the dawning of the day, and cried: because in thy words I very much <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse148">148</span> My eyes to thee have prevented the morning: that I might <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditate<!--</a>--> on thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse149">149</span> Hear thou my voice, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, according to thy mercy: and quicken me according to thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse150">150</span> They that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">-->persecute<!--</a>--> me have drawn nigh to <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>; but they are gone far off from thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse151">151</span> Thou art near, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and all thy ways are <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse152">152</span> I have <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> from the beginning concerning thy testimonies: that thou hast founded them for ever.
<p align=center><strong>RES</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse153">153</span> See my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">-->humiliation<!--</a>--> and deliver me for I have not forgotten thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse154">154</span> <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Judge<!--</a>--> my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> me: quicken thou me for thy word's sake.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse155">155</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->Salvation<!--</a>--> is far from sinners; because they have not sought thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse156">156</span> Many, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, are thy mercies: quicken me according to thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse157">157</span> Many are they that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">-->persecute<!--</a>--> me and afflict me; but I have not declined from thy testimonies.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse158">158</span> I beheld the transgressors, and pined away; because they kept not thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse159">159</span> Behold I have <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; quicken me thou in thy mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse160">160</span> The beginning of thy words is <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: all the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> are for ever.
<p align=center><strong>SIN</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse161">161</span> Princes have <a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">persecuted</a> me without cause: and my heart hath been in awe of thy words.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse162">162</span> I will rejoice at thy words, as one that hath found great spoil.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse163">163</span> I have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">-->abhorred<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>; but I have <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse164">164</span> Seven times a day I have given praise to thee, for the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> of thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse165">165</span> Much peace have they that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->, and to them there is no stumbling block.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse166">166</span> I looked for thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and I <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse167">167</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath kept thy testimonies and hath <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loved</a> them exceedingly.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse168">168</span> I have kept thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> and thy testimonies: because all my ways are in thy sight.
<p align=center><strong>TAU</strong></p></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse169">169</span> Let my supplication, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, come near in thy sight: give me understanding according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse170">170</span> Let my request come in before thee; deliver thou me according to thy word.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse171">171</span> My lips shall utter a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07595a.htm">-->hymn<!--</a>-->, when thou shalt teach me thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justifications<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse172">172</span> My <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> shall pronounce thy word: because all thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>--> are <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse173">173</span> Let thy hand be with me to <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> me; for I have chosen thy <a href="../cathen/12372b.htm">precepts</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse174">174</span> I have longed for thy <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>; and thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>--> is my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditation<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse175">175</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> shall live and shall praise thee: and thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgments<!--</a>--> shall help me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse176">176</span> I have gone astray like a sheep that is lost: seek thy servant, because I have not forgotten thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa118001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="speaker">Aleph.</span> Beati immaculati in via,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui ambulant in lege Domini.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Beati qui scrutantur testimonia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in toto corde exquirunt eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Non enim qui operantur iniquitatem</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in viis ejus ambulaverunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Tu mandasti mandata tua</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> custodiri nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Utinam dirigantur vi&aelig; me&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad custodiendas justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Tunc non confundar,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum perspexero in omnibus mandatis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Confitebor tibi in directione cordis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in eo quod didici judicia justiti&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Justificationes tuas custodiam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non me derelinquas usquequaque.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118009vul">9</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Beth.</span> In quo corrigit adolescentior viam suam?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in custodiendo sermones tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118010vul">10</span>&nbsp;In toto corde meo exquisivi te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne repellas me a mandatis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118011vul">11</span>&nbsp;In corde meo abscondi eloquia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut non peccem tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Benedictus es, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> doce me justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118013vul">13</span>&nbsp;In labiis meis pronuntiavi omnia judicia oris tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118014vul">14</span>&nbsp;In via testimoniorum tuorum delectatus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut in omnibus divitiis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118015vul">15</span>&nbsp;In mandatis tuis exercebor,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et considerabo vias tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118016vul">16</span>&nbsp;In justificationibus tuis meditabor:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non obliviscar sermones tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118017vul">17</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Ghimel.</span> Retribue servo tuo, vivifica me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et custodiam sermones tuos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Revela oculos meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et considerabo mirabilia de lege tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Incola ego sum in terra:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non abscondas a me mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Concupivit anima mea</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> desiderare justificationes tuas in omni tempore.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Increpasti superbos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> maledicti qui declinant a mandatis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118022vul">22</span>&nbsp;Aufer a me opprobrium et contemptum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia testimonia tua exquisivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Etenim sederunt principes, et adversum me loquebantur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> servus autem tuus exercebatur in justificationibus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118024vul">24</span>&nbsp;Nam et testimonia tua meditatio mea est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et consilium meum justificationes tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118025vul">25</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Daleth.</span> Adh&aelig;sit pavimento anima mea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> vivifica me secundum verbum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Vias meas enuntiavi, et exaudisti me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> doce me justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118027vul">27</span>&nbsp;Viam justificationum tuarum instrue me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exercebor in mirabilibus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118028vul">28</span>&nbsp;Dormitavit anima mea pr&aelig; t&aelig;dio:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> confirma me in verbis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118029vul">29</span>&nbsp;Viam iniquitatis amove a me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de lege tua miserere mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118030vul">30</span>&nbsp;Viam veritatis elegi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> judicia tua non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118031vul">31</span>&nbsp;Adh&aelig;si testimoniis tuis, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> noli me confundere.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118032vul">32</span>&nbsp;Viam mandatorum tuorum cucurri,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum dilatasti cor meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118033vul">33</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">He.</span> Legem pone mihi, Domine, viam justificationum tuarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exquiram eam semper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118034vul">34</span>&nbsp;Da mihi intellectum, et scrutabor legem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et custodiam illam in toto corde meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118035vul">35</span>&nbsp;Deduc me in semitam mandatorum tuorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia ipsam volui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118036vul">36</span>&nbsp;Inclina cor meum in testimonia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non in avaritiam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118037vul">37</span>&nbsp;Averte oculos meos, ne videant vanitatem;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in via tua vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118038vul">38</span>&nbsp;Statue servo tuo eloquium tuum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in timore tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118039vul">39</span>&nbsp;Amputa opprobrium meum quod suspicatus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia judicia tua jucunda.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118040vul">40</span>&nbsp;Ecce concupivi mandata tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in &aelig;quitate tua vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118041vul">41</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Vau.</span> Et veniat super me misericordia tua, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> salutare tuum secundum eloquium tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118042vul">42</span>&nbsp;Et respondebo exprobrantibus mihi verbum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia speravi in sermonibus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118043vul">43</span>&nbsp;Et ne auferas de ore meo verbum veritatis usquequaque,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in judiciis tuis supersperavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118044vul">44</span>&nbsp;Et custodiam legem tuam semper,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in s&aelig;culum et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118045vul">45</span>&nbsp;Et ambulabam in latitudine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mandata tua exquisivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118046vul">46</span>&nbsp;Et loquebar in testimoniis tuis in conspectu regum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non confundebar.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118047vul">47</span>&nbsp;Et meditabar in mandatis tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; dilexi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118048vul">48</span>&nbsp;Et levavi manus meas ad mandata tua, qu&aelig; dilexi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exercebar in justificationibus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118049vul">49</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Zain.</span> Memor esto verbi tui servo tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in quo mihi spem dedisti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118050vul">50</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c me consolata est in humilitate mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia eloquium tuum vivificavit me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118051vul">51</span>&nbsp;Superbi inique agebant usquequaque;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a lege autem tua non declinavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118052vul">52</span>&nbsp;Memor fui judiciorum tuorum a s&aelig;culo, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et consolatus sum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118053vul">53</span>&nbsp;Defectio tenuit me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pro peccatoribus derelinquentibus legem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118054vul">54</span>&nbsp;Cantabiles mihi erant justificationes tu&aelig;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in loco peregrinationis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118055vul">55</span>&nbsp;Memor fui nocte nominis tui, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et custodivi legem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118056vul">56</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c facta est mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia justificationes tuas exquisivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118057vul">57</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Heth.</span> Portio mea, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dixi custodire legem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118058vul">58</span>&nbsp;Deprecatus sum faciem tuam in toto corde meo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> miserere mei secundum eloquium tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118059vul">59</span>&nbsp;Cogitavi vias meas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et converti pedes meos in testimonia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118060vul">60</span>&nbsp;Paratus sum, et non sum turbatus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut custodiam mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118061vul">61</span>&nbsp;Funes peccatorum circumplexi sunt me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et legem tuam non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118062vul">62</span>&nbsp;Media nocte surgebam ad confitendum tibi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super judicia justificationis tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118063vul">63</span>&nbsp;Particeps ego sum omnium timentium te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et custodientium mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118064vul">64</span>&nbsp;Misericordia tua, Domine, plena est terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justificationes tuas doce me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118065vul">65</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Teth.</span> Bonitatem fecisti cum servo tuo, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum verbum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118066vul">66</span>&nbsp;Bonitatem, et disciplinam, et scientiam doce me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mandatis tuis credidi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118067vul">67</span>&nbsp;Priusquam humiliarer ego deliqui:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea eloquium tuum custodivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118068vul">68</span>&nbsp;Bonus es tu, et in bonitate tua</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> doce me justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118069vul">69</span>&nbsp;Multiplicata est super me iniquitas superborum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem in toto corde meo scrutabor mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118070vul">70</span>&nbsp;Coagulatum est sicut lac cor eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego vero legem tuam meditatus sum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118071vul">71</span>&nbsp;Bonum mihi quia humiliasti me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut discam justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118072vul">72</span>&nbsp;Bonum mihi lex oris tui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super millia auri et argenti.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118073vul">73</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Jod.</span> Manus tu&aelig; fecerunt me, et plasmaverunt me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> da mihi intellectum, et discam mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118074vul">74</span>&nbsp;Qui timent te videbunt me et l&aelig;tabuntur,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in verba tua supersperavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118075vul">75</span>&nbsp;Cognovi, Domine, quia &aelig;quitas judicia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in veritate tua humiliasti me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118076vul">76</span>&nbsp;Fiat misericordia tua ut consoletur me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum eloquium tuum servo tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118077vul">77</span>&nbsp;Veniant mihi miserationes tu&aelig;, et vivam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia lex tua meditatio mea est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118078vul">78</span>&nbsp;Confundantur superbi, quia injuste iniquitatem fecerunt in me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem exercebor in mandatis tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118079vul">79</span>&nbsp;Convertantur mihi timentes te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et qui noverunt testimonia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118080vul">80</span>&nbsp;Fiat cor meum immaculatum in justificationibus tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut non confundar.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118081vul">81</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Caph.</span> Defecit in salutare tuum anima mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in verbum tuum supersperavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118082vul">82</span>&nbsp;Defecerunt oculi mei in eloquium tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dicentes: Quando consolaberis me?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118083vul">83</span>&nbsp;Quia factus sum sicut uter in pruina;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justificationes tuas non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118084vul">84</span>&nbsp;Quot sunt dies servi tui?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quando facies de persequentibus me judicium?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118085vul">85</span>&nbsp;Narraverunt mihi iniqui fabulationes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sed non ut lex tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118086vul">86</span>&nbsp;Omnia mandata tua veritas:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> inique persecuti sunt me, adjuva me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118087vul">87</span>&nbsp;Paulominus consummaverunt me in terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ego autem non dereliqui mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118088vul">88</span>&nbsp;Secundum misericordiam tuam vivifica me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et custodiam testimonia oris tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118089vul">89</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Lamed.</span> In &aelig;ternum, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> verbum tuum permanet in c&aelig;lo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118090vul">90</span>&nbsp;In generationem et generationem veritas tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> fundasti terram, et permanet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118091vul">91</span>&nbsp;Ordinatione tua perseverat dies,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam omnia serviunt tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118092vul">92</span>&nbsp;Nisi quod lex tua meditatio mea est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tunc forte periissem in humilitate mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118093vul">93</span>&nbsp;In &aelig;ternum non obliviscar justificationes tuas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in ipsis vivificasti me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118094vul">94</span>&nbsp;Tuus sum ego; salvum me fac:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam justificationes tuas exquisivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118095vul">95</span>&nbsp;Me exspectaverunt peccatores ut perderent me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> testimonia tua intellexi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118096vul">96</span>&nbsp;Omnis consummationis vidi finem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> latum mandatum tuum nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118097vul">97</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Mem.</span> Quomodo dilexi legem tuam, Domine!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die meditatio mea est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118098vul">98</span>&nbsp;Super inimicos meos prudentem me fecisti mandato tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in &aelig;ternum mihi est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118099vul">99</span>&nbsp;Super omnes docentes me intellexi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia testimonia tua meditatio mea est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118100vul">100</span>&nbsp;Super senes intellexi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mandata tua qu&aelig;sivi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118101vul">101</span>&nbsp;Ab omni via mala prohibui pedes meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut custodiam verba tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118102vul">102</span>&nbsp;A judiciis tuis non declinavi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia tu legem posuisti mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118103vul">103</span>&nbsp;Quam dulcia faucibus meis eloquia tua!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super mel ori meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118104vul">104</span>&nbsp;A mandatis tuis intellexi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propterea odivi omnem viam iniquitatis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118105vul">105</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Nun.</span> Lucerna pedibus meis verbum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lumen semitis meis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118106vul">106</span>&nbsp;Juravi et statui</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> custodire judicia justiti&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118107vul">107</span>&nbsp;Humiliatus sum usquequaque, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> vivifica me secundum verbum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118108vul">108</span>&nbsp;Voluntaria oris mei beneplacita fac, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et judicia tua doce me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118109vul">109</span>&nbsp;Anima mea in manibus meis semper,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et legem tuam non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118110vul">110</span>&nbsp;Posuerunt peccatores laqueum mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et de mandatis tuis non erravi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118111vul">111</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;reditate acquisivi testimonia tua in &aelig;ternum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia exsultatio cordis mei sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118112vul">112</span>&nbsp;Inclinavi cor meum ad faciendas justificationes tuas in &aelig;ternum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter retributionem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118113vul">113</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Samech.</span> Iniquos odio habui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et legem tuam dilexi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118114vul">114</span>&nbsp;Adjutor et susceptor meus es tu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in verbum tuum supersperavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118115vul">115</span>&nbsp;Declinate a me, maligni,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et scrutabor mandata Dei mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118116vul">116</span>&nbsp;Suscipe me secundum eloquium tuum, et vivam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non confundas me ab exspectatione mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118117vul">117</span>&nbsp;Adjuva me, et salvus ero,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et meditabor in justificationibus tuis semper.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118118vul">118</span>&nbsp;Sprevisti omnes discedentes a judiciis tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia injusta cogitatio eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118119vul">119</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig;varicantes reputavi omnes peccatores terr&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ideo dilexi testimonia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118120vul">120</span>&nbsp;Confige timore tuo carnes meas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a judiciis enim tuis timui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118121vul">121</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Ain.</span> Feci judicium et justitiam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non tradas me calumniantibus me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118122vul">122</span>&nbsp;Suscipe servum tuum in bonum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non calumnientur me superbi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118123vul">123</span>&nbsp;Oculi mei defecerunt in salutare tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in eloquium justiti&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118124vul">124</span>&nbsp;Fac cum servo tuo secundum misericordiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justificationes tuas doce me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118125vul">125</span>&nbsp;Servus tuus sum ego: da mihi intellectum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut sciam testimonia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118126vul">126</span>&nbsp;Tempus faciendi, Domine:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dissipaverunt legem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118127vul">127</span>&nbsp;Ideo dilexi mandata tua</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super aurum et topazion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118128vul">128</span>&nbsp;Propterea ad omnia mandata tua dirigebar;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnem viam iniquam odio habui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118129vul">129</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Phe.</span> Mirabilia testimonia tua:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ideo scrutata est ea anima mea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118130vul">130</span>&nbsp;Declaratio sermonum tuorum illuminat,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et intellectum dat parvulis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118131vul">131</span>&nbsp;Os meum aperui, et attraxi spiritum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mandata tua desiderabam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118132vul">132</span>&nbsp;Aspice in me, et miserere mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum judicium diligentium nomen tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118133vul">133</span>&nbsp;Gressus meos dirige secundum eloquium tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non dominetur mei omnis injustitia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118134vul">134</span>&nbsp;Redime me a calumniis hominum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut custodiam mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118135vul">135</span>&nbsp;Faciem tuam illumina super servum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et doce me justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118136vul">136</span>&nbsp;Exitus aquarum deduxerunt oculi mei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia non custodierunt legem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118137vul">137</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Sade.</span> Justus es, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et rectum judicium tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118138vul">138</span>&nbsp;Mandasti justitiam testimonia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et veritatem tuam nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118139vul">139</span>&nbsp;Tabescere me fecit zelus meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia obliti sunt verba tua inimici mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118140vul">140</span>&nbsp;Ignitum eloquium tuum vehementer,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et servus tuus dilexit illud.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118141vul">141</span>&nbsp;Adolescentulus sum ego et contemptus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justificationes tuas non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118142vul">142</span>&nbsp;Justitia tua, justitia in &aelig;ternum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lex tua veritas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118143vul">143</span>&nbsp;Tribulatio et angustia invenerunt me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mandata tua meditatio mea est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118144vul">144</span>&nbsp;&AElig;quitas testimonia tua in &aelig;ternum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intellectum da mihi, et vivam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118145vul">145</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Coph.</span> Clamavi in toto corde meo: exaudi me, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> justificationes tuas requiram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118146vul">146</span>&nbsp;Clamavi ad te; salvum me fac:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut custodiam mandata tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118147vul">147</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig;veni in maturitate, et clamavi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in verba tua supersperavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118148vul">148</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig;venerunt oculi mei ad te diluculo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut meditarer eloquia tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118149vul">149</span>&nbsp;Vocem meam audi secundum misericordiam tuam, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et secundum judicium tuum vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118150vul">150</span>&nbsp;Appropinquaverunt persequentes me iniquitati:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a lege autem tua longe facti sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118151vul">151</span>&nbsp;Prope es tu, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes vi&aelig; tu&aelig; veritas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118152vul">152</span>&nbsp;Initio cognovi de testimoniis tuis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in &aelig;ternum fundasti ea.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118153vul">153</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Res.</span> Vide humilitatem meam, et eripe me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia legem tuam non sum oblitus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118154vul">154</span>&nbsp;Judica judicium meum, et redime me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> propter eloquium tuum vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118155vul">155</span>&nbsp;Longe a peccatoribus salus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia justificationes tuas non exquisierunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118156vul">156</span>&nbsp;Misericordi&aelig; tu&aelig; mult&aelig;, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum judicium tuum vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118157vul">157</span>&nbsp;Multi qui persequuntur me, et tribulant me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a testimoniis tuis non declinavi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118158vul">158</span>&nbsp;Vidi pr&aelig;varicantes et tabescebam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia eloquia tua non custodierunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118159vul">159</span>&nbsp;Vide quoniam mandata tua dilexi, Domine:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in misericordia tua vivifica me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118160vul">160</span>&nbsp;Principium verborum tuorum veritas;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in &aelig;ternum omnia judicia justiti&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118161vul">161</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Sin.</span> Principes persecuti sunt me gratis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et a verbis tuis formidavit cor meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118162vul">162</span>&nbsp;L&aelig;tabor ego super eloquia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut qui invenit spolia multa.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118163vul">163</span>&nbsp;Iniquitatem odio habui, et abominatus sum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> legem autem tuam dilexi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118164vul">164</span>&nbsp;Septies in die laudem dixi tibi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super judicia justiti&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118165vul">165</span>&nbsp;Pax multa diligentibus legem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non est illis scandalum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118166vul">166</span>&nbsp;Exspectabam salutare tuum, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mandata tua dilexi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118167vul">167</span>&nbsp;Custodivit anima mea testimonia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dilexit ea vehementer.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118168vul">168</span>&nbsp;Servavi mandata tua et testimonia tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia omnes vi&aelig; me&aelig; in conspectu tuo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118169vul">169</span>&nbsp;<span class="speaker">Tau.</span> Appropinquet deprecatio mea in conspectu tuo, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> juxta eloquium tuum da mihi intellectum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118170vul">170</span>&nbsp;Intret postulatio mea in conspectu tuo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> secundum eloquium tuum eripe me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118171vul">171</span>&nbsp;Eructabunt labia mea hymnum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum docueris me justificationes tuas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118172vul">172</span>&nbsp;Pronuntiabit lingua mea eloquium tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia omnia mandata tua &aelig;quitas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118173vul">173</span>&nbsp;Fiat manus tua ut salvet me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam mandata tua elegi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118174vul">174</span>&nbsp;Concupivi salutare tuum, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lex tua meditatio mea est.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118175vul">175</span>&nbsp;Vivet anima mea, et laudabit te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et judicia tua adjuvabunt me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa118176vul">176</span>&nbsp;Erravi sicut ovis qu&aelig; periit: qu&aelig;re servum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia mandata tua non sum oblitus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
