<h1>Psalm 120</h1>
<div class="h1a">God is the keeper of his servants.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 121</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa119.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 120</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> I have lifted up my eyes to the mountains, from whence help shall come to me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> My help is from the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who made <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> May he not suffer thy foot to be moved: neither let him slumber that keepeth thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Behold he shall neither slumber nor sleep, that keepeth <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is thy keeper, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is thy protection upon thy right hand.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The sun shall not burn thee by day: nor the moon by night.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> keepeth thee from all <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>: may the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> keep thy <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> May the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> keep thy coming in and thy going out; from henceforth now and for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa120001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Levavi oculos meos in montes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> unde veniet auxilium mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Auxilium meum a Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui fecit c&aelig;lum et terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Non det in commotionem pedem tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque dormitet qui custodit te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Ecce non dormitabit neque dormiet</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui custodit Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Dominus custodit te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus protectio tua super manum dexteram tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Per diem sol non uret te,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque luna per noctem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Dominus custodit te ab omni malo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> custodiat animam tuam Dominus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa120008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dominus custodiat introitum tuum et exitum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex hoc nunc et usque in s&aelig;culum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
