<h1>Psalm 121</h1>
<div class="h1a">The desire and hope of the just for the coming of the kingdom of God, and the peace of his Church.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 122</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa120.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 121</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> I rejoiced at the things that were said to me: We shall go into the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Our feet were standing in thy <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a>, O <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>, which is built as a city, which is compact together.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For thither did the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15039a.htm">-->tribes<!--</a>--> go up, the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15039a.htm">-->tribes<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: the testimony of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>, to praise the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Because their seats have sat in <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>-->, seats upon the house of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">Pray</a> ye for the things that are for the peace of <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>: and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->abundance<!--</a>--> for them that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Let peace be in thy strength: and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->abundance<!--</a>--> in thy towers.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> For the sake of my brethren, and of my neighbours, I spoke peace of thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Because of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a> our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I have sought <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things for thee.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa121001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">L&aelig;tatus sum in his qu&aelig; dicta sunt mihi:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In domum Domini ibimus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Stantes erant pedes nostri</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in atriis tuis, Jerusalem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Jerusalem, qu&aelig; &aelig;dificatur ut civitas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cujus participatio ejus in idipsum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Illuc enim ascenderunt tribus, tribus Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> testimonium Isra&euml;l,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad confitendum nomini Domini.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quia illic sederunt sedes in judicio,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sedes super domum David.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Rogate qu&aelig; ad pacem sunt Jerusalem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et abundantia diligentibus te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Fiat pax in virtute tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et abundantia in turribus tuis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Propter fratres meos et proximos meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> loquebar pacem de te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa121009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Propter domum Domini Dei nostri,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig;sivi bona tibi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
