<h1>Psalm 123</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church gives glory to God for her deliverance, from the hands of her enemies.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 124</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa122.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 123</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> If it had not been that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> was with us, let <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> now say:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> If it had not been that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> was with us, When <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> rose up against us,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Perhaps they had swallowed us up alive. When their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">-->fury<!--</a>--> was enkindled against us,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Perhaps the waters had swallowed us up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Our <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath passed through a torrent: perhaps our <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> had passed through a water insupportable.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who hath not given us to be a prey to their teeth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Our <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath been delivered as a sparrow out of the snare of the fowlers. The snare is broken, and we are delivered.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Our help is in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who made <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and earth.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa123001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Nisi quia Dominus erat in nobis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dicat nunc Isra&euml;l,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123002vul">2</span>&nbsp;nisi quia Dominus erat in nobis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum exsurgerent homines in nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123003vul">3</span>&nbsp;forte vivos deglutissent nos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum irasceretur furor eorum in nos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123004vul">4</span>&nbsp;forsitan aqua absorbuisset nos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123005vul">5</span>&nbsp;torrentem pertransivit anima nostra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> forsitan pertransisset anima nostra</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aquam intolerabilem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Benedictus Dominus, qui non dedit nos</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in captionem dentibus eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Anima nostra sicut passer erepta est</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> de laqueo venantium;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laqueus contritus est,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nos liberati sumus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa123008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Adjutorium nostrum in nomine Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui fecit c&aelig;lum et terram.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
