<div class="h1a">The just are always under God's protection.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 125</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa123.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 124</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> They that trust in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall be as mount Sion: he shall not be moved for ever that dwelleth</span><!--/propar--></p>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> In <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>. Mountains are round about it: so the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is round about his people from henceforth now and for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will not leave the rod of sinners upon the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09366b.htm">-->lot<!--</a>--> of the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>: that the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> may not stretch forth their hands to <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Do <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to those that are <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>, and to the upright of heart.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> But such as turn aside into bonds, the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall lead out with the workers of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: peace upon <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa124001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Qui confidunt in Domino, sicut mons Sion:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non commovebitur in &aelig;ternum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui habitat</span>
<span class="poe003"><span class="verse" id="psa124002vul">2</span>&nbsp;in Jerusalem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Montes in circuitu ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Dominus in circuitu populi sui,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex hoc nunc et usque in s&aelig;culum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa124003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Quia non relinquet Dominus virgam peccatorum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super sortem justorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ut non extendant justi</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad iniquitatem manus suas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa124004vul">4</span>&nbsp;benefac, Domine, bonis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et rectis corde.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa124005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Declinantes autem in obligationes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adducet Dominus cum operantibus iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Pax super Isra&euml;l!</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
