<h1>Psalm 125</h1>
<div class="h1a">The people of God rejoice at their delivery from captivity.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 126</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa124.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 125</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> When the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> brought back the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>--> of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, we became like <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> comforted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Then was our mouth filled with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">gladness</a>; and our <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> with <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>. Then shall they say among the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a>: The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath done great things for them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath done great things for us: we are become <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyful<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Turn again our <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03315a.htm">-->captivity<!--</a>-->, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, as a stream in the south.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They that sow in tears shall reap in <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Going they went and wept, casting their seeds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> But coming they shall come with <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyfulness<!--</a>-->, carrying their sheaves.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa125001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">In convertendo Dominus captivitatem Sion,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facti sumus sicut consolati.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa125002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Tunc repletum est gaudio os nostrum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et lingua nostra exsultatione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Tunc dicent inter gentes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Magnificavit Dominus facere cum eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa125003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Magnificavit Dominus facere nobiscum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facti sumus l&aelig;tantes.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa125004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Converte, Domine, captivitatem nostram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sicut torrens in austro.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa125005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Qui seminant in lacrimis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in exsultatione metent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa125006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Euntes ibant et flebant,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mittentes semina sua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Venientes autem venient cum exsultatione,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> portantes manipulos suos.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
