<h1>Psalm 127</h1>
<div class="h1a">The fear of God is the way to happiness.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 128</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa126.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 127</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> are all they that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: that walk in his ways.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> For thou shalt eat the labours of thy hands: <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> art thou, and it shall be well with thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thy wife as a fruitful vine, on the sides of thy house. Thy children as olive plants, round about thy table.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Behold, thus shall the <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> be <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->feareth<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> May the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thee out of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: and mayst thou see the <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> things of <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a> all the days of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> And mayst thou see thy children's children, peace upon <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa127001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Beati omnes qui timent Dominum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui ambulant in viis ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa127002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Labores manuum tuarum quia manducabis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> beatus es, et bene tibi erit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa127003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Uxor tua sicut vitis abundans</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in lateribus domus tu&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> filii tui sicut novell&aelig; olivarum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in circuitu mens&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa127004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Ecce sic benedicetur homo</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui timet Dominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa127005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Benedicat tibi Dominus ex Sion,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et videas bona Jerusalem omnibus diebus vit&aelig; tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa127006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Et videas filios filiorum tuorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pacem super Isra&euml;l.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
