<h1>Psalm 128</h1>
<div class="h1a">The Church of God is invincible: her persecutors come to nothing.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 129</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa127.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 128</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Often have they fought against me from my youth, let <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> now say.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Often have they fought against me from my youth: but they could not prevail over me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> have wrought upon my back: they have lengthened their <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> who is <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> cut the necks of sinners:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Let them all be confounded and turned back that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hate</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Let them be as grass upon the tops of houses: which withereth before it be plucked up:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Who with the mower filleth not his hand: nor he that gathereth sheaves his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01055a.htm">-->bosom<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And they that passed by have not said: The <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> be upon you: we have <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessed</a> you in the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa128001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">S&aelig;pe expugnaverunt me a juventute mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dicat nunc Isra&euml;l;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128002vul">2</span>&nbsp;s&aelig;pe expugnaverunt me a juventute mea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> etenim non potuerunt mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Supra dorsum meum fabricaverunt peccatores;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> prolongaverunt iniquitatem suam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Dominus justus</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> concidit cervices peccatorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Confundantur, et convertantur retrorsum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnes qui oderunt Sion.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Fiant sicut f&oelig;num tectorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quod priusquam evellatur exaruit:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128007vul">7</span>&nbsp;de quo non implevit manum suam qui metit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sinum suum qui manipulos colligit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa128008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Et non dixerunt qui pr&aelig;teribant:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Benedictio Domini super vos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Benediximus vobis in nomine Domini.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
