<h1>Psalm 129</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of a sinner, trusting in the mercies of God. The sixth penitential psalm.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 130</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa128.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 129</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/04738b.htm">Out of the depths</a> I have cried to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, hear my voice. Let thy ears be attentive to the voice of my supplication.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> If thou, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, wilt mark <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>: <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, who shall stand it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For with thee there is merciful forgiveness: and by <!--nnn--><!--<a href="../cathen/12673b.htm">-->reason<!--</a>--> of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->law<!--</a>-->, I have waited for thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath relied on his word:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> My <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> From the morning watch even until night, let <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Because with the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> there is mercy: and with him plentiful <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redemption</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> And he shall <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeem</a> <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> from all his <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa129001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">De profundis clamavi ad te, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Domine, exaudi vocem meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Fiant aures tu&aelig; intendentes in vocem deprecationis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Si iniquitates observaveris, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, quis sustinebit?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia apud te propitiatio est;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et propter legem tuam sustinui te, Domine.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Sustinuit anima mea in verbo ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129005vul">5</span>&nbsp;speravit anima mea in Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129006vul">6</span>&nbsp;A custodia matutina usque ad noctem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> speret Isra&euml;l in Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Quia apud Dominum misericordia,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et copiosa apud eum redemptio.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa129008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Et ipse redimet Isra&euml;l</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ex omnibus iniquitatibus ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
