<h1>Psalm 131</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer for the fulfilling of the promise made to David.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 132</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa130.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 131</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <a href="../cathen/06718a.htm">gradual canticle</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, remember <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, and all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">-->meekness<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> How he <a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">swore</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, he <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vowed</a> a <a href="../cathen/15511a.htm">vow</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> If I shall enter into the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">-->tabernacle<!--</a>--> of my house: if I shall go up into the bed wherein I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->lie<!--</a>-->:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> If I shall give sleep to my eyes, or slumber to my eyelids,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Or rest to my <a href="../cathen/14495a.htm">temples</a>: until I find out a place for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">-->tabernacle<!--</a>--> for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Behold we have heard of it in <a href="../cathen/02533a.htm">Ephrata</a>: we have found it in the fields of the wood. <span class="stiki"><strong>We have heard of it in Ephrata...</strong> When I was young, and lived in <a href="../cathen/02533a.htm">Bethlehem</a>, otherwise called <a href="../cathen/02533a.htm">Ephrata</a>, I heard of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God's</a> <a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">tabernacle</a> and <a href="../cathen/01721a.htm">ark</a>, and had a devout desire of seeking it; and accordingly I found it at Cariathiarim, the city of the woods: where it was till it was removed to <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>. See <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->1<!--</a>--> Par. <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->13<!--</a>-->.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> We <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> go into his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14424b.htm">-->tabernacle<!--</a>-->: we <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">adore</a> in the place where his feet stood.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Arise, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, into thy resting place: thou and the <a href="../cathen/01721a.htm">ark</a>, which thou hast <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">sanctified</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Let thy <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priests</a> be clothed with <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>: and let thy <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a> rejoice.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> For thy servant <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David's</a> sake, turn not away the face of thy <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->anointed<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11176a.htm">-->sworn<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, and he will not make it void: of the fruit of thy womb I will set upon thy throne.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> If thy children <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> keep my covenant, and these my testimonies which I shall teach them: Their children also for evermore shall sit upon thy throne.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath chosen <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->: he hath chosen it for his dwelling.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> This is my rest for ever and ever: here <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I dwell, for I have chosen it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessing</a> I will <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> her <a href="../cathen/15617c.htm">widow</a>: I will <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/02055a.htm">-->satisfy<!--</a>--> her <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>--> with bread.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> I will clothe her <a href="../cathen/12406a.htm">priests</a> with <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>, and her <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a> shall rejoice with exceeding great <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> There <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> I bring forth a horn to <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>: I have prepared a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08770a.htm">-->lamp<!--</a>--> for my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->anointed<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> His enemies I will clothe with confusion: but upon him shall my <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">sanctification</a> flourish.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa131001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Canticum graduum.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Memento, Domine, David,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnis mansuetudinis ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131002vul">2</span>&nbsp;sicut juravit Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> votum vovit Deo Jacob:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Si introiero in tabernaculum domus me&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> si ascendero in lectum strati mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131004vul">4</span>&nbsp;si dedero somnum oculis meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et palpebris meis dormitationem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131005vul">5</span>&nbsp;et requiem temporibus meis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> donec inveniam locum Domino,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tabernaculum Deo Jacob.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Ecce audivimus eam in Ephrata;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> invenimus eam in campis silv&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Introibimus in tabernaculum ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> adorabimus in loco ubi steterunt pedes ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Surge, Domine, in requiem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tu et arca sanctificationis tu&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Sacerdotes tui induantur justitiam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sancti tui exsultent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Propter David servum tuum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> non avertas faciem christi tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Juravit Dominus David veritatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non frustrabitur eam:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> De fructu ventris tui</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ponam super sedem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Si custodierint filii tui testamentum meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et testimonia mea h&aelig;c qu&aelig; docebo eos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et filii eorum usque in s&aelig;culum</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> sedebunt super sedem tuam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Quoniam elegit Dominus Sion:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> elegit eam in habitationem sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131014vul">14</span>&nbsp;H&aelig;c requies mea in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> hic habitabo, quoniam elegi eam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Viduam ejus benedicens benedicam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pauperes ejus saturabo panibus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Sacerdotes ejus induam salutari,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sancti ejus exsultatione exsultabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Illuc producam cornu David;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> paravi lucernam christo meo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa131018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Inimicos ejus induam confusione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super ipsum autem efflorebit sanctificatio mea.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
