<h1>Psalm 134</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to praise God: the vanity of idols.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 135</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa133.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 134</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: O you his servants, praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> You that stand in the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of the Lord</a>, in the <a href="../cathen/04445a.htm">courts</a> of the <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">house of our God</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: sing ye to his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, for it is sweet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> hath chosen <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> unto himself: <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> for his own <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12462a.htm">-->possession<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> For I have <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is great, and our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is above all <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Whatsoever the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> pleased he hath done, in <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>, in earth, in the sea, and in all the <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">deeps</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> He bringeth up clouds from the end of the earth: he hath made lightnings for the rain. He bringeth forth winds out of his stores:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> He <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slew<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06081a.htm">firstborn</a> of <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a> from <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> even unto beast.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> He sent forth <a href="../cathen/10338a.htm">signs and wonders</a> in the midst of thee, O <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a>: upon <a href="../cathen/11788c.htm">Pharao</a>, and upon all his servants.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> He smote many <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">-->nations<!--</a>-->, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slew<!--</a>--> mighty kings:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Sehon king of the <a href="../cathen/01433c.htm">Amorrhites</a>, and Og king of Basan, and all the kingdoms of <a href="../cathen/03569b.htm">Chanaan</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And gave their land for an inheritance, for an inheritance to his people <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, is for ever: thy memorial, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, unto all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> judge his people, and will be entreated in favour of his servants.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> The <a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">idols</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06422a.htm">Gentiles</a> are silver and gold, the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men's</a> hands.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> They have a mouth, but they speak not: they have eyes, but they see not.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> They have ears, but they hear not: neither is there any breath in their mouths.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> Let them that make them be like to them: and every one that trusteth in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">house of Israel</a>: <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O house of <a href="../cathen/01003a.htm">Aaron</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O <a href="../cathen/09206a.htm">house of Levi</a>: you that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> out of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, who dwelleth in <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa134001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Laudate nomen Domini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate, servi, Dominum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134002vul">2</span>&nbsp;qui statis in domo Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in atriis domus Dei nostri.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Laudate Dominum, quia bonus Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallite nomini ejus, quoniam suave.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quoniam Jacob elegit sibi Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Isra&euml;l in possessionem sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Quia ego cognovi quod magnus est Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et Deus noster pr&aelig; omnibus diis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Omnia qu&aelig;cumque voluit Dominus fecit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in c&aelig;lo, in terra, in mari et in omnibus abyssis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Educens nubes ab extremo terr&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> fulgura in pluviam fecit;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui producit ventos de thesauris suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Qui percussit primogenita &AElig;gypti,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ab homine usque ad pecus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Et misit signa et prodigia in medio tui, &AElig;gypte:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in Pharaonem, et in omnes servos ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Qui percussit gentes multas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et occidit reges fortes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Sehon, regem Amorrh&aelig;orum, et Og, regem Basan,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnia regna Chanaan:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134012vul">12</span>&nbsp;et dedit terram eorum h&aelig;reditatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> h&aelig;reditatem Isra&euml;l populo suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Domine, nomen tuum in &aelig;ternum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, memoriale tuum in generationem et generationem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Quia judicabit Dominus populum suum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in servis suis deprecabitur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Simulacra gentium argentum et aurum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> opera manuum hominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Os habent, et non loquentur;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oculos habent, et non videbunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Aures habent, et non audient;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque enim est spiritus in ore ipsorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Similes illis fiant qui faciunt ea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes qui confidunt in eis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Domus Isra&euml;l, benedicite Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> domus Aaron, benedicite Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Domus Levi, benedicite Domino;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui timetis Dominum, benedicite Domino.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa134021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Benedictus Dominus ex Sion,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui habitat in Jerusalem.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
