<h1>Psalm 135</h1>
<div class="h1a">God is to be praised for his wonderful works.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 136</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa134.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 135</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>. Praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, for he is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever. <span class="stiki"><strong>Praise the Lord...</strong> By this invitation to praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thrice repeated, we profess the <a href="../cathen/15047a.htm">Blessed Trinity</a>, One <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> in three distinct <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11726a.htm">-->Persons<!--</a>-->, the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Father<!--</a>-->, and the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14142b.htm">-->Son<!--</a>-->, and the <a href="../cathen/07409a.htm">Holy Ghost</a>.</span></span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07636a.htm">-->gods<!--</a>-->: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of lords: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Who alone doth great wonders: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Who made the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> in understanding: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Who established the earth above the waters: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Who made the great lights: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The sun to rule the day: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> The moon and the stars to rule the night: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Who smote <a href="../cathen/05329b.htm">Egypt</a> with their <a href="../cathen/06081a.htm">firstborn</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Who brought out <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> from among them: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> With a mighty hand and with a stretched out arm: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Who divided the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a> into parts: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> And brought out <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> through the midst thereof: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> And overthrew <a href="../cathen/11788c.htm">Pharao</a> and his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">-->host<!--</a>--> in the <a href="../cathen/12688a.htm">Red Sea</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Who led his people through the <a href="../cathen/04749a.htm">desert</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> Who smote great kings: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> And <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->slew<!--</a>--> strong kings: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> Sehon king of the <a href="../cathen/01433c.htm">Amorrhites</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> And Og king of Basan: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> And he gave their land for an inheritance: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> For an inheritance to his servant <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> For he was mindful of us in our affliction: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> And he <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> us from our enemies: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse25">25</span> Who giveth food to all flesh: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse26">26</span> Give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<p class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse27">27</span> Give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> of lords: for his mercy endureth for ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa135001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Confitemini Domino, quoniam bonus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Confitemini Deo deorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Confitemini Domino dominorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Qui facit mirabilia magna solus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Qui fecit c&aelig;los in intellectu,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Qui firmavit terram super aquas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Qui fecit luminaria magna,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135008vul">8</span>&nbsp;solem in potestatem diei,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135009vul">9</span>&nbsp;lunam et stellas in potestatem noctis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Qui percussit &AElig;gyptum cum primogenitis eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Qui eduxit Isra&euml;l de medio eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135012vul">12</span>&nbsp;in manu potenti et brachio excelso,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Qui divisit mare Rubrum in divisiones,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135014vul">14</span>&nbsp;et eduxit Isra&euml;l per medium ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135015vul">15</span>&nbsp;et excussit Pharaonem et virtutem ejus in mari Rubro,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Qui traduxit populum suum per desertum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Qui percussit reges magnos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135018vul">18</span>&nbsp;et occidit reges fortes,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Sehon, regem Amorrh&aelig;orum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135020vul">20</span>&nbsp;et Og, regem Basan,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135021vul">21</span>&nbsp;et dedit terram eorum h&aelig;reditatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135022vul">22</span>&nbsp;h&aelig;reditatem Isra&euml;l, servo suo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135023vul">23</span>&nbsp;Quia in humilitate nostra memor fuit nostri,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135024vul">24</span>&nbsp;et redemit nos ab inimicis nostris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135025vul">25</span>&nbsp;Qui dat escam omni carni,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa135026vul">26</span>&nbsp;Confitemini Deo c&aelig;li,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Confitemini Domino dominorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam in &aelig;ternum misericordia ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
