<h1>Psalm 137</h1>
<div class="h1a">Thanksgiving to God for his benefits.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 138</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa136.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 137</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> For <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">I will praise thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, with my whole heart: for thou hast heard the words of my mouth. I will sing praise to thee in the sight of the <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I will <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01151a.htm">-->worship<!--</a>--> towards thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/14499a.htm">temple</a>, and I will give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>. For thy mercy, and for thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: for thou hast magnified thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> above all.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> In what day soever I shall call upon thee, hear me: thou shalt multiply strength in my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> May all the kings of the earth give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to thee: for they have heard all the words of thy mouth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> And let them sing in the ways of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: for great is the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is high, and looketh on the low: and the high he <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knoweth</a> afar off.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> If I shall walk in the midst of tribulation, thou wilt quicken me: and thou hast stretched forth thy hand against the <a href="../cathen/01489a.htm">wrath</a> of my enemies: and thy right hand hath <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->saved<!--</a>--> me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will repay for me: thy mercy, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, endureth for ever: O <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despise</a> not the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of thy hands.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa137001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Confitebor tibi, Domine, in toto corde meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam audisti verba oris mei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In conspectu angelorum psallam tibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137002vul">2</span>&nbsp;adorabo ad templum sanctum tuum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et confitebor nomini tuo:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> super misericordia tua et veritate tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam magnificasti super omne, nomen sanctum tuum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137003vul">3</span>&nbsp;In quacumque die invocavero te, exaudi me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> multiplicabis in anima mea virtutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Confiteantur tibi, Domine, omnes reges terr&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia audierunt omnia verba oris tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Et cantent in viis Domini,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam magna est gloria Domini;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137006vul">6</span>&nbsp;quoniam excelsus Dominus, et humilia respicit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et alta a longe cognoscit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Si ambulavero in medio tribulationis, vivificabis me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et super iram inimicorum meorum extendisti manum tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et salvum me fecit dextera tua.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa137008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dominus retribuet pro me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Domine, misericordia tua in s&aelig;culum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> opera manuum tuarum ne despicias.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
