<h1>Psalm 138</h1>
<div class="h1a">God's special providence over his servants.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 139</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa137.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 138</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou hast <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12454c.htm">-->proved<!--</a>--> me, and <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Thou hast <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> my sitting down, and my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->rising<!--</a>--> up.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Thou hast understood my thoughts afar off: my path and my line thou hast searched out.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And thou hast foreseen all my ways: for there is no speech in my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>-->. <span class="stiki"><strong>There is no speech, etc...</strong> Viz., unknown to thee: or when there is no speech in my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>-->; yet my whole interior and my most secret thoughts are <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> to thee.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Behold, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou hast <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> all things, the last and those of old: thou hast formed me, and hast laid thy hand upon me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Thy <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knowledge</a> is become wonderful to me: it is high, and I cannot reach to it.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Whither shall I go from thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>-->? or whither shall I flee from thy face?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> If I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01767a.htm">-->ascend<!--</a>--> into <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a>, thou art there: if I descend into hell, thou art present.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> If I take my wings early in the morning, and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Even there also shall thy hand lead me: and thy right hand shall hold me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> And I said: Perhaps darkness shall cover me: and night shall be my light in my pleasures.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> But darkness shall not be dark to thee, and night shall be light all the day: the darkness thereof, and the light thereof are alike to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For thou hast possessed my reins: thou hast protected me from my mother's womb.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> I will praise thee, for thou art <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fearfully<!--</a>--> magnified: wonderful are thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->, and my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">knoweth</a> right well.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> My bone is not hidden from thee, which thou hast made in secret: and my <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->substance<!--</a>--> in the lower parts of the earth.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Thy eyes did see my imperfect being, and in thy book all shall be written: days shall be formed, and no one in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> But to me thy friends, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, are made exceedingly <a href="../cathen/07462a.htm">honourable</a>: their principality is exceedingly strengthened.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> I will <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11151a.htm">-->number<!--</a>--> them, and they shall be multiplied above the sand, I rose up and am still with thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> If thou wilt <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07441a.htm">-->kill<!--</a>--> the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: ye <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> of blood, depart from me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> Because you say in thought: They shall receive thy cities in vain. <span class="stiki"><strong>Because you say in thought, etc...</strong> Depart from me, you <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>, who plot against the servants of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and think to cast them out of the cities of their habitation; as if they have received them in vain, and to no purpose.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> Have I not <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> them, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, that <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> thee: and pined away because of thy enemies?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse22">22</span> I have <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hated</a> them with a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11665b.htm">-->perfect<!--</a>--> <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hatred</a>: and they are become enemies to me. <span class="stiki"><strong>I have hated them...</strong> Not with an <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">hatred</a> of <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">malice</a>, but a <a href="../cathen/15753a.htm">zeal</a> for the observance of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God's</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04153a.htm">-->commandments<!--</a>-->; which he saw were <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">despised</a> by the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>, who are to be considered enemies to <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse23">23</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12454c.htm">-->Prove<!--</a>--> me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, and <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> my heart: examine me, and <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> my paths.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse24">24</span> And see if there be in me the way of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and lead me in the <a href="../cathen/05551b.htm">eternal</a> way.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

