<h1>Psalm 139</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer to be delivered from the wicked.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 140</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa138.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 139</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Unto the end, a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Deliver me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, from the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>: rescue me from the <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Who have devised <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquities</a> in their hearts: all the day long they designed battles.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> They have sharpened their <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongues<!--</a>--> like a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04764a.htm">-->serpent<!--</a>-->: the venom of asps is under their lips.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Keep me, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, from the hand of the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>: and from <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> deliver me. Who have proposed to supplant my steps:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/12405a.htm">proud</a> have hidden a net for me. And they have stretched out cords for a snare: they have laid for me a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13506d.htm">-->stumbling block<!--</a>--> by the wayside.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> I said to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: Thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>: hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the voice of my supplication.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, the strength of my <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>: thou hast overshadowed my head in the day of battle.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Give me not up, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, from my desire to the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a>: they have plotted against me; do not thou forsake me, lest they should triumph.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The head of them compassing me about: the labour of their lips shall overwhelm them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Burning coals shall fall upon them; thou wilt cast them down into the fire: in miseries they shall not be able to stand.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> A <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> full of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14776c.htm">-->tongue<!--</a>--> shall not be established in the earth: <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> shall catch the <a href="../cathen/08010c.htm">unjust</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> unto destruction.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> I <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> that the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> will do <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a> to the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->needy<!--</a>-->, and will revenge the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12327a.htm">-->poor<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> But as for the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>, they shall give <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> to thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: and the upright shall dwell with thy countenance.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa139001vul">1</span>&nbsp;In finem. Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa139002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Eripe me, Domine, ab homine malo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> a viro iniquo eripe me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Qui cogitaverunt iniquitates in corde,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tota die constituebant pr&aelig;lia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Acuerunt linguas suas sicut serpentis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> venenum aspidum sub labiis eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Custodi me, Domine, de manu peccatoris,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ab hominibus iniquis eripe me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Qui cogitaverunt supplantare gressus meos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139006vul">6</span>&nbsp;absconderunt superbi laqueum mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Et funes extenderunt in laqueum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> juxta iter, scandalum posuerunt mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Dixi Domino: Deus meus es tu;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exaudi, Domine, vocem deprecationis me&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Domine, Domine, virtus salutis me&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> obumbrasti super caput meum in die belli.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Ne tradas me, Domine, a desiderio meo peccatori:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cogitaverunt contra me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ne derelinquas me, ne forte exaltentur.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Caput circuitus eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> labor labiorum ipsorum operiet eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Cadent super eos carbones;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in ignem dejicies eos:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in miseriis non subsistent.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Vir linguosus non dirigetur in terra;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> virum injustum mala capient in interitu.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Cognovi quia faciet Dominus judicium inopis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vindictam pauperum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa139014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Verumtamen justi confitebuntur nomini tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et habitabunt recti cum vultu tuo.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
