<h1>Psalm 140</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer against sinful words, and deceitful flatterers.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 141</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa139.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 140</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> I have cried to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, hear me: hearken to my voice, when I cry to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Let my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> be directed as <a href="../cathen/07716a.htm">incense</a> in thy sight; the lifting up of my hands, as evening <a href="../cathen/13309a.htm">sacrifice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Set a watch, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, before my mouth: and a door round about my lips.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Incline not my heart to <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a> words; to make excuses in <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">sins</a>. With <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> that work <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>: and I will not communicate with the choicest of them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> shall correct me in mercy, and shall reprove me: but let not the oil of the sinner fatten my head. For my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> shall still be against the things with which they are well pleased: <span class="stiki"><strong>Let not the oil of the sinner, etc...</strong> That is, the flattery, or <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09469a.htm">-->deceitful<!--</a>--> praise. -- Ibid. <strong>For my prayer, etc...</strong> So far from <a href="../cathen/04462a.htm">coveting</a> their praises, who are never well pleased but with things that are <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">evil</a>; I shall continually <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">pray</a> to be preserved from such things as they are delighted with.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Their <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judges<!--</a>--> falling upon the rock have been swallowed up. They shall hear my words, for they have prevailed: <span class="stiki"><strong>Their judges, etc...</strong> Their rulers, or chiefs, quickly vanish and perish, like ships dashed against the rocks, and swallowed up by the waves. Let them then hear my words, for they are powerful and will prevail; or, as it is in the <a href="../cathen/07176a.htm">Hebrew</a>, for they are sweet.</span></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> As when the thickness of the earth is broken up upon the ground: Our bones are <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">-->scattered<!--</a>--> by the side of hell.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> But to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, are my eyes: in thee have I put my trust, take not away my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Keep me from the snare, which they have laid for me, and from the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13506d.htm">-->stumbling blocks<!--</a>--> of them that work <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> shall fall in his net: I am alone until I pass. <span class="stiki"><strong>I am alone, etc...</strong> Singularly protected by the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">-->Almighty<!--</a>-->, until I pass all their nets and snares.</span></span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa140001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Domine, clamavi ad te: exaudi me;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> intende voci me&aelig;, cum clamavero ad te.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Dirigatur oratio mea sicut incensum in conspectu tuo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> elevatio manuum mearum sacrificium vespertinum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Pone, Domine, custodiam ori meo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et ostium circumstanti&aelig; labiis meis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Non declines cor meum in verba maliti&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad excusandas excusationes in peccatis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> cum hominibus operantibus iniquitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non communicabo cum electis eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Corripiet me justus in misericordia, et increpabit me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oleum autem peccatoris non impinguet caput meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quoniam adhuc et oratio mea in beneplacitis eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140006vul">6</span>&nbsp;absorpti sunt juncti petr&aelig; judices eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Audient verba mea, quoniam potuerunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Sicut crassitudo terr&aelig; erupta est super terram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dissipata sunt ossa nostra secus infernum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Quia ad te, Domine, Domine, oculi mei;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in te speravi, non auferas animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Custodi me a laqueo quem statuerunt mihi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et a scandalis operantium iniquitatem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa140010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Cadent in retiaculo ejus peccatores:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> singulariter sum ego, donec transeam.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
