<h1>Psalm 141</h1>
<div class="h1a">A prayer of David in extremity of danger.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 142</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa140.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 141</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Of understanding for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, A <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a> when he was in the cave. <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">--><!--</a>-->[1 <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08647b.htm">-->Samuel<!--</a>--> 24.]</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> I cried to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with my voice: with my voice I made supplication to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> In his sight I pour out my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, and before him I declare my trouble:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> When my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> failed me, then thou <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">-->knewest<!--</a>--> my paths. In this way wherein I walked, they have hidden a snare for me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I looked on my right hand, and beheld, and there was no one that would <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">know</a> me. Flight hath failed me: and there is no one that hath regard to my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> I cried to thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I said: Thou art my <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a>, my portion in the land of the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->living<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Attend to my supplication: for I am brought very low. Deliver me from my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">-->persecutors<!--</a>-->; for they are stronger than I.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Bring my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> out of <a href="../cathen/12430a.htm">prison</a>, that I may praise thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a>: the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> wait for me, until thou reward me.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa141001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Intellectus David, cum esset in spelunca, oratio.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa141002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Voce mea ad Dominum clamavi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> voce mea ad Dominum deprecatus sum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Effundo in conspectu ejus orationem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tribulationem meam ante ipsum pronuntio:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141004vul">4</span>&nbsp;in deficiendo ex me spiritum meum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tu cognovisti semitas meas.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> In via hac qua ambulabam</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> absconderunt laqueum mihi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Considerabam ad dexteram, et videbam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non erat qui cognosceret me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> periit fuga a me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et non est qui requirat animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Clamavi ad te, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dixi: Tu es spes mea,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> portio mea in terra viventium.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Intende ad deprecationem meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia humiliatus sum nimis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Libera me a persequentibus me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia confortati sunt super me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa141008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Educ de custodia animam meam</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad confitendum nomini tuo;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> me exspectant justi donec retribuas mihi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
