<h1>Psalm 142</h1>
<div class="h1a">The psalmist in tribulation calls upon God for his delivery. The seventh penitential psalm.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 143</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa141.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 142</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a>, when his son <a href="../cathen/01058c.htm">Absalom</a> pursued him. <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">--><!--</a>-->[<a href="../bible/2sa017.htm">2 Samuel 17</a>]<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">Hear, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, my <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>: give ear to my supplication in thy <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>: hear me in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> And enter not into <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->judgment<!--</a>--> with thy servant: for in thy sight no <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->living<!--</a>--> shall be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08573a.htm">-->justified<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> For the enemy hath <a href="../cathen/11703a.htm">persecuted</a> my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: he hath brought down my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>--> to the earth. He hath made me to dwell in darkness as those that have been dead of old:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> And my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> is in anguish within me: my heart within me is troubled.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> I remembered the days of old, I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditated<!--</a>--> on all thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->: I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04324b.htm">-->meditated<!--</a>--> upon the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>--> of thy hands.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> I stretched forth my hands to thee: my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> is as earth without water unto thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Hear me speedily, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> hath fainted away. Turn not away thy face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03459a.htm">-->Cause<!--</a>--> me to hear thy mercy in the morning; for in thee have I <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>-->. Make the way <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> to me, wherein I should walk: for I have lifted up my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Deliver me from my enemies, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, to thee have I fled:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Teach me to do thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>-->, for thou art my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>. Thy <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> shall lead me into the right land:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> For thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name's</a> sake, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, thou wilt quicken me in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>. Thou wilt bring my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a> out of trouble:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> And in thy mercy thou wilt destroy my enemies. And thou wilt cut off all them that afflict my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>: for I am thy servant.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa142001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David, quando persequebatur eum Absalom filius ejus.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Domine, exaudi orationem meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> auribus percipe obsecrationem meam in veritate tua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> exaudi me in tua justitia.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Et non intres in judicium cum servo tuo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia non justificabitur in conspectu tuo omnis vivens.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Quia persecutus est inimicus animam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> humiliavit in terra vitam meam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> collocavit me in obscuris, sicut mortuos s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Et anxiatus est super me spiritus meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in me turbatum est cor meum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Memor fui dierum antiquorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> meditatus sum in omnibus operibus tuis:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in factis manuum tuarum meditabar.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Expandi manus meas ad te;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> anima mea sicut terra sine aqua tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Velociter exaudi me, Domine;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> defecit spiritus meus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non avertas faciem tuam a me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et similis ero descendentibus in lacum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Auditam fac mihi mane misericordiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia in te speravi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Notam fac mihi viam in qua ambulem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia ad te levavi animam meam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Eripe me de inimicis meis, Domine:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ad te confugi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Doce me facere voluntatem tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quia Deus meus es tu.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Spiritus tuus bonus deducet me in terram rectam.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Propter nomen tuum, Domine, vivificabis me:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in &aelig;quitate tua, educes de tribulatione animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa142012vul">12</span>&nbsp;et in misericordia tua disperdes inimicos meos,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et perdes omnes qui tribulant animam meam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quoniam ego servus tuus sum.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
