<h1>Psalm 143</h1>
<div class="h1a">The prophet praises God, and prays to be delivered from his enemies. No worldly happiness is to be compared with that of serving God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 144</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa142.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 143</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em>A <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> against Goliath.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> be the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, who teacheth my hands to fight, and my fingers to <a href="../cathen/15546c.htm">war</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> My mercy, and my refuge: my support, and my deliverer: My protector, and I have <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">-->hoped<!--</a>--> in him: who subdueth my people under me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, what is <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>, that thou art made known to him? or the <a href="../cathen/14144a.htm">son of man</a>, that thou makest account of him?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">-->Man<!--</a>--> is like to vanity: his days pass away like a shadow.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, bow down thy <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> and descend: touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Send forth lightning, and thou shalt <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">-->scatter<!--</a>--> them: shoot out thy arrows, and thou shalt trouble them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Put forth thy hand from on high, take me out, and deliver me from many waters: from the hand of strange children:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Whose mouth hath spoken vanity: and their right hand is the right hand of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> To thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, I will sing a new <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/03301a.htm">-->canticle<!--</a>-->: on the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psaltery<!--</a>--> and an instrument of ten strings I will sing praises to thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Who givest <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a> to kings: who hast <a href="../cathen/12681a.htm">redeemed</a> thy servant <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> from the <a href="../cathen/07149b.htm">malicious</a> sword:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Deliver me, And rescue me out of the hand of strange children; whose mouth hath spoken vanity: and their right hand is the right hand of <a href="../cathen/14004b.htm">iniquity</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Whose <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> are as new plants in their youth: Their daughters decked out, adorned round about after the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07664a.htm">-->similitude<!--</a>--> of a <a href="../cathen/14495a.htm">temple</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Their storehouses full, flowing out of this into that. Their sheep fruitful in young, abounding in their goings forth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> Their oxen fat. There is no breach of wall, nor passage, nor crying out in their streets.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> They have called the people <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">happy</a>, that hath these things: but <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">happy</a> is that people whose <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa143001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Psalmus David. Adversus Goliath.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Benedictus Dominus Deus meus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui docet manus meas ad pr&aelig;lium,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et digitos meos ad bellum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Misericordia mea et refugium meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> susceptor meus et liberator meus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> protector meus, et in ipso speravi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui subdit populum meum sub me.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Domine, quid est homo, quia innotuisti ei?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> aut filius hominis, quia reputas eum?</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Homo vanitati similis factus est;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dies ejus sicut umbra pr&aelig;tereunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Domine, inclina c&aelig;los tuos, et descende;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> tange montes, et fumigabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Fulgura coruscationem, et dissipabis eos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> emitte sagittas tuas, et conturbabis eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Emitte manum tuam de alto: eripe me,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et libera me de aquis multis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> de manu filiorum alienorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143008vul">8</span>&nbsp;quorum os locutum est vanitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dextera eorum dextera iniquitatis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Deus, canticum novum cantabo tibi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in psalterio decachordo psallam tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Qui das salutem regibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui redemisti David servum tuum de gladio maligno,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143011vul">11</span>&nbsp;eripe me, et erue me de manu filiorum alienorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> quorum os locutum est vanitatem,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dextera eorum dextera iniquitatis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143012vul">12</span>&nbsp;Quorum filii sicut novell&aelig; plantationes in juventute sua;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> fili&aelig; eorum composit&aelig;,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> circumornat&aelig; ut similitudo templi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Promptuaria eorum plena, eructantia ex hoc in illud;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> oves eorum f&oelig;tos&aelig;, abundantes in egressibus suis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143014vul">14</span>&nbsp;boves eorum crass&aelig;.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Non est ruina maceri&aelig;, neque transitus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> neque clamor in plateis eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa143015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Beatum dixerunt populum cui h&aelig;c sunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> beatus populus cujus Dominus Deus ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
