<h1>Psalm 144</h1>
<div class="h1a">A psalm of praise, to the infinite majesty of God.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 145</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa143.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 144</strong>.</span></p></span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Praise, for <a href="../cathen/04642b.htm">David</a> himself.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem">I will extol thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> my king: and I will <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> for ever; yea, for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Every day will I <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thee: and I will praise thy <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> for ever; yea, for ever and ever.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Great is the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, and greatly to be praised: and of his greatness there is no end.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">-->Generation<!--</a>--> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> shall praise thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->: and they shall declare thy power.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> They shall speak of the magnificence of the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of thy <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holiness</a>: and shall tell thy wondrous <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> And they shall speak of the might of thy terrible <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->acts<!--</a>-->: and shall declare thy greatness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> They shall publish the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/10174a.htm">-->memory<!--</a>--> of the <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->abundance<!--</a>--> of thy sweetness: and shall rejoice in thy <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">justice</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is gracious and merciful: patient and plenteous in mercy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is sweet to all: and his tender mercies are over all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Let all thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->, O lord, praise thee: and let thy <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> thee.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> They shall speak of the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">-->kingdom<!--</a>-->: and shall tell of thy power:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> To make thy might <a href="../cathen/08673a.htm">known</a> to the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01148a.htm">-->sons<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>: and the <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> of the magnificence of thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">-->kingdom<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> Thy <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">-->kingdom<!--</a>--> is a <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08646a.htm">-->kingdom<!--</a>--> of all ages: and thy dominion endureth throughout all <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generations</a>. The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->faithful<!--</a>--> in all his words: and <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> in all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> lifteth up all that fall: and setteth up all that are cast down.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse15">15</span> The eyes of all <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> in thee, O <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and thou givest them meat in due season.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse16">16</span> Thou openest thy hand, and fillest with <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">blessing</a> every <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->living<!--</a>--> creature.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse17">17</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a> in all his ways: and <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> in all his <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01115a.htm">-->works<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse18">18</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is nigh unto all them that call upon him: to all that call upon him in <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse19">19</span> He will do the <a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">will</a> of them that fear him: and he will hear their <a href="../cathen/12345b.htm">prayer</a>, and <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">-->save<!--</a>--> them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse20">20</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> keepeth all them that <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">love</a> him; but all the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> he will destroy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse21">21</span> My mouth shall speak the praise of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: and let all flesh <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">bless</a> his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> forever; yea, for ever and ever.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa144001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Laudatio ipsi David.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Exaltabo te, Deus meus rex,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et benedicam nomini tuo in s&aelig;culum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Per singulos dies benedicam tibi,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et laudabo nomen tuum in s&aelig;culum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Magnus Dominus, et laudabilis nimis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et magnitudinis ejus non est finis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Generatio et generatio laudabit opera tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et potentiam tuam pronuntiabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Magnificentiam glori&aelig; sanctitatis tu&aelig; loquentur,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et mirabilia tua narrabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Et virtutem terribilium tuorum dicent,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et magnitudinem tuam narrabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Memoriam abundanti&aelig; suavitatis tu&aelig; eructabunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et justitia tua exsultabunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Miserator et misericors Dominus:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> patiens, et multum misericors.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Suavis Dominus universis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et miserationes ejus super omnia opera ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Confiteantur tibi, Domine, omnia opera tua,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sancti tui benedicant tibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Gloriam regni tui dicent,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et potentiam tuam loquentur:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144012vul">12</span>&nbsp;ut notam faciant filiis hominum potentiam tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gloriam magnificenti&aelig; regni tui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144013vul">13</span>&nbsp;Regnum tuum regnum omnium s&aelig;culorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et dominatio tua in omni generatione et generationem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Fidelis Dominus in omnibus verbis suis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sanctus in omnibus operibus suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Allevat Dominus omnes qui corruunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et erigit omnes elisos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144015vul">15</span>&nbsp;Oculi omnium in te sperant, Domine,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et tu das escam illorum in tempore opportuno.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144016vul">16</span>&nbsp;Aperis tu manum tuam,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et imples omne animal benedictione.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144017vul">17</span>&nbsp;Justus Dominus in omnibus viis suis,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sanctus in omnibus operibus suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144018vul">18</span>&nbsp;Prope est Dominus omnibus invocantibus eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> omnibus invocantibus eum in veritate.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144019vul">19</span>&nbsp;Voluntatem timentium se faciet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et deprecationem eorum exaudiet, et salvos faciet eos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144020vul">20</span>&nbsp;Custodit Dominus omnes diligentes se,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnes peccatores disperdet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa144021vul">21</span>&nbsp;Laudationem Domini loquetur os meum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et benedicat omnis caro nomini sancto ejus in s&aelig;culum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
