<h1>Psalm 145</h1>
<div class="h1a">We are not to trust in men, but in God alone.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in most modern Bible translations, this psalm is called <strong>Psalm 146</strong>, and the <strong><a href="../bible/psa144.htm">previous psalm</a></strong> is known as <strong>Psalm 145</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>, of <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/01209d.htm">-->Aggeus<!--</a>--> and <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Zacharias<!--</a>-->.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, O my <a href="../cathen/14153a.htm">soul</a>, in my <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/09238c.htm">-->life<!--</a>--> I will praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>: I will sing to my <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> as long as I shall be. Put not your trust in princes:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> In the children of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>, in whom there is no <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> His <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/14220b.htm">-->spirit<!--</a>--> shall go forth, and he shall return into his earth: in that day all their thoughts shall perish.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> <a href="../cathen/02599b.htm">Blessed</a> is he who hath the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Jacob</a> for his helper, whose <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> is in the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> his <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> Who made <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and earth, the sea, and all things that are in them.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Who keepeth <a href="../cathen/15073a.htm">truth</a> for ever: who <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12565a.htm">-->executeth<!--</a>--> judgment for them that suffer wrong: who giveth food to the hungry. The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> looseth them that are fettered:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> enlighteneth the blind. The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> lifteth up them that are cast down: the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> <a href="../cathen/09397a.htm">loveth</a> the <a href="../cathen/08571c.htm">just</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> keepeth the strangers, he will support the <a href="../cathen/11322b.htm">fatherless</a> and the <a href="../cathen/15617c.htm">widow</a>: and the ways of sinners he <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/15624a.htm">-->will<!--</a>--> destroy.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> shall reign for ever: thy <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a>, O <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">-->Sion<!--</a>-->, unto <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a> and <a href="../cathen/06412c.htm">generation</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa145001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja, Agg&aelig;i et Zachari&aelig;.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001"><span class="verse" id="psa145002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Lauda, anima mea, Dominum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Laudabo Dominum in vita mea;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallam Deo meo quamdiu fuero.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Nolite confidere in principibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145003vul">3</span>&nbsp;in filiis hominum, in quibus non est salus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Exibit spiritus ejus, et revertetur in terram suam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in illa die peribunt omnes cogitationes eorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Beatus cujus Deus Jacob adjutor ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> spes ejus in Domino Deo ipsius:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145006vul">6</span>&nbsp;qui fecit c&aelig;lum et terram,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> mare, et omnia qu&aelig; in eis sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Qui custodit veritatem in s&aelig;culum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> facit judicium injuriam patientibus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dat escam esurientibus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus solvit compeditos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Dominus illuminat c&aelig;cos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus erigit elisos;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Dominus diligit justos.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145009vul">9</span>&nbsp;Dominus custodit advenas,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pupillum et viduam suscipiet,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et vias peccatorum disperdet.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa145010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Regnabit Dominus in s&aelig;cula;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deus tuus, Sion, in generationem et generationem.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
