<h1>Psalm 146</h1>
<div class="h1a">An exhortation to praise God for his benefits.</div>
<p><span class="stiki">Does this psalm differ from what you were expecting? Don't be confused. There are two systems for arranging the psalms: the <strong>Septuagint</strong> and the <strong>Masoretic</strong>. We use the Septuagint system here. In the Masoretic system, which is used in many popular Bible translations, the psalm below is combined with the <strong><a href="../bible/psa147.htm">next psalm</a></strong> to form <strong>Psalm 147</strong>.</span></p>

<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.<!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>, because <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/12533a.htm">-->psalm<!--</a>--> is <a href="../cathen/06636b.htm">good</a>: to our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> be <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">-->joyful<!--</a>--> and comely praise.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> buildeth up <a href="../cathen/08344a.htm">Jerusalem</a>: he will gather together the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/04775c.htm">-->dispersed<!--</a>--> of <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Who healeth the broken of heart, and bindeth up their bruises.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Who telleth the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11151a.htm">-->number<!--</a>--> of the stars: and calleth them all by their <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">names</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Great is our <!--k03--><!--<a href="../cathen/xxyyyk.htm">-->Lord<!--</a>-->, and great is his power: and of his wisdom there is no <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/11151a.htm">-->number<!--</a>-->.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> lifteth up the <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/07543b.htm">-->meek<!--</a>-->, and bringeth the <a href="../cathen/05649a.htm">wicked</a> down even to the ground.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> with praise: sing to our <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> upon the harp.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Who covereth the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> with clouds, and prepareth rain for the earth. Who maketh grass to grow on the mountains, and herbs for the service of <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Who giveth to beasts their food: and to the young ravens that call upon him.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> He shall not delight in the strength of the horse: nor take pleasure in the legs of a <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">man</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> The <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> taketh pleasure in them that <!--k07--><!--<a href="../cathen/06021a.htm">-->fear<!--</a>--> him: and in them that <a href="../cathen/07465b.htm">hope</a> in his mercy.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa146001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Laudate Dominum, quoniam bonus est psalmus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Deo nostro sit jucunda, decoraque laudatio.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146002vul">2</span>&nbsp;&AElig;dificans Jerusalem Dominus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dispersiones Isra&euml;lis congregabit:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146003vul">3</span>&nbsp;qui sanat contritos corde,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et alligat contritiones eorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146004vul">4</span>&nbsp;qui numerat multitudinem stellarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et omnibus eis nomina vocat.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Magnus Dominus noster, et magna virtus ejus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et sapienti&aelig; ejus non est numerus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Suscipiens mansuetos Dominus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> humilians autem peccatores usque ad terram.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Pr&aelig;cinite Domino in confessione;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> psallite Deo nostro in cithara.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146008vul">8</span>&nbsp;Qui operit c&aelig;lum nubibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et parat terr&aelig; pluviam;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qui producit in montibus f&oelig;num,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et herbam servituti hominum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146009vul">9</span>&nbsp;qui dat jumentis escam ipsorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et pullis corvorum invocantibus eum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146010vul">10</span>&nbsp;Non in fortitudine equi voluntatem habebit,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> nec in tibiis viri beneplacitum erit ei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa146011vul">11</span>&nbsp;Beneplacitum est Domino super timentes eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et in eis qui sperant super misericordia ejus.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
