<h1>Psalm 148</h1> <!--ce=n-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> from the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: praise ye him in the high places.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Praise ye him, all his <a href="../cathen/01476d.htm">angels</a>, praise ye him, all his <a href="../cathen/13286a.htm">hosts</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Praise ye him, O sun and moon: praise him, all ye stars and light.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Praise him, ye <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a> of <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a>: and let all the waters that are above the <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heavens</a></span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Praise the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. For he spoke, and they were made: he commanded, and they were <a href="../cathen/04470a.htm">created</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> He hath established them for ever, and for ages of ages: he hath made a decree, and it shall not pass away.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> Praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> from the earth, ye dragons, and all ye <a href="../cathen/01075d.htm">deeps</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> Fire, hail, snow, ice, stormy winds, which fulfil his word:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> Mountains and all hills, fruitful trees and all <a href="../cathen/03473a.htm">cedars</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse10">10</span> Beasts and all cattle: serpents and feathered fowls:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse11">11</span> Kings of the earth and all people: princes and all judges of the earth:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse12">12</span> Young <a href="../cathen/09580c.htm">men</a> and maidens: let the old with the younger, praise the <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> of the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse13">13</span> For his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> alone is exalted.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse14">14</span> The praise of him is above <a href="../cathen/07170a.htm">heaven</a> and earth: and he hath exalted the horn of his people. A hymn to all his <a href="../cathen/01800b.htm">saints</a> to the <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">children of Israel</a>, a people approaching to him. <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa148001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Laudate Dominum de c&aelig;lis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum in excelsis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum, omnes angeli ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum, omnes virtutes ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum, sol et luna;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum, omnes stell&aelig; et lumen.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum, c&aelig;li c&aelig;lorum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et aqu&aelig; omnes qu&aelig; super c&aelig;los sunt,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148005vul">5</span>&nbsp;laudent nomen Domini.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Quia ipse dixit, et facta sunt;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ipse mandavit, et creata sunt.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Statuit ea in &aelig;ternum, et in s&aelig;culum s&aelig;culi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> pr&aelig;ceptum posuit, et non pr&aelig;teribit.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148007vul">7</span>&nbsp;Laudate Dominum de terra,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> dracones et omnes abyssi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148008vul">8</span>&nbsp;ignis, grando, nix, glacies, spiritus procellarum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> qu&aelig; faciunt verbum ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148009vul">9</span>&nbsp;montes, et omnes colles;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> ligna fructifera, et omnes cedri;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148010vul">10</span>&nbsp;besti&aelig;, et universa pecora;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> serpentes, et volucres pennat&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148011vul">11</span>&nbsp;reges terr&aelig; et omnes populi;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> principes et omnes judices terr&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148012vul">12</span>&nbsp;juvenes et virgines; senes cum junioribus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudent nomen Domini:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148013vul">13</span>&nbsp;quia exaltatum est nomen ejus solius.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa148014vul">14</span>&nbsp;Confessio ejus super c&aelig;lum et terram;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltavit cornu populi sui.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Hymnus omnibus sanctis ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> filiis Isra&euml;l, populo appropinquanti sibi.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Alleluja.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
