<h1>Psalm 149</h1> <!--ce=n-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Sing ye to the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> a new canticle: let his praise be in the church of the <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Let <a href="../cathen/08193a.htm">Israel</a> rejoice in him that made him: and let the children of Sion be joyful in their king.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Let them praise his <a href="../cathen/10675a.htm">name</a> in choir: let them sing to him with the timbrel and the psaltery.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> For the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> is well pleased with his people: and he will exalt the meek unto <a href="../cathen/13407a.htm">salvation</a>.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> The <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a> shall rejoice in <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a>: they shall be joyful in their beds.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse6">6</span> The high praises of <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">God</a> shall be in their mouth: and two-edged swords in their hands:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse7">7</span> To execute vengeance upon the nations, chastisements among the people:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse8">8</span> To bind their kings with fetters, and their nobles with manacles of iron.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse9">9</span> To execute upon them the judgment that is written: this <a href="../cathen/06585a.htm">glory</a> is to all his <a href="../cathen/04171a.htm">saints</a>. <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa149001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Cantate Domino canticum novum;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laus ejus in ecclesia sanctorum.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149002vul">2</span>&nbsp;L&aelig;tetur Isra&euml;l in eo qui fecit eum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et filii Sion exsultent in rege suo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Laudent nomen ejus in choro;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> in tympano et psalterio psallant ei.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Quia beneplacitum est Domino in populo suo,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et exaltabit mansuetos in salutem.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Exsultabunt sancti in gloria;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> l&aelig;tabuntur in cubilibus suis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Exaltationes Dei in gutture eorum,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et gladii ancipites in manibus eorum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149007vul">7</span>&nbsp;ad faciendam vindictam in nationibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> increpationes in populis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149008vul">8</span>&nbsp;ad alligandos reges eorum in compedibus,</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> et nobiles eorum in manicis ferreis;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa149009vul">9</span>&nbsp;ut faciant in eis judicium conscriptum:</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> gloria h&aelig;c est omnibus sanctis ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Alleluja.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
