<h1>Psalm 150</h1> <!--ce=n-->
<div class="h1a">Visit New Advent for the Summa Theologica, Church Fathers, Catholic Encyclopedia and more.</div>
<h2>English (Douay-Rheims)</h2>

<p><em><a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</em>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe000"><span class="verse" id="verse1">1</span> Praise ye the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a> in his <a href="../cathen/07386a.htm">holy</a> places: praise ye him in the <a href="../cathen/06079b.htm">firmament</a> of his power.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse2">2</span> Praise ye him for his mighty acts: praise ye him according to the multitude of his greatness.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse3">3</span> Praise him with the sound of trumpet: praise him with psaltery and harp.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse4">4</span> Praise him with timbrel and choir: praise him with strings and organs.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="verse5">5</span> Praise him on high sounding cymbals: praise him on cymbals of <a href="../cathen/07131b.htm">joy</a>: let every spirit praise the <a href="../cathen/06608a.htm">Lord</a>. <a href="../cathen/01319b.htm">Alleluia</a>.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>

<blockquote class="copyright">Old Testament first published 1609 by the English College at Douay<br />New Testament first published 1582 by the English College at Rheims<br />Revised and Annotated 1749 by Bishop Richard Challoner<br /><em>Imprimatur.</em> +James Cardinal Gibbons, Archbishop of Baltimore, September 1, 1899</blockquote>

<h2>Latin (Clementine Vulgate)</h2>
<!--propar--><p class="bibleprose"><span class="pro000"><span class="verse" id="psa150001vul">1</span>&nbsp;Alleluja.</span><!--/propar--></p>
<!--poepar--><blockquote class="biblepoem"><span class="poe001">Laudate Dominum in sanctis ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum in firmamento virtutis ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa150002vul">2</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum in virtutibus ejus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum secundum multitudinem magnitudinis ejus.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa150003vul">3</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum in sono tub&aelig;;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum in psalterio et cithara.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa150004vul">4</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum in tympano et choro;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum in chordis et organo.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa150005vul">5</span>&nbsp;Laudate eum in cymbalis benesonantibus;</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> laudate eum in cymbalis jubilationis.</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"><span class="verse" id="psa150006vul">6</span>&nbsp;Omnis spiritus laudet Dominum!</span><!--poebre--><br />
<span class="poe002"> Alleluja.</span><!--poepar--></blockquote>
